ItemDescription: A modern interpretation of the purity of form of Greek and Roman columns, the 4-light Hera Flush Mount features glass cylinder rods to provide the exterior frame of this hex-shaped fixture. The vintage silver finish on the delicate steel frame and candelabra lighting lend a classical quality that's totally transitional. Additional pipe available (PIPE-126).

Indulge your inner classicist with this demure two-light pendant. The glass opal shade and heritage brass accents are timeless design choices that will elevate any setting. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Classic mid-century style is explored through the clean lines and organic curves displayed in this pendant. An opal glass globe looks stunning suspended from a steel pipe finished in bronze, creating a look that transcends time. The capped top adds dimension and helps create a warm, free-flowing glow. A statement piece for any space. Additional pipe available (PIPE-105).

Classic mid-century style is explored through the clean lines and organic curves displayed in this pendant. An opal glass globe looks stunning suspended from a steel pipe finished in pale brass, creating a look that transcends time. The capped top adds dimension and helps create a warm, free-flowing glow. A statement piece for any space. Additional pipe available (PIPE-419).

The simple and sophisticated style of this sconce goes a long way. This clear, fluted glass fixture features a vintage silver belt that cinches the shape, adding a polished element to its textured form. Versatile, this piece works well in almost any style setting. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

A straightforward examination of the basic principles of design takes place with this semi-flush pendant. A sleek steel shade in a polished nickel finish frames this 3-light fixture, which features an acrylic diffuser that is suspended from within. The balance and contrast of materials delivers a fundamental visual aesthetic that transcends time and style. Also available in antique brass (49266), heritage brass (49267) and bronze (49268) finishes. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Keep your bedtime reads well-lit with this simply stunning wall sconce. The adjustable position of the sleek steel frame makes it the perfect task light for bedrooms or directional lighting option for an entryway. Spotlight a space by pairing with another for an even more dramatic lightscape. Also available in antique brass and bronze finishes. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Modern desires take the lead on this contemporary candelabra design. Light and airy, Griffith masters simplistic sophistication. Suspended from decorative piping, the steel frame is finished in antique brass and paired with two-tone ivory/clear crystal rods. Also available in heritage brass (DP89001). Additional chain available (CHN-200).

Let the austere grandeur of this white snow marble mirror effortlessly elevate a space. Snow marble and antique brass keystones frame a round plain mirror, delivering the right amount of drama to its luxe style. The textural yet polished frame delivers maximum luster when hung over a vanity or console. Hung with a security cleat attachment. Marble may vary.

This mirror is the design equivalent to adding diamonds to wear with your evening gown. Its pure and classic elegance is what makes it stunning, with details including a vintage silver finish, refined beaded trim and etched line carvings. This beauty hangs both vertically or diagonally to fit the look you’re aiming for. Mirror is trimmed with a bevel edge. Hangs on a security cleat attachment. Also comes in antique brass (6874).

A natural twist on the traditional sunburst design, this handcrafted beaut makes a staggering statement in any style setting. Driftwood branches in a hand-painted whitewash finish are styled around a small plain round mirror to create a striking decorative piece for a fireplace mantel or bedroom wall. Finish may vary.

No doubt this mirror was geometric inspired—it’s a wonderful combination of simple squares, rectangles and a central circle, all delicately trimmed in a polished nickel finish Each mirror is clear and features a bevel edge that elevates the look immensely. Can be hung vertically or horizontally for versatility. Hangs on a security cleat attachment. Also available in antique brass (2198).
Rectangular wall mirror framed with interlocking pieces of natural driftwood in a white wash finish. Can be hung vertically or horizontally.

We drew inspiration from our Gemma Collection to create a luxe box that is both captivating and functional. The arresting hue of the champagne crystal softens the defined edges of the diamond-like facets that shape this dimensional piece. The top swivels for easy opening and secure storage, making this is a great keepsake box for mementos and other prized possessions.

Inspired by elements of industrial mechanics, this porcelain lamp is both edgy and elegant. The base has dramatic angles and channels that first must be expertly made, then the ivory crackle glaze is applied, where ink is carefully infused to articulate the crackle. This blend of industrial design with the softness of a glossy, textural glaze creates visual movement and makes this piece totally versatile. It is topped with an ivory microfiber drum shade with white cotton lining.

You may recognize this urn-shaped vase from ancient Greek art. It was once a common vessel for water, wine and oil to be transported and served in royal palaces. Its form transcends time, as evidenced by this modern version, crafted in blown glass. Clear handles accent an opal white structure with a top layer of glass that's dappled with gold metallic highlights. Also comes in a small vase (7416).

You may recognize this urn-shaped vase from ancient Greek art. It was once a common vessel for water, wine and oil to be transported and served in royal palaces. Its form transcends time, as evidenced by this modern version, crafted in blown glass. Clear handles accent an opal white structure with a top layer of glass that's dappled with gold metallic highlights.

This natural iron box with hinged lid has a band of faceted iron shards running across the sides and top. It is the perfect size for letterhead or important documents, or you can even use it to store your watches. The bottom is lined in black microsuede to protect your treasures.
This mouth blown white cased glass sculpture is mounted on a thick crystal base. It will make quite a statement no matter where you choose to display it. Size may vary.

Composed of leather in a dove gray finish with an exposed stitch trim and an antique brass rod detail, our Taft Box will revive your desktop's presence by keeping it organized. As one continuous piece with a hinged lid, this box neatly conceals important documents and other desktop items in a clutch-like fashion. Leather may vary.
Set of 2 handmade whitewashed wood boxes offer storage and add a linear and artistic element to a bathroom counter, console, or nightstand.

Simple but dazzling, this massive faux marble carved vase is fantastic in pairs. Use it on the mantle, on cabinets and buffets on the dining table or as a singularly stunning centerpiece for large stemmed flowers or branches. Features a removable clear glass insert. Finish may vary.
These handmade wood boxes offer storage and add a linear and artistic element to a bathroom counter, console, or nightstand.

This natural indigo leather box is the perfect size for safely storing jewelry, keepsakes and miscellaneous items. The fine execution of the antique brass inlay, which runs across the top to the center of the arched bottom, delivers a refined element to its natural materials. The inside is lined with a suede interior to protect your treasures. Antique brass feet keep the box slightly raised, which adds an additional element of classic style. Leather may vary.

Exquisitely crafted, the Alek game box is sure to draw admirers. The black oak and faux quill detailing lends an heirloom quality, versatile enough to sit pretty on a cocktail table or tuck away in a library or salon Perfect for an impromptu game night, the wooden box comes outfitted with one deck of National cards, one deck of High Victorian cards and two sets of poker chips.

Revered in ancient Egypt, the scarab is a sacred status symbol that has adorned designs for centuries. The antique brass motif sits atop a small decorative box in an opulent black hide. The black velvet liner is a subtle detail that adds another layer of refinement. Hide may vary. Also available in gray hide (4511).

Revered in ancient Egypt, the scarab is a sacred status symbol that has adorned designs for centuries. The antique brass motif sits atop two decorative boxes in an opulent grey hide. The grey suede liner is a subtle detail that adds another layer of refinement. Hide may vary. Also available in black hide (4508).

The subtle accents, rich wood grain, and a deep ebony finish of this handsomely crafted oak box make it stand out from just any old container. Just a peek of brass from the lid forms the handle, with hidden brass hinges that reveal themselves when you open the top. Inside, the bottom is lined with black velvet to keep items from shifting too much and helping to keep the box pristine. Also comes in a large size (6879).

This natural indigo leather box is the perfect size for safely storing jewelry, keepsakes and miscellaneous items. The fine execution of the antique brass inlay, which runs across the top to the center of the arched bottom, delivers a refined element to its natural materials. The inside is lined with a suede interior to protect your treasures. Antique brass feet keep the box slightly raised, which adds an additional element of classic style. Leather may vary.
White marble and antique brass inlay give a modern take on this cocktail table. The natural iron base adds more dimension. Marble may vary.

The subtle accents, rich wood grain and a deep ebony finish of this handsomely crafted oak box make it stand out from just any old container. Just a peek of brass from the lid forms the handle, with hidden brass hinges that reveal themselves when you open the top. Inside, the bottom is lined with black velvet to keep items from shifting too much and helping to keep the box pristine. Also comes in a small size (6878).

Deep, elegant tufting comes together with soft curves and a champagne-finished swivel base to create the classically stylish Capri Chair. Covered in Muslin, allowing you to slipcover or reupholster in the fabric of your choice.
Covered in Muslin, allowing you to slipcover or upholster in the fabric of your choice.

Whether a place to gather your things in an entryway or as a decorative seat at the foot of a bed, this mid-century modern inspired bench has one-of-a-kind looks. Bronze-finish tapered legs raise a plush, button-tufted seat, wrapped in a muslin base. The angles of the bench and updated upholstery give it a hint of contemporary style. Covered in muslin, allowing you to slipcover or upholster in the fabric of your choice. Also comes in watercrest velvet (4549) and armor chenille (4550).
Ebony and ivory are classics together. Beautiful, oversized blackened steel sabots anchor the angular form of the cerused white oak table. Pair with the Lionel Small Console (DJ5004) for nesting.

A true standout, the George Sofa could never be backed against a wall. The steel details on the charcoal wood frame are reminiscent of extending tree branches. We affectionately refer to this sofa as the treehouse. A very chic treehouse at that! Covered in Muslin, allowing you to slipcover or upholster in the fabric of your choice.

Tables similar to this one were quite popular in parlors and salons in the early 20th century. The Percy End Table has the same elevated feel, but with a modern edge. Three round tiers are seamlessly welded together from polished stainless steel. Each layer is set with a plate of plain-mirrored glass for added shine and elegance. Also comes in antique brass finish with antiqued mirror (2032) and zinc finish with antiqued mirror (2028).

Over 50 iron rods are welded by hand to create each of these side tables. Expert craftsmen mold each piece and weld them to the structure, creating a seamless look from top to bottom. It’s then finished in a brushed nickel metallic and a disk of plain mirror glass is inset, all giving it ultimate shine. Pair it with the matching end table (6925) and pendant lamp (84013). Also comes in antique brass (6920).

The Elton Dining Table is laden with intricate design details that will make this a cherished heirloom for years to come. Blonde oak veneers and solids, a series of gold rings resembling nuts and bolts and the octagonal shape work together to make a strong statement. Perfect in a dining room or grand entryway.

Over 50 iron rods are welded by hand to create each of these end tables. Expert craftsmen mold each piece and weld them to the structure, creating a seamless look from top to bottom. It’s then finished in a brushed nickel metallic and a disk of plain mirror glass is inset, all giving it ultimate shine. Pair it with the matching side table (6921) and pendant lamp (84013). Also comes in antique brass (6924).

Sleek. Simple. Sophisticated. This cocktail table is modern elegance realized. Seamlessly crafted in stainless steel, it is finished in a polished nickel finish, yet with slightly natural touches that recall a sort of Japanese Wabi-Sabi balance. The top is plated in beveled mirror glass to not only elevate the look even further, but to add light and shine. Pairs with the Marcus Console (6909) and Marcus End Table (6919).

Black and white pattern play on this hair-on-hide barstool contrasts beautifully with the modern polished nickel legs. The sleek profile makes these perfect for tucking under a bar. Hide may vary. Also available in Dove Gray (2857).

ItemName: Avebury Off-White Linen Bench Slipcover Only
ItemDescription: This slipcover is designed to fit the Avebury Bench.

The perfect armchair, Nicola is plush and inviting while maintaining a natural sense of refinement. The exposed solid maple frame is expertly crafted, featuring curved arms, legs and accents finished in a deep umber stain. The frame is further accentuated by the Mediterranean Texture fabric, a linen weave with flecks of blue, brown and gold.

Whether a place to gather your things in an entryway or as a decorative seat at the foot of a bed, this handsome, mid-century modern inspired bench has one-of-a-kind looks. Bronze-finish tapered legs raise a plush, button-tufted seat, wrapped in unique, geometric-pattern velvet. The slight angles of the bench and updated upholstery give it a hint of contemporary style. Also comes in armor chenille (4550) and muslin (4551).
Jessie Ottoman Mojave Embroidery

Reflective and ever-so intriguing, this tall mirror is crafted from hand-distressed mirror tiles, artfully inlaid within an iron trim to form a patchwork design. Set in a thick plaque with matching iron trim, its simplicity in form is what gives it such sophistication. Also available in rectangular form (6479). Antique mirror finish may vary.
Jessie Ottoman Citron Texture

Individual iron rods are welded together and finished in silver leaf to create this fresh interpretation of the French-inspired starburst design. The round shape looks great alone or in multiples. Hung with security cleat attachment. Silver leaf finish may vary. Also available in antiqued gold leaf (2134).

The dark and moody border of this bold mirror was inspired by the antiqued distressing of our Luxembourg Mirrors. The mirror tiles that form the border get their intensity from a handmade process that involves applying a finish that then undergoes a chemical reaction. Once completed, the result is a nearly opaque surface that’s rich with organic texture beneath the glass surface. The plain glass mirror in the center makes this version more functional than its decorative counterpart.

The more practical relative of the antique dragon etched counterpart, this mirror, still held in place by dramatic antique brass talons, is left clear in the center and framed with a smoky, irregular rim of antiqued mirror. Perfect in a chic powder room or in pairs over small consoles or cabinets. Features a security cleat attachment. Can be hung vertically or horizontally. Also available in antiqued dragon etched (DD2084). Finish may vary.

Richly applied brushstrokes in a brilliant chemical oxidation creates the Modernist Art aesthetic of this bold mirror. To create the tonal variance, artisans apply the textures by hand in layers, then leaving the organic chemical processes to do the rest—making each mirror unique. Its round, unframed structure makes a minimalist statement, so this mirror transcends singular style to fit in just about anywhere, whether paired over a vanity or displayed above a console.

Hovering ever-so-slightly against the wall, this brilliant mirror performs “depth-defying” feats in a space. Two polished nickel brackets hold a plain glass mirror, which has rounded edges for a softer look. Can be hung vertically or horizontally depending on the wall space. Hangs on two security cleat attachments. Also available in antique brass (6872).
Round wall mirror with natural oyster shell frame is detailed with smaller oyster shells rimming inner and outer borders.

As brilliant as a newfound treasure trove, this glamourous mirror is an extraordinary find. The frame is crafted using large plates of semi-precious stones, created through purely organic processes. The dazzling array of colors and textures comes from the differences in elements that are infused while the crystallization process is in effect, which means each mirror the artisan creates will be truly unique in almost every way. For a touch of added glamour, the mirror has a slight bevel.

Thousands of years ago, this mirror was first being created. How is that? The frame is crafted using large pieces of petrified wood, created through an organic process of heat and pressure. The dazzling array of colors and textures comes from the differences in woods and elements that are infused while the petrifying process is in effect, which means each mirror the artisan creates will be truly unique in almost every way. For a touch of added glamour, the mirror has a slight bevel.

A truly one-of-a-kind piece, the Jude Mirror's starburst-patterned antiquing amidst a convex mirror draws attention from all angles. Also available in small (2865) and medium (4104). Feature a security cleat attachment. Finishes may vary.

Featuring a frame of alternating rippled antiqued mirrored glass tiles, the Isabel Rectangular Mirror is a subtle, softened industrial piece of decor. With the beveled mirror and textured panel frame, Isabel is an easy way to add layers and depth to a space. Hung with security cleat attachment. Square mirror (2942) also available. Finish may vary.

The Hana Mirror is highlighted by its antiqued mirror border that gives way to a plain mirrored surface. Contrasting mirror finishes are accentuated by antique brass details and gold painted wooden frame. Can be hung horizontally or vertically. Features security cleat attachement. Finish may vary.

This elegant ovoid mirror is held in place by an organic cluster of antique brass leafy branches that conceal a small ledge at the plain mirror's base. Perfect for a scented candle, figurine or objet d'art. Use it over a console or in a glamorous powder room. Hung with a security cleat attachment.
An iconic frameless convex mirror. Features a security cleat attachement. Large mirror (2885) also available.

Featuring a frame of alternating rippled antiqued mirrored glass tiles, the Isabel Square Mirror is a subtle, softened industrial piece of decor. With a beveled mirror and textured panel frame, Isabel is an easy way to add layers and depth to a space. Hung with security cleat attachment. Rectangular mirror (2944) also available. Finish may vary.
Jasmine Mirror
Pitney Mirror

Why mount your favorite treasure when it can float? Windsor Smith transformed a classical pedestal shelf into illusionistic display using a clear acrylic top. Smoky gray lacquer resin completes its modern transformation. Lovely paired with our Larissa urn or your own collected treasures, this piece bridges all styles of interiors.

A traditional window-frame form with an artisan-crafted accent. The Henrietta Mirror features a distressed painted rust frame encasing multiple panels of antiqued mirror. A striking fleur-de-lis etched pattern adorns the outer mirror pieces. Can be hung vertically or horizontally. Features a security cleat attachment. Finish may vary.
Keaton Large Mirror

This mirror is the design equivalent to adding diamonds to wear with your evening gown. Its pure and classic elegance is what makes it stunning, with details including an antique brass finish, refined beaded trim and etched line carvings. This beauty hangs both vertically or diagonally to fit the look you’re aiming for. Mirror is trimmed with a bevel edge. Hangs on a security cleat attachment. Also comes in vintage silver (6871).
Keaton Small Mirror

The artistry of this vase-shaped lamp is both unique and understated. Echoing a Moorish design, a faux marble base is shaped around an antique brass steel base to create the subtle play on geometrics. A simple braided design has been embossed onto the handles to add a textured element to the otherwise soft façade. When in use, the intricacy of the details are highlighted. Topped with an off-white linen drum shade with white cotton lining and a matching metal finial. Finish may vary.
Bransen Mirror

The classic shape of this lamp creates a timeless dynamic. White marble is at the forefront of this formation, offering a sleek and sophisticated appeal to its surroundings. Though the natural veining of the marble is slight, it delivers a visual texture that livens the smooth surface. An antique brass base works to elevate and accent this effortlessly stylish piece. Topped with a ash microfiber drum shade with off-white cotton lining and a matching metal finial. Finish may vary.

The Vinton Lamp: sculptural in form and dynamic by design. Four antique brass pillars pierce a rectangle faux marble base, expressing a clean, geometric form. The blend of materials work together to create an elegance that is even more so defined when illuminated by a brilliant bulb. Its open design delivers an airiness and adds a dimensional quality to its textural properties. Topped with a tapered off-white microfiber shade with off-white cotton lining and a matching finial. Finish may vary

Elegance is defined by the simple form and classic design of this lamp. Sharp, clean lines frame the column silhouette of the solid snow marble structure that has been fitted on an antique brass steel base, which acts as a functional and stylish accent. When in use, the opaque structure catches the light and appears to almost glow. A cornerstone for any space. Topped with a rectangle off-white microfiber shade with off-white cotton lining and a matching metal finial. Finish may vary.

Clean, sweeping lines trace the classic capsule shape of this sleek and stylish lamp. An ivory crackle finish breaks beautifully over the ceramic form that blends seamlessly into antique brass steel, lending a mid-century modern allure. Displayed on a clear canine crystal base, so the fixture appears to be floating. Topped with a pewter microfiber drum shade with off-white cotton lining and a matching metal finial. Finish may vary.

Our Whitman Lamp draws inspiration from modern design and natural materials. The sleek cylindrical form is composed of a smoke crystal top and a faux marble bottom that are divided by a pale brass belt, which accents, as well as contrasts, these two materials. A luxe lighting option for any space. Topped with a ash microfiber drum shade with ash microfiber lining and a matching metal finial. Finish may vary.

Evoke the essence of modern sculpture with this arresting table lamp. Six faux marble disks descend an antique brass frame, increasing and then decreasing in size before reaching the circular base. The polished profile exceeds expectations as it showcases as a visual work of art. Elegant and engaging, this structural piece delivers suave sophistication sofa side or bedside. Topped with a putty microfiber drum shade with putty cotton lining and a matching metal finial. Finish may vary.

Let the Uriah Lamp elevate your table top to museum status. A thick, seedy slumped glass in a smoke luster finish cascades down the front of a snow marble wall to create this functional showpiece. The use of mixed materials that shape this rectangular form brings a refined organic element to a space. Topped with a rectangle off-white microfiber shade with off-white cotton lining and a matching metal finial. Finish may vary.

The unique form of this lamp creates interest and intrigue. The sculptural faux marble base has been shaped into an arched, open design that brings forth a dimensional quality to the space it occupies. The entire structure is fashioned to a hexagon-shaped antique brass base for an additional geometric appeal. Its narrow silhouette makes it a great beside luminary. Topped with an ivory microfiber drum shade and a matching metal finial. Finish may vary.

Rich textures and smooth surfaces work as one to create the striking aesthetics of this lamp. Opal glass is blown into a bottom-heavy hourglass shape and is trimmed with hand-etched gold leaf scallops that add a refined yet textural element. A great addition to a modern-coastal environment. Topped with a white microfiber drum shade with gold foil lining. Finish may vary.

It takes excellence and expert knowledge in glassblowing to create the tapered bottle form of this lamp, which is created by taking a base glass and then adding stems of colored glass to create unique patterns. This one has a white base glass with deep, contrasting black swirls that make it undeniably modern. Adding to its modern appeal is a square acrylic base. Topped with a tapered microfiber shade in black with a white cotton lining. Glass designs will vary

Layers upon layers of glossy white glaze is necessary in order to create the immense details in this ceramic vase. All hand-applied, artists must apply each one separately before it’s fired, so that the glazes build on top of each other, rather than blend. The effect is a piece that is rich in tonal depth and classic design. It is topped with an off-white linen drum shade with white cotton lining. Finish may vary.

Standing proudly on its gold-leafed wooden base, the Phoebe Lamp beholds elegance and modernity so beautifully. The bottle form is made from art glass, where glassblowers incorporate stems of colored glass into a base to form patterns and textures. In this, a clear base is infused with opal glass to create a look that’s swirling and smoky. It is topped with a tapered white microfiber shade that has a gold foil interior, so it glows brilliantly when switched on. Finish may vary.

Inspired by mid-century design, this table lamp has a stacked figure silhouette that nearly looks like an abstract human silhouette. The top dome shape is made from snow marble, which naturally has a range of tones that give it rich texture and subtle color. The conical base is crafted from walnut with a brass-plated ring and band, adding to its textures and organic sensibility. It is topped with an off-white silk tapered shade with white cotton lining. Finish may vary.

Entirely unique, this terracotta lamp is made completely by hand. It’s first formed on the potter’s wheel, then is handed off to another group of artists to add all of the dappled textures by hand. The gloss white finish has a slight crackle and is formulated especially for this piece to accentuate and draw out all the handcrafted elements. It’s a remarkable piece that brings artistic design to lighting. It is topped with a natural linen drum shade with white cotton lining.

One-of-a-kind in nearly every way, the snow marble used to make this lamp is unique and luxurious. It’s made to feature a raw surface and edges, with an endless array of hues ranging from whites to ambers, so it has so much organic texture. The block of stone is elevated on a pale brass finished steel base. The lamp is topped with a rectangular ivory linen shade with white cotton lining. Marble may vary.

Rich in natural details, this white sand infused ceramic lamp is as artistic as it is divine. The grainy texture in the surface is from sand that's incorporated into clay before it's molded—the white tones are embedded in the clay, so the color will stay true longer. It is topped with a contrasting, slate gray linen drum shade. Finish may vary.

Opal-toned swirls swarm through the thinly cut glass in this artistically designed lamp. The glass plate is formed by hand, giving it organic edges and just a little texture, and it’s fitted to heritage-finished stainless steel. The swirled designs are also done by hand, so every lamp is going to be slightly different from one to the next. Topped with a tapered, rectangular shade in ivory cotton with an ivory cotton lining and matched heritage finish cube finial.

The dozens of honeycomb facets in the base of this lamp cast shadows within the design, giving it a mysterious and handsome quality. It’s crafted by hand from porcelain and is glazed in such a way that it develops an intricate crackle design. This amazing finish is done in pure white, so the textures are extraordinary. Topped with a drum shade in sepia linen with ivory cotton lining and a matching ceramic finial. Finish may vary.

The dozens of facets in the base of this lamp reflect light, making the design even more brilliant. It’s crafted by hand from ceramic and is glazed in such a way that it develops an intricate crackle design. This amazing finish is done in pure white, so the textures are extraordinary. Topped with a microfiber drum shade in wren with ivory cotton lining and a matching ceramic finial. Finish may vary.

The lamp base is a modern take on an 18th century French design, updated with clean lines and a soft, faux marble finish. These urns would be seen gracing gardens across the French countryside, set amongst palatial landscapes. It pairs perfectly with the Montgomery Urn (9565), Miranda Urn (9566) and Marietta Urn (9567). Topped with a tapered, microfiber drum shade in ivory with an eggshell cotton lining and matched faux marble finial.

Elegant in form and style, this table lamp defies the standard in lighting. Crafted from porcelain, it is finished with an uncommon, circular brushstroke texture in hues of ivory, ecru and shining gilt. It rests on a round, acrylic disk base Topped with a drum shade in beige linen with cotton lining and an acrylic ball finial. Glaze finish may vary. Also comes in patterned chambray (11018).

Wintery details glisten on the new Farrel Lamp. From the vintage silver band to the alluring snow marble, the Farrel masters effortless cool. The body features a corner cut-out that has been meticulously crafted to yield exacting angles. Topped with a rectangular ivory microfiber shade with a gray cord trim. Also available in white onyx/antique brass (49715-759). Marble may vary.

Clean lines and cool finishes are a winning combination on this tall and slender table lamp. The painted silver band is a delicate embellishment that pops on the white glossy ceramic body. Topped with a white microfiber drum shade, silver foil lining, and matching ceramic finial. Finish may vary.

This incredible carved faux marble lamp is inspired by a pair of large antique vases Barry found in India. Best in pairs to anchor the sides of a bed or large sofa, the sculptural surface of this base is highlighted by the lamplight itself. Just beautiful! Topped with an off-white linen drum shade, lined in gold foil, and matching antique brass finial. Finish may vary.

A glossy pearl finish adds the perfect amount of polish to this statuesque ceramic design. We decided to break up the trim silhouette by adding a sphere toward the base. Topped with an off-white linen drum shade and matching ceramic finial. Finish may vary.

Rustic yet refined, the Johan glass lamp is an obvious proponent of art in design. The metallic bronze glaze washes up the opal body with quiet finesse. French wired with a taupe cloth cord and topped with a tapered, light cinder microfiber drum shade. Finish may vary.

Crafted from hand-blown glass, the Ludwig Lamp features curved ridges that create a beautiful, uneven surface on the delicate vessel. The soft opal finish is magnified with metallic highlights speckled throughout the body. Topped with a beige sheer microfiber drum shade with matching lining. Finish may vary.
Lincoln Lamp

We took a minimalist approach when applying the reactive glaze on this classically designed table lamp. The light écru finished body is speckled with soft celadon markings that add subtle texture to the piece. Topped with a light gray cotton drum shade. Finish may vary.
Kayden Lamp

Light flows beautifully on the irregular carvings seen on all facets of this ivory porcelain design. Shadow play runs rampant with each groove creating three-dimensional contours. Topped with an off-white linen drum shade with a crinkled trim and matching ceramic finial.

A cousin of the Hopkins, the Hoover Lamp is a subtle artisan work of art. The porcelain Hoover becomes functional art with its white and dove gray finish, hand-painted patterns that evoke a sense of warmth and comfort. Topped with an ivory microfiber drum shade and matching white finial. Finish may vary.

From overlapping shapes to bevels on the base, our Taylor Lamp uses geometric blocking seamlessly. Finished in a textured, white plaster resin. Paired with a rectangular, cloud gray microfiber shade with white cotton lining. Finish may vary.

The Gormerly Lamp is an opal glass pillar that's more than meets the eye. Gormerly features crossing etched patterns that inspire touch and curiosity. Topped with a white linen drum shade. Finish may vary.

Intricately handmade details give this round chandelier sophistication in craftsmanship. It’s made entirely of iron and each of the four bulb shades and ceiling mount have wonderfully hammered relief, accentuated with the white gesso finish. The Mckenna Chandelier is rich with textures, contrasted with the polished brass interior central shade that scatters light downward. Gesso finish may vary.

Organic elegance is established with this lively luminescent. Coconut shell beads are cut by hand and then woven onto a metal frame to create the distinct and winsome form of this chandelier. The winter white finish adds an airiness to the incredibly detailed structure that functions well in traditional and coastal settings. Finish may vary. Additional chain available (CHN-205).

Let coastal elegance live vibrantly in a space with this exotic chandelier. Thousands of pieces of hand-carved coconut shell are threaded together to drape freely on three tiers of rings. The top ring is concealed by a band of twine-wrapped fabric. It’s built from iron and the exposed metal has a natural finish that keeps with the organic look. Fitted for eight chandelier bulbs. Additional chain is available (CHN-128).

Sleek and sharp, the traditional shape of this mirror has been updated with a modern façade that offers deep but clean lines that add depth and dimension to a wall space. The lustrous design of the creamy ivory lacquer finish works with the cavernous double-wall frame to create a two-tone effect when caught in the right light. A stylish solution for everyday use over a vanity or in a powder room.

6-light chandelier with several tiers of wooden sticks on curved iron arms, all in a whitewash finish. The wooden dowels are placed atop pliable arms. When switched on, the light glows from within and transforms the space into something magical. During installation, please ensure that all bulbs are not touching any of the wooden dowels. If they are, gently press the arm away from the bulb about an inch to allow heat to properly disperse. Also comes in small (89559) and as a pendant (49558).

The simple, vessel-like silhouette of the popular Woodall Torchiere multiplies with the Woodall Chandelier. The four-light chandelier marries opal glass shades with a vintage silver steel frame, immediately drawing the eye with its rich, straightforward materials. Perfect for adding a warm glow and welcoming tone to any room. Additional pipe available (PIPE-126). Also available in antique brass (89445) and as a torchiere (49015). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

The simple, vessel-like silhouette of the popular Woodall Torchiere multiplies with the Woodall Chandelier. The four-light chandelier marries opal glass shades with an antique brass steel frame, immediately drawing the eye with its rich, straightforward materials. Perfect for adding a warm glow and welcoming tone to any room. Additional pipe available (PIPE-101). Also available in vintage silver (89461) and as a torchiere (49015). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Coral inspired, the small 8 light white lacquered resin chandelier is as dramatic as it is unique. The satin gold center sphere gives it just the right amount of bling. Shown with silver bowl globe bulbs. Additional pipe available PIPE-101. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

5-light chandelier with five tiers of wooden sticks on curved iron arms, all in a whitewash finish. The wooden dowels are placed atop pliable arms. During installation, please ensure that all bulbs are not touching any of the wooden dowels. If they are, gently press the arm away from the bulb about an inch to allow heat to properly disperse.

Coral inspired, the large 8 light white lacquered resin chandelier, is as dramatic as it is unique. The antique brass center sphere gives it just the right amount of bling. Photographed with silver tip globe bubs. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

This 12-light chandelier imparts classic elegance to the space it occupies. Tuxedo-style fluted clear glass shades are individually suspended from a pale brass steel frame, each working to maximize the light and to add texture to its directional pattern. The versatile design allows this luminary to function alongside any style décor. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Additional chain available (CHN-198).

The oversized version of our Florko Chandelier (82000), is just as out of this world as its predecessor. This multi-light design features silver-leafed iron curved discs that float effortlessly under the space-like dome. The lower level holds lights, creating a soft glow. The hand-applied silver leaf finish may vary. Additional chain available (CHN-209). Also available in a gold leaf finish 86007.

Irregular symmetry meets superlative style to create a classic chandelier in modern form. Pale brass hex pipe arms spider out to showcase 12 large, opal swirl glass globes, allowing light to be amply dispersed across a room. Each G4 LED globe is left almost completely exposed, delivering a low profile for a more streamlined look. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Additional pipe available (PIPE-412).

Classic and versatile, this timeless piece is styled to resist trend and adornment. It’s the kind of piece that fits in with almost any space, from traditional to modern, and gives off ample light even in a grand room. A total of nine lights are stacked in two tiers, each topped with an opal glass shade and fitted with a decorative finial beneath. The structure is crafted from steel with a vintage silver finish. Additional pipe available (PIPE-202). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

This grand chandelier features arms that curve upwards, reaching from a center point at two distinct heights to create a double tier effect. The entire steel structure is finished in dark vintage silver and is constructed in a highly modern design. Each arm holds a fluted frosted glass shade to slightly filter the glow of each of the 12 lights. Additional pipe is available (PIPE-204). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

The popular Waldorf's spherical form gets a boost with the large-scale Waldorf Round Chandelier. Brutalism and harsh glamour immediately come to mind with Waldorf's angular steel shards adorning its satin-nickel finished interior base. The sword-like spokes, contrasting slightly in a vintage silver finish on the exterior, yield stunning shadow play with the chandelier's lights. Shown with radio bulbs. Additional pipe available (PIPE-126). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Like an old torch chandelier, this fixture glows brilliantly in sophistication and elegance. The swirled, opal glass textured in the six torch lights lend a unique quality to their traditional shape, with exposed dark, vintage silver accents that add subtle shine and character. It's a graceful chandelier that exudes a gentle exuberance. Additional pipe available (PIPE-202). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Playfully modern and utterly unique, this quad-light chandelier is a brilliantly retro design. Alternating demi-globes of steel and opal glass are fixed onto a complementing stem, each oversized to create a hint of drama in scale and proportion. The polished vintage silver is classic finish choice. It’s a piece that not only brings light to a space, but life and energy. Additional pipe available (PIPE-126). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Synonymous with vintage elegance, the slight geometric design of this sconce conveys effortless style. The convex opal glass framed in steel delivers a retro quality that is reminiscent of 1960s design, and the vintage silver and bronze finishes recall mid-century style. Two tapered steel batons protrude from the top and bottom of the frame to add a slight dynamic—and a touch of personality—to the straightforward arrangement. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

An imbalance in scale incites intrigue and allure in this wall sconce. Two globes of chrome ombré glass reach the tips of a crescent-shaped post, each sliced open to expose unfiltered light. The globes swivel in their mounts, so you can guide the light as well. The slender steel frame is finished in dark vintage silver. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Finish may vary.

Taking a cue from modern style, this wall sconce gives a traditional design an updated look. Made entirely of brass, it is then finished in a highly polished nickel, which lends the updated twist and adds so much shine. The interior of the shade is a simple, brushed brass and conceals a small light, like a torpedo bulb. The result is an elegant sconce that elevates a space with a timeless look.

Crafted entirely of stainless steel, the mount and arm have a rich bronze finish that is slightly weathered to add to its vintage look. The shade is finished in a pale brass, while the interior is painted in white for added reflective light. It is mounted on an 180º swivel arm and the shade has slight vertical maneuverability. Photographed with a 5-inch frosted globe bulb. Also available in antique brass (49084). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Inspired by the lustrousness of our Waldorf Chandelier, we've created a smaller version fit for a wallspace. Depth and scale are just as transformative, as angular steel shards in varying sizes extend from the center. Steel rods are interspersed throughout the vibrant form finished in vintage silver, creating a stunning contrast from the metal form. Available in a heritage brass finish (49275). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

A modern sensibility defines this midcentury sconce finished in vintage silver with an inky bronze plaque mount. The shade can be angled to cast light right where you need it, and the interior is finished in white for added reflective light. This the perfect sconce for spotlighting your favorite art piece or next to a bed. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Also available in antique brass (49020) or as a floor lamp in antique brass (79006) and vintage silver/bronze (79013).

Sleek, slender, svelte; this handsome stainless steel sconce brings light and looks to a space. A curving stem has a ball accent and is crafted into a matching flush mount with a disk of black crystal, both featuring a dark, vintage silver finish. The design is fantastically modern and the mixing of crystal and stainless steel is utterly unique. Topped with a tapered, black silk shade.

The latest addition to the Parrish series is a single-light sconce. A three-pronged steel frame finished in vintage silver suspends a clear glass cylinder shade on a solitary slip hook. Shown with an Edison bulb. Also available in antique brass (49086) and antique bronze (49953), as well as an antique bronze floor lamp (79953) and chandelier (89033). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Vertically symmetrical in design, two conical lamps form the brilliance that is this sconce. Crafted entirely of stainless steel, a single post stands from a square plaque mount, with matching shades casting light both upward and downward. The effect is quite moody and dramatic. Both lamps are lined with a matching metal shade, so the sconce is touch-safe when switched on. Also available in antique brass (49169). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

This vintage-inspired sconce has endless sophistication that will never go out of style. Each piece is crafted from brass, constructed in a tall, slender form. The wall mount is made in three tiers, a plaque of brilliantly clear acrylic separating two plates of brass. All the metal is finished in a silvery vintage polish—down to the screws—and a petite linen barrel shade in white perches atop. Also available in vintage brass (44368).

So unexpected, this design is so uniquely modern it’ll be a constant marvel. A single bulb nests inside a stainless steel cube form, finished in pale brass for a very warm and organic look. The twist lies beneath: 16 hand-formed, matching diamond links hang dramatically at almost three feet in length. Also available in antique brass (49085). Metal finish may vary.

So simple and so modern, this is a sconce that fits in anywhere. Clean lines, crafted from stainless steel, frame cubes of frosted glass, so the light is filtered beautifully. The warm metal tones are thanks to a dark vintage silver finish that covers the piece. It mounts flush to the wall, so the look is clean and sleek. Fits two candelabra bulbs. Also available in brown nickel (49102) and antique brass (49104). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.
Your barware and accouterments will shine on this swanky bar cart. The x-frame features a mix of contrasting materials including polished nickel steel, natural teak and clear glass. Finish may vary.

Serve your guests without forfeiting function or style. Crafted with an iron frame in an antique brass finish, each of the three tiers of this capsule-shaped bar cart features a different element. The top tier is inset with solid white marble, the second tier is inset with clear glass and the third tier is inset with mirrored glass. The use of mixed materials delivers a luxe visual appeal. Finish may vary.

This sleek little bar cart is equal parts form and function. Beautifully crafted with a vintage brass finish, it features two tiers plated with antiqued mirror glass that has a brilliantly whimsical pattern. So handy, the bar is footed with 360º swivel casters for mobility, which are finished to blend seamlessly into the design

Serve your guests without forfeiting function or style. Crafted with an iron frame in a graphite finish, each of the three tiers of this capsule-shaped bar cart features a different element. The top tier of this cart is inset with solid white marble, the second tier is inset with clear glass and the third tier is inset with mirrored glass. The use of mixed materials creates interest and delivers a luxe visual appeal. Finish may vary.

The evolution of the Ramirez design family. An organically-shaped, opal glass shade rests atop a vintage silver-finished steel arm and matching backplate, creating a soft statement piece. Also available in antique brass (49126). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Upgrade an entertaining space to art deco grandeur with this brassy bar cart. Beautifully crafted with an antique brass finish, it features two tiers inset with plain mirror glass, each with a matching stripe pattern that adds character and charm. So handy, the bar is footed with 360º swivel casters for mobility, which are finished to blend seamlessly into the design. Metal finish may vary

The Linkka Sconce is a lesson in scaled-down, Sputnik-inspired design. The sharp angles of the vintage silver-finished steel arms and matching backplate create graphic movement that is softened by the opal glass globes. Also available in heritage brass (49163). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Whether you choose to mix and mingle in the dining room or kitchen, choose to do it with effortless style—simple and never boring. Featuring a sleek iron frame in a carbon metal finish and black glass shelves, this multi-tiered bar cart is as fashionable as it is functional. Perfect for parties, the tray top is removable so you can serve cocktails and hor d'oeuvres to guests in style. Rolling casters do lock, which allows for easy mobility and stationary stability.

A distant cousin of the Yasmin family, Juniper combines clean lines and industrial silver touches for a beautifully functional sconce. A dimmer switch is located on the backplate to allow lighting flexibility. The white linen shade with the vintage silver details oozes modern glam. Also available in antique brass (49123), as a floor lamp (78680), table lamps (49023, 49680) and pendant (49051). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.
Multi-tiered, this antique brass bar cart offers extensive opportunities for styling. Perfect for parties, the black glass tray top is removable, taking martinis on the go.

From table lamp to floor lamp, pendant to chandelier, the Sabine family continues to evolve with the Sabine Vanity Light. Three opal glass tear drops hang from a vintage silver backplate, featuring matching brass details. Also available in antique brass (49153). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

The Hampton Sconce is already a popular bath lighting choice, now the Hampton Vanity Light takes it to the next level. Delicate vintage silver rings fall playfully around its frosted glass shades, tripled and mounted on a matching vintage silver backplate. Also available in antique brass (49151). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Equal parts classic and dramatic, this versatile light fixture delivers form & function in one supple curve. The streamlined dome design features an outer matte egg shell surface while the interior features a brilliant gold metallic semi-matte finish. Though a stand-out fixture on its own, it makes an even bigger impact when grouped with the complementary shapes and tones in the Pascal, Patton and Ponce Pendant Collections. Additional pipe available (PIPE-101).

Here's a light fixture that's universally modern, timeless and beautifully functional. Each section is crafted from bent, flat strips of resilient bamboo, mounted to the rattan frame in two layers to create depth and filter the glow even further. Adding to the modern look is a white painted finish throughout that makes it stand out in a moody, dramatic setting. The light that comes through the bamboo strips casts wonderful shadows around the room. Additional pipe available (PIPE-101).

Equal parts classic and dramatic, this over-scaled light fixture delivers form & function in grand scale. The streamlined dome design features an outer matte eggshell surface while the interior of the dome features a brilliant gold metallic semi-matte finish. Though a stand-out fixture on its own, it makes an even bigger impact when grouped with the complementary shapes and tones in the Pascal, Patton and Ponce Pendant Collections. Additional pipe available (PIPE-101).

A classic cousin of the Hariette (42101), the Gillespie Pendant features a frosted glass shade that's highlighted by its etched pattern and detail. Shown with a clear bent tip candelabra bulb. Finish may vary. Additional pipe available (PIPE-149). vary. Additional pipe available (PIPE-149).

The Tilda pendant is a white washed single-light pendant with two tiers of hand carved wooden rods attached on- by-one to the circular frames. Enjoy the shadow play on the walls and floor. During installation, please ensure that the bulb is not touching any of the wooden dowels. Finish may vary. Additional chain available (CHN-127).

Equal parts classic and dramatic, this versatile light fixture delivers form & function in one supple curve. The streamlined dome design features an outer matte eggshell surface while the interior features a brilliant gold metallic semi-matte finish. Though a stand-out fixture on its own, it makes an even bigger impact when grouped with the complementary shapes and tones in the Pascal, Patton and Ponce Pendant Collections. Additional pipe available (PIPE-101).

Transitional 1-light hand carved wooden drum shade pendant in whitewash finish with tiny perforations for detail and texture. Topped with an interior mirror border allowing light to disperse downward and through the holes across the surface of the shade. Additional chain CHN-947.

Transitional hammered iron shade pendant with glossy white powder coated finish and brass plated interior provides extra illumination. Display in pairs or multiples, along a kitchen island or home office.

Simple can be so sophisticated—and this pendant is a wonderful example. A sleek stem of antique-brass finished stainless steel descends into a cylinder of polished white marble. Fitted with a bulb of your choice, the look is clean, classic and elegant. Additional pipe available (PIPE-180). Photographed with a 5-inch frosted globe bulb. Marble may vary in tone and texture. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Transitional 1-light hand carved wooden drum shade pendant in whitewash finish with tiny perforations for detail and texture. Topped with an interior mirror allowing light to disperse downward and through the holes across the surface of the shade. Additional chain CHN-947.

This one light frosted glass pendant is highlighted by its wonderful, exaggerated bubble surface. Above the cloud-like texture, the piece is topped with a brushed nickel canopy and pipe. Finish may vary. Additional pipe available (PIPE-143). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

This pendant breaks the boundaries of geometric design. A large opal glass globe seems to float effortlessly in a steel circular cage that has been embellished with champagne crystal disks. The interplay of circles in different materials and sizes yields an unexpected spatial silhouette. When in use, the manipulation and play of light on the steel and glass creates a warm and inspiring atmosphere. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Additional pipe available (PIPE-424).

The depths of spatial design are defined with the Volta Pendant. An opal glass globe is suspended by a steel pipe finished in pale brass that encompasses it in free-form fashion. The simple geometric silhouette of the circumambient façade creates a visual of a floating orb, delivering a dimensional dynamic to a space. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Additional pipe available (PIPE-176).

Gloriously modern, this sleek and slender pendant is a unique wonder. The steel frame drops dramatically with sharp angles to accommodate a conical opal glass shade. It’s finished in a dark vintage silver and is adorned with a crystal drop finial at the bottom. Due to its height, this light fixture is ideal in tall spaces, especially over a kitchen island or in a bathroom. Additional pipe (PIPE-202) available. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

A stylish and elegant pairing of geometric inspiration and transitional design come together in this pendant. Two linear squares of steel encase a demi-globe of opal glass, which casts a warm glow throughout a space . The frame has a classic vintage silver finish. Additional pipe available (PIPE-126). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Sink into the rolling landscape of the Dune Chair. A lounger designed for comfort in every way, the sleek channeled form and tapered antique brass legs are elegantly effortless. The seat is covered in muslin, allowing you to slipcover or reupholster in the fabric of your choice. Finish may vary.
The disco nap is making a comeback and this generously scaled poof is perfect for curling up or lounging with a friend. The snow basketweave linen and cognac leather buckles lend an easy versatility.

Timeless design can elicit intrigue when done right. At first, it looks like a traditional lantern-that is, until you notice the shade is made entirely of pieces of glass. This modern light fixture features 60 tubes of frosted glass , which get their opacity from an acid-etched process. They conceal four light bulbs, all in a dark, vintage silver finished steel frame. Additional pipe available (PIPE-200). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.
Made of resin with an aging marble finish, this oversized urn looks beautiful atop the Pygmalion stand, or try two of them filled with a carefully shaped boxwood on either side of a doorway.

A symbol of the sun setting over the desert horizon as it fades into the night. The Horizon Mirror features an intriguing oblong shape, antique nickel finished brass frame and antique smoke mirror. Antiquing is hand-applied and will vary. It hangs sturdy and flush to the wall using a security cleat mount.

Illuminate a photograph or line drawing with this architectural steel table easel in vintage silver. Adjustable and well proportioned on a white marble base, it’s the missing piece in any room. Marble may vary

Beautiful on a writing desk or console, the whitewashed wood layered base is inspired by a desert sand drift. The pale brass finished steel double stem and anchor detail hovering over the white linen shade make it a standout.

We bow down to this beautifully romantic pendant. Features a simple, opal glass orb wrapped with a dark bronze steel band, embellished with decorative vintage silver elements. See where the arrow of the Celeste Pendant will take you! Additional pipe available (PIPE-210).

Blending art and poetry together with useful functionality - the Aja Wall Sonce was originally designed to hold a cookbook but lends itself as the perfect perch for a poem or artwork. The steel frame is finished in vintage silver.

Free in form, modern and simplified, the Desert Sun pendant in its raw, deep umbers emulates the setting desert sun. The rose-colored, glass orb sits inside a delicate steel cage finished in rose gold to create a tone on tone masterpiece. Additional chain available (CHN-154).

Simple in form yet wildly intriguing, the Spirit Decanter is perfect for the world traveler who seeks the unexpected in all facets of life. The glass form features heather colored glass, a brushed nickel brim and chestnut leather stopper. Pair with DS2031 and DS2032 to create the ultimate trifecta.

Simple in form yet wildly intriguing, the Elixir Decanter is perfect for the world traveler who seeks the unexpected in all facets of life. The glass form features petal colored glass, a brushed nickel brim and chestnut leather stopper. Pair with DS2032 and DS2033 to create the ultimate trifecta.
The perfect chair for anywhere. Zephyr’s slender, curved rose gold steel frame and white hide-covered seat are minimal in form while offering maximum glamour. Hide will vary.

The artisan beauty of these white hide bands handwoven into a simple basket weave pattern that is stretched around a sleek and modern rose gold steel frame, makes this bench both a statement piece and a practical seating option. Influenced by equestrian culture and the juxtaposition of the materials, this bench brings texture and modern style to any room. Hide will vary.

Simple in form yet wildly intriguing, the Essence Decanter is perfect for the world traveler who seeks the unexpected in all facets of life. The glass form features dusty rose colored glass, a brushed nickel brim and chestnut leather stopper. Pair with DS2031 and DS2033 to create the ultimate trifecta.

The amorphic shape of this stylish blotter tray brings back the lost art of writing. The sumptuous dove leather and bronzed finished aluminum edging elicit delight, inspiring old traditions to take new form. form. Perfect when paired with the Sheath Letter Opener (DS2028).

Boho simplicity at its finest - this single pendant goes au natural in rattan. The steel canopy and pipe are finished in antique brass to offer a sense of balance and sophistication. Additional pipe available (PIPE-101).

Modern desires take the lead on this contemporary sconce design. Light and airy, Griffith masters simplistic sophistication. The steel backplate features an antique brass frame, paired with two-tone ivory enamel and clear crystal for subtle contrast. Also available in black and heritage brass (DP49004).

The Watercrest Sconce redefines natural sophistication. Blocks of honed snow marble framed in antique brass steel offer a raw yet refined element to the space it occupies. The unfinished quality of the façade possesses an incredible amount of texture, both visual and to the touch, that is heightened when illuminated. A luxe lighting option for small, stylish spaces. Marble may vary. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

This golden beauty is an inspired design from the popular mid-century sputnik ball chandeliers. We’ve given it a modern overhaul as a sconce, with an antique brass finished steel frame and a series of thick disks of opal swirl glass that dimple in the center. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

An imbalance in scale incites intrigue and allure in this wall sconce. Two globes of opal swirl glass reach the tips of a crescent-shaped post, each sliced open to expose unfiltered light. The globes swivel in their mounts, so you can guide the light, which casts a diffused glow from the opal swirls in the design. The slender steel metal frame is finished in antique brass. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Finish may vary.

Gorgeous, polished white onyx creates a warm filtered light and adds natural sophistication to any space. Two small bulbs beneath accentuate the stone’s organic veins and features brilliantly as it rests perfectly in the frame. The fixture mounts directly from a steel frame, finished in antique brass. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Onyx will vary naturally in tone and texture.
The perfect companion to the Mercurial Blotter (DS2029). This letter opener’s subtle details like the dove leather handle and bronzed finished aluminum look beautiful when juxtaposed with the trays.

In a slightly mid-century fashion, this curvy sconce revels in elegant simplicity. It exudes charm with a brilliant, antique brass finish and grand opal glass shade. The shade is formed into an oblong shape and is open at the top to shine exposed light upward. The steel wall mount features etched ribbing that adds a bit of an edge. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Like a modern torch light, this sconce glows brilliantly in sophistication and elegance. The swirled, opal glass textures lend a unique quality to its traditional shape, with exposed dark, vintage silver accents that add subtle shine and character. Grace several down a hallway or in a powder room for artistic flair. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Finish may vary.

A simple homage to natural and refined materials, this oversized sconce exudes elegance and sophistication. Snow marble tiles are fashioned together and framed in antique brass steel to create such a polished piece. The natural veining and textures of the marble is brilliantly put on display when lit, adding an intriguing visual appeal and an intimate illuminating glow. Marble may vary. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

This extremely practical wall sconce pivots to allow the customization of the light source: top, bottom, or side depending on what you want to highlight. Crafted with white onyx and steel finished in antique brass, this light is at its essence classically simple and completely modern. Use it in a bedroom or down a hallway for the perfect serene glow of light. Onyx may vary.

Art deco and modern styles make a wonderful duet in this sconce. Crafted in stainless steel, the base form is first created, then the accent tiles are welding on perfectly and it’s covered in an antique brass finish. A plate of white onyx slides into the metal frame, accenting the cut designs. When switched on, you can see all the organic textures in the stone, highlighted by a chandelier bulb from behind. Onyx will vary naturally in tone and texture. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Elegantly styled, this dynamic fixture has art deco leanings and upscale panache. The bi-tonal stainless steel is finished in both an inky bronze and antique brass, which holds a plate of white onyx stone. When switched on, you can see all the organic textures, highlighted by two chandelier bulbs. Onyx will vary naturally in tone and texture. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.
A striking frosted glass shade is uniquely contrasted by five fine polished nickel bands. Also available in antique brass (49047). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.
A striking frosted glass shade is uniquely contrasted by five fine antique brass bands. Also available in polished nickel (49048). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Gorgeous, polished white onyx creates a warm filtered light and adds natural elegance to any space. The three bulbs beneath accentuate the stone’s organic veins and features brilliantly. The fixture mounts directly to a ceiling or wall from a stainless steel frame, finished in antique brass. Fitted for three candelabra bulbs. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Onyx will vary naturally in tone and texture.

A design derived from our very popular Stefan floor lamp (79661), this one light wall sconce combines vintage brass with frosted glass and bronze in a sophisticated and modern way. Consider pairs on either side of a mirror in the hallway. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

A modern interpretation of the purity of form of Greek and Roman columns, this 4-light chandelier features glass cylinder rods to provide the exterior frame of this oval-shaped fixture. The vintage silver finish on the delicate steel frame and candelabra lighting lend a classical quality that's totally transitional. Additional pipe available (PIPE-126).

Derived from the popular Stefan Floor Lamp (79661), this one-light wall sconce combines vintage silver with frosted glass and bronze to create a sophisticated and modern look. Consider pairs flanking a mirror in the hallway. Damp rated and approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

The smaller kin of the Royalton Chandelier and its all-time elegance. The Royalton Small Pendant brings polished nickel plating and uneven ribbed glass rods together for a glamorous vibe. This smaller size of this pendant is perfect for a luxurious powder room or office. Additional pipe available (PIPE-100). Also available in antique brass (49918). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

The Toya Sconce brings a new twist to the traditional torch silhouette. Tapered off-white linen shades softly scatter the light, creating a warm glow that contrasts the sloped angles and the two-tone finishes of antique brass and vintage silver. A decorative ring adds a unique visual to its classic form. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Industrial rivets emerge as unexpected ornament paired with milky, opaline glass. Based on an Art Nouveau original, this antique silver flush mount fixture solves the problem of what to hang when ceilings are too low for a chandelier but befitting of beautiful decoration.

The pivots on each of the five, clear seedy globes can be adjusted to suit your needs and design aesthetic. With an undulating design and vintage silver finish, the piece itself is an arresting light sculpture - perfect for hanging horizontally, vertically or even as a ceiling mount. Shown here with clear tubular bulbs, the piece is damp rated and approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

A work of art, our Hanley Flush Mount features fluted glass that has been handcrafted into triangular rods. Each rod extends from a polished nickel dome, taking the sunburst trend up a notch. Shown with silver globe bulbs. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

This eight-light, polished nickel flush mount chandelier re-imagines the Zanadoo starburst in a manner that works perfectly in smaller rooms. The result still has a beautiful light and shadow effect on the walls and ceiling. Shown with small tubular bulbs. Damp rated: Approved for use in covered outdoor areas or bathrooms.

A straightforward examination of the basic principles of design takes place with this semi-flush pendant. A sleek steel shade in an antique brass finish frames this 3-light fixture, which features an acrylic diffuser that is suspended from within. The balance and contrast of materials delivers a fundamental visual aesthetic that transcends time and style. Also available in heritage brass (49267), bronze (49268) and polished nickel (49269) finishes. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

A modern interpretation of the purity of form of Greek and Roman columns, this 4-light chandelier features glass cylinder rods to provide the exterior frame of this oval-shaped fixture. The antique brass finish on the delicate steel frame and candelabra lighting lend a classical quality that's totally transitional. Additional pipe available (PIPE-101).

A modern interpretation of the purity of form of Greek and Roman columns, the 4-light Hera Flush Mount features glass cylinder rods to provide the exterior frame of this hex-shaped fixture. The antique brass finish on the delicate steel frame and candelabra lighting lend a classical quality that's totally transitional. Additional pipe available (PIPE-101).

The smaller space with lower ceilings finally has its focal point with the Nessa Flushmount, a petite take on the larger Nessa Chandelier (89009). The antique brass frame is adorned with clear fluted glass rods, all individually attached, adding to the design's glam quotient. Shown with small clear tubular bulbs. Also available in polished nickel (89427). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

The smaller kin of the Royalton Chandelier and its all-time elegance. The Royalton Small Pendant brings antique brass plating and uneven ribbed glass rods together for a glamorous vibe. This smaller size of this pendant is perfect for a luxurious powder room or office. Additional pipe available (PIPE-101). Also available in polished nickel (49919). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

This four-light chandelier features a stunning arrangement of gently-curved plates, embossed with a leaf motif and finished in vintage brass. This gilded piece has a traditional and feminine feel that won't overpower a streamlined space. A frosted acrylic diffuser softens the light. Additional pipe available (PIPE-159). Also available in large (42253) and two-tiered (84310).

Our popular Hanley design is now available as a Flush Mount, perfect for the powder room or hallway. Featuring the same fluted glass and antique brass dome, this beautiful light takes the sunburst trend up a notch. Shown with small clear tubular bulbs. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

So stately, this fixture is the ultimate sophisticate. A polished brass structure holds a large sleeve of clear glass, framed in real walnut wood, fitted with a glass bottom. The blend of warm brass and dark finished wood is what gives this light its signature level of elegance. Two exposed bulbs become the center of attention, perfect for Edison bulbs or other decorative bulbs. Also available as a pendant (DC42006).

The smaller space with lower ceilings finally has its focal point with the Nessa Small Chandelier, the smaller cousin of the larger Nessa Chandelier (89009). The polished nickel frame is adorned with clear fluted glass rods, all individually attached, adding to the design's glam quotient. Shown with small clear tubular bulbs. Additional pipe available (PIPE-100). Also available in antique brass (89426). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

This unique flush mount chandelier takes the Zanadoo starburst concept and makes it applicable for smaller rooms or rooms with lower ceilings. This eight-light fixture casts a beautiful light and shadow effect on the walls and ceiling. Shown with frosted globe bulbs and small clear tubular bulbs. Damp rated: Approved for use in covered outdoor areas or bathrooms.

A straightforward examination of the basic principles of design takes place with this semi-flush pendant. A sleek steel shade in a heritage brass finish frames this 3-light fixture, which features an acrylic diffuser that is suspended from within. The balance and contrast of materials delivers a fundamental visual aesthetic that transcends time and style. Also available in antique brass (49266), bronze (49268) and polished nickel (49269) finishes. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

A straightforward examination of the basic principles of design takes place with this semi-flush pendant. A sleek steel shade in a bronze finish frames this 3-light fixture, which features an acrylic diffuser that is suspended from within. The balance and contrast of materials delivers a visual aesthetic that transcends time and style. Also available in antique brass (49266), heritage brass (49267) and polished nickel (49269) finishes. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

This eight-point star pendant provides sculptural interest, as well as a unique option for those rooms with low ceilings. Formed of solid brass with a warm antique finish, its four lights reflect off the round canopy for a luminous glow. Additional pipe available PIPE-114.

A sleek and simple light solution for smaller spaces with lower ceilings has arrived with the Voss Flushmount. Antique brass iron tops textured clear glass, which helps to softly scatter light across a room. The straightforward design allows this piece to blend seamlessly with any style décor.
Venus Tall Vase
This beautifully cut crystal vase is veiled in a champagne hue. Up the cool factor and fill with oversized matches or chic drink stirrers.
Gilda Vase

This exotic art piece showcases an abstracted dragon, etched on the reverse of an elongated antiqued mirror mirror. Dramatically held in place by the five antique brass talons of same mythical creature. Game of Thrones for the home? A timeless focal point to any room. Features a security cleat attachment. Can be hung vertically or horizontally. Also available in plain mirror with antiqued border (DD2085). Finish may vary.

A lesson in complementing contrast, the Gerti Square Container marries gold plated porcelain and a gunmetal lacquer to create a striking and functional piece of mixed materials. Also available as a round container (7142) with inverted finishes. Finish may vary.

A nod to the decades of Art Deco the Vogel Mirror features a large, circular smoke mirror embedded with a separate triangular mirror noted with brass knobs to create a visual study in symmetry. The antique brass frame lends a sophisticated touch to this already exceptional piece, while the beveled edges accentuates the overall geometry. Features two security cleat attachments, so you can hang with the triangle pointing upwards or downwards.

Round cocktail tables are the perfect choice if you have children or a tendency to run into corners. This natural iron cocktail table features round edges and an acid-etched top that resembles the cross cut of a tree trunk.

Create curiosity with this sizable round mirror. Heavily antiqued glass is framed in thin brass with a gold leaf finish that delivers a sophisticated element to this statement piece. The unique antiquing process has created an almost swirl-like pattern that sweeps across the glass, and you're bound to notice a new whorl every time you look its way. Features a security cleat for hanging. Finish may vary.

As a nod to the urban spirit of Chicago, Frank designed a tattoo-inspired emblem that was hand-etched on this alluring mirror. The perfect balance of graphic refinement, featuring a black-washed wood frame contrasted with the antiqued mirror. Each piece will be hand-done, lending a one-of-a-kind quality to the design.

Simple and modern, this cone-shaped floor lamp is finished in ivory and heritage brass. Topped with a unique spider-like frame that supports the white linen shade. No harp is needed for this lamp. Features a full-range dimmer switch on a black cotton cord.

Enamored with the bold and burnished appeal of our Kilpatrick Collection, we designed a mirror in the same fashion. A heritage piece with contemporary flair, the striking contrast between the rich ebony stained oak finish and earthy burnished gold leaf lends dimension to the traditional silhouette that frames beveled glass. Multiple security cleat attachments allow this mirror to be hung vertically or horizontally.

Simple form and mixed materials work together to create a lighting option that portrays sleek style and timeless design. A horseshoe-shaped pale brass stem extends downward into a white marble base, which adds a luxe touch to its utilitarian frame. The sophisticated and straightforward nature of the lamp gets a vibrant update each time its in use. Topped with an oval ash microfiber shade with white cotton lining and a matching metal finial. Finish may vary.

Form meets function with this oblong-octagon style mirror. A handcrafted, lacquered Chatéau Gray frame accentuates the angular facets of the elongated beveled glass for a classic yet contemporary feel. Large in size, the Wentworth Mirror makes a stylish statement in any setting. Security cleat hanging hardware allows for vertical and horizontal display.
Tall clear glass cylindrical base with slightly flared white linen shade and white cotton lining. Foot dimmer switch.
Slender wrought iron floor lamp in a white gesso finish features a subtle ring detail and a curved tripod stand. Topped with a tall ivory microfiber drum shade. 3-way switch.

The large scale tapered hourglass shape is cast in aluminum then antiqued to emphasize the pitted natural surface. It is topped with a tapered natural linen shade, lined in a light gray cotton. Finish may vary.

Sculptural in form, the floor lamp version of it's tabletop predecessor blends the beauty of wood, brass and marble to create stylish elegance. The tapered wood base is finished in walnut and is fitted with a brilliantly gilt eyelet design, almost flowing through the shade to the matching finial. Mounted to a square plaque of natural white marble. Topped with a white linen drum shade with white cotton lining and a matching metal finial. Marble tones and grain may vary.
