Organic, rattan wicker is just as Caribbean in its style as it is sophisticated. The shade is made of natural, handwoven rattan, featuring double pull chains. The base and accents are crafted from stainless steel, finished in a warm antique brass that contrasts the whimsical silhouette.

A wonder in structural brilliance, this towering floor lamp brings architectural ingenuity to interior lighting. The industrial inspired, fixed-angle natural teak arm is mounted into a cream concrete base. Running along its length is a gray cloth cord that suspends the lamp at different heights—the extra length can be wrapped around the mounted anchor on the side. The lamp is fitted with an ivory linen drum shade with ivory cotton lining and a dimmer switch.

All the handcrafted textures in this exotic accent table make it shine in the spotlight. From meticulously hammered surfaces to etched carvings, the entire piece has been formed and detailed by hand. It’s completely smithed from brass and has a brilliant polished nickel finish. Sized perfectly to hold an afternoon cocktail...or two. Also comes in vintage brass (6918).

Sleek and simple, this ultra-minimalist floor lamp has wonderful details that make it quite unique. The steel frame is given warmth with a heritage brass finish, with a matching finial so the shade seems suspended within the design. The disk base leaves a small footprint and is fitted with a clear plate of glass. Topped with a tapered wren microfiber shade with off-white cotton lining and a matching heritage brass finial.

Classic white marble and sleek polished stainless steel make for a sophisticated pairing in this modern side table. The slab of natural marble rests effortlessly within the frame and is supported underneath by a full perimeter of steel. Also comes in dark natural iron with white marble (6392) and vintage brass with black marble (6683). Marble tones may vary.
Natural driftwood base side table with clear round glass top.
This solid wood carved stool with limed wash finish also makes a great drink table. Try three in front of a chaise. Expect to see cracks...that is all part of the natural beauty.

Tricky, like trompe l’oeil, this stunning table has a secret—though it looks to be made completely of stone, lift it and you’ll discover it’s actually much lighter in weight. Made from lightweight concrete, its marble-like façade is made in a process called hydrographics. Since the process is done individually, each piece will have a look that varies slightly in veining and color scale. It is also available in a darker palette and smaller scale (5549).

Tricky, like trompe l’oeil, this stunning table has a secret—though it looks to be made completely of stone, lift it and you’ll discover it’s actually much lighter in weight. Made from lightweight concrete, its marble-like façade is made in a process called hydrographics. Since the process is done individually, each piece will have a look that varies slightly in veining and color scale. It is also available in a lighter palette and larger scale (5550).

Sleek. Simple. Sophisticated. This table is modern elegance realized. Seamlessly crafted in stainless steel, it is finished in a polished nickel finish, yet with slightly natural touches that recall a sort of Japanese Wabi-Sabi balance. Two tiers of shelving are plated in beveled mirror glass to not only elevate the look even further, but to add light and shine. Pairs with the Marcus Cocktail Table (6912) and Marcus Console (6909).

Who knew that leather and metal could make such a sophisticated pairing? Brushed brass forms the structure, cognac leather wraps it, stitched together with an exposed hem to add a handsome finishing touch. Topped with a tapered, white linen barrel shade with a cotton lining and matching brass ball finial. Also comes in indigo leather (DC72015), as well as a table lamp version in cognac leather (DC12012) and indigo leather (DC12012). Leather finish may vary.

The raw look of jute rope fully wraps the stem of this slender floor lamp. Natural fibers give the design an organic edge and an incredible amount of texture you can see and feel. It’s mounted in a plate of walnut finished wood, which helps conceal the clear cord for a streamlined look. Topped with a drum shade in ivory linen with ivory cotton lining and a matching jute finial.

All the handcrafted textures in this exotic accent table make it shine in the spotlight. From meticulously hammered surfaces to etched carvings, the entire piece has been formed and detailed by hand. It’s completely smithed from brass and has a worldly vintage finish. Sized perfectly to hold an afternoon cocktail...or two. Also comes in polished nickel (6917).
A sculptural accent table with teardrop base design and round top in a dark walnut finish.

Though side tables were originally made strictly for function, this modern maven delivers looks along with utility. Crafted entirely from solid oak, its seamless design is due to an ebony black veneer that's unique and rich with natural textures. Its function comes through in thoughtful details, like a wide tabletop, roomy nook and bottom drawer that opens and closes smoothly on soft-close slides. Features a signature aged brass pull.
This striking wooden tripod floor lamp is topped with an off-white linen shade with white cotton lining. 3-way switch.

This table not only elevates the room it occupies, but also showcases a level of class on its own. Constructed of hand-forged iron, the frame is delicately tapered with a distressed, antique pewter finish that lends a slightly industrial edge. The tiers are both rich with organic texture in a tiled blueschist veneer that holds bold, scattered veining. Its demure size means this table is an ideal occasional or drink table and a perfect companion to a cozy armchair. Finish may vary.

Inspired by the rounded, gourd-shaped tribal drums found throughout Africa, this side table has a silhouette that is voluptuous and curvy. It’s crafted from blackened wood, which is first sandblasted to give it an intense, charred wood finish that you can really see and feel. The top has an added brushed texture that is so unique, and the overall slightly glossy look comes from the final wax coat that’s added to give it modern polish.

Who knew that leather and metal could make such a sophisticated pairing? Brushed brass forms the structure, indigo leather wraps it, stitched together with an exposed hem to add a handsome finishing touch. Topped with a tapered, white linen barrel shade with a cotton lining and matching brass ball finial. Also comes in cognac leather (DC72014), as well as a table lamp version in cognac leather (DC12012) and indigo leather (DC12012). Leather finish may vary.

Made with a faux bois inspiration in mind, this side table is ideal for a space that needs a little natural beauty. Though it’s cast from aluminum, it’s molded into an exaggerated woodgrain design to give it an organic sophistication. The shape is what gives it a modern update, tapered at the base and in the top with a narrowed collar that joins them together. The form alone recalls Brancusi style. The entire piece has a graphite finish, giving it that bit of mood we love.

Diminutive in scale, this aluminum accent table is cast in a deep bronze finish. A dueling antiqued aluminum finish was applied to the inner curves for slight contrast. Layer with a larger end table for a nesting effect. Finish may vary.

We love the yin and yang on this transitional side table. Hand-forged black iron legs are delicately tapered creating the perfect base for the chunky white marble top. Also available as an accent table (4391) and a cocktail table (4392). Marble color may vary.

We love the yin and yang on this transitional side table. Hand-forged black iron legs are delicately tapered creating the perfect base for the chunky white marble top. Also available as a cocktail table (4392). Marble may vary.

Industrial materials and hand-applied techniques update the classic shape of this enviable end table. The chiseled white marble top sits atop a pedestal base with fanned black iron rods. Marble may vary.

This seemingly simple table has details that make it quite extraordinary. It is crafted entirely from cast aluminum, finished in a graphite tone that gives it a slightly Brutalist and tribal look, though updated in a polished, modern silhouette. The legs are thinly tapered to accentuate the aesthetic, with an outer arch—a detail common in Art Nouveau tables. It’s scaled to fit in a variety of spaces in a variety of different ways.

A modern design infused with Moroccan flair, the Konrad End Table blurs the lines between new and old world. While the frame features a decorative motif, the use of natural iron and sable-finished oak are contemporary references that appeal to all audiences.

Cylindrical with a twist, the Herschel Side Table is an iron, bronze-finished beauty that instantly adds weight and artisanal detail to any space. The hammered finish brings unexpectedness to the table's modified hourglass form. Matching cocktail table (2824) and lamp (42069-622) also available.

A smaller version of our Hattie End Table (4257), this “C” shaped side table features an antiqued mirror top combined with blackened iron legs. A striking shape, this piece fits perfectly next to a chair or can become a unique nightstand. Mirror finish may vary.
Round side table supported by an iron base made from an interlocking scallop pattern and topped with rough hewn black marble accented with a ribbon of gold leaf banding.

Beauty unfolds at every curve on this traditional oak side table. Smooth cut-outs reveal a cinched silhouette that is as alluring as the deep ebony stain. Prop a decorative box or sculpture on the middle shelf to create another styling moment. Nylon nail-in glides will protect exposed floors.
Drum shaped side table with bronze aluminum base features asymmetrical honeycomb design cut-out design and clear glass top.

We love the juxtaposition of the industrial iron base, with the elegant and decorative top made of solid wood that has been scored and then clad in antique brass sheet. The brass surface will patina over time. Clad may vary. Also available as a console (2752) and coffee table (6175).

This round side table has a thoroughly modern base made from thin iron rods in a blackened finish. The irregularities on the iron surface are part of the finish and add to the sense of artisan craftsmanship.

Polished brass on the base and lip contrast beautifully with the vintage brass pedestal and black mirror top. Group with the rectangle (4386) and square (4387) counterparts to create the ultimate trifecta.

This solid wood tabletop is diamond-scored and then clad in antiqued brass sheet. The looped pedestal base is fashioned from hand-forged black iron and cinched with a gold-finish iron belt. Scaled to hold its own next to a large sofa or chair. Part of the Draco collection. Finish may vary.

This exquisite end table is like bringing the brilliance of the sun into a space. Honed hexagonal white marble is inlaid with 30 slices of polished brass, forming a shining sunburst design that is elegant and oh-so-sophisticated. It’s truly a feat of daring craftsmanship. The six-leg base is smithed from iron and finished in an antique brass finish, with a silhouette that has a slightly Moroccan feel. Also available as a cocktail table (6881). Marble tones may vary.

Polished brass on the base and lip contrast beautifully with the vintage brass pedestal and black mirror top. Group with the round (4385) and rectangle (4386) counterparts to create the ultimate trifecta.
Minimalist hammered iron accent table with black wax finish.

This iron drum shape has been finished in antique brass with a bronze plinth to give it an artisanal effect that will only get better with time. Finish may vary. Also available as a cocktail table (2864).

Artisan technique takes hold in this compelling design. The slim tapered aluminum base is finished in antique bronze. The wood top has been carved with a rhythmic ring design then clad in antique brass sheet. Clad finish may vary.

Polished brass on the base and lip contrast beautifully with the vintage brass pedestal and black mirror top. Group with the round (4385) and square (4387) counterparts to create the ultimate trifecta.
Fitz offers a modern take on the traditional drinks table. Slight curves, antique brass and the chunky blackened iron base bring new life to the midcentury design fixture.
Spark conversation with this whimsical accent table touting antique brass bird legs. Perfect for the avid collector of the unusual. The top features a bronze glass mirror.

Round 3-tier iron accent table with an antique brass finished frame and antiqued mirror shelves. This is the perfect table to situate next to a chair and can hold everything you may need: a lamp, magazines, notebooks, remote controls or a sculpture.

The iron Haven Accent Table features a gently rounded hand formed base that culminates in a flat top resting on the tapered neck. This burnt brass finish warms up the silhouette, making it a perfect companion to any chair.
We love the irregular shape of this antique brass low side table. Try it next to a chaise or armless chair, or use two in front of a sofa or sectional. Can also be turned upside down as a planter.

This accent table livens up a space with its charming and unique design like a bubbly party guest. It stands on a four-footed, antique brass base featuring clean lines and angles. But it’s the tabletop that is the most intriguing— ebony-finished, solid oak inlayed with an irregular brass pattern. The underside of the table has an inward bevel to mimic the angles in the footed base. It’s the perfect size to nest in a set or cluster for a custom look.
This iron drum shaped side table features an antique bronze finish and repousse ringed detail on the top surface. Coordinates with Clint coffee table #4007.
Round 3-tiered iron side table in an antique brass finish with inlaid antique mirrored top and shelves.
Starts with a distressed vintage brass finish on the square tubing and ends with a slab of matte black marble resting on the frame. The narrow silhouette works well when space is tight.

A new version of a very popular design, this Celeste Accent Table is a mix of white marble and antique brass. Like the original, the height adjusts while still having a small footprint. One of the best-selling designs we have. The adjustable height (19" or 21") makes it possible to nest two of them together.

The beauty of mixed materials is recognized in our Wharton Side Table. Oak veneer in a smoke finish comprises the pedestal-style frame of this subtly stunning piece. A simple antique brass inlay graces the table's top, delivering a refined element to the rustic façade. This side table is a sophisticated way to showcase objets d'art or other prized possessions, but looks equally stunning on its own.

The dichotomy of the heavily textured, cast aluminum base and elegant antique brass top adds to the visual interest of this unique design. Place it between two chairs so you can show off the oval shape and striking dark bronze finish of the base.
Round iron side table of darkened silver with brass accents finish.

Though side tables were originally made strictly for function, this modern maven brings looks and utility. Crafted entirely from solid oak, its seamless design is thanks to a smoky gray veneer that’s unique and rich with natural textures. Its function comes through in thoughtful details, like a wide tabletop, roomy nook and bottom drawer that opens and closes smoothly on soft-close slides. Signature aged finish brass drawer pull. Nylon nail-in glides will protect exposed floors.

This decorative drum table captures the collected aesthetic without the jet lag. The hand-carved natural bone inlay is set in a whimsical botanical pattern. The iron base in antique zinc complements the phantom gray finish surrounding the bone. Place two under a translucent coffee table and pull out for extra seating. Bone may vary.

Industrial elements like smoke gray stain and natural iron accents add a distressed feel to this solid oak side table. A ring under the table top matches the iron base, creating cohesiveness throughout.

We love the round shape of this slate veneer side table. We also love how the gray slate pairs with the stainless steel accent at the bottom. The thick stainless steel ring handles are the perfect decorative touch.
This iron drum shaped side table features vintage nickel finish and repouss ringed detail on the top surface. Also available in small (4414), large (4413), and bronze (2034). Finish may vary.
Round end table of gray limed oak veneer with polished nickel sleeves at feet. Perfect size for use as a side table or as a nightstand to display books and treasures.

Tables similar to this one were quite popular in parlors and salons in the early 20th century. The Percy Side Table has the same elevated feel, but with a modern edge. Three round tiers are seamlessly welded together from polished stainless steel. Each layer is set with a plate of plain-mirrored glass for added shine and elegance. Also comes in antique brass finish with antiqued mirror (6553) and zinc finish with antiqued mirror (6682).
Organic style with an eclectic edge; this iron table supported by cast tree branches is finished in a distressed silver.
Side table with simple dark natural iron frame that supports a slab of white marble.

Split between two tones, this side table is a modern wonder. The lighter top is an antique gold, where the bottom section is done in a burnished gold, adding the immense level of sophistication and craftsmanship. The table top is crafted with a sandblasted texture and the top of the base is molded to a heavy woodgrain pattern, so texture and intrigue are immense throughout the piece.
Round 3-tier iron accent table with zinc finish frame and antiqued mirror surfaces.

Round 3-tier iron accent table with zinc finished frame and antiqued mirror shelves. This is the perfect table to situate next to a chair and can hold everything you may need: a lamp, magazines, notebooks, remote controls or a beautiful sculpture.

Over 50 iron rods are welded by hand to create each of these end tables. Expert craftsmen mold each piece and weld them to the structure, creating a seamless look from top to bottom. It’s then finished in an antique brass metallic and a disk of antiqued mirror glass is inset, all giving it ultimate shine. Pair it with the matching side table (6920) and pendant lamp (84013). Also comes in brushed nickel (6925).
Convex straps of natural iron form an open "X" design in this drum shaped iron side table or stool. The hammered antique brass finish is detailed with matching brass studs.

The simple form of this large-scale floor lamp is shaped by a classic silhouette framed in solid wood that offers a timeless look to a space. The crinkle shade and umber finish work in unison to accent the textures of the natural wood grain. The neutral hue and natural material make it a versatile piece that functions alongside a variety of décor styles. Topped with an off-white linen drum shade with off-white cotton lining. Finish may vary.

A new version of a very popular design, this Celeste Accent Table is a mix of black marble and vintage silver. Like the original, the height adjusts while still having a small footprint. One of the best-selling designs we have. The adjustable height (19" or 21") makes it possible to nest two of them together.

We intentionally left this cast aluminum side table unpolished to reinforce the industrial “re-claimed” feel. The pitted and distressed surfaces on the top and base are characteristic to the casting process and add interest to the sleek design. Perfect between two chairs.

Over 50 iron rods are welded by hand to create each of these side tables. Expert craftsmen mold each piece and weld them to the structure, creating a seamless look from top to bottom. It’s then finished in an antique brass metallic and a disk of antiqued mirror glass is inset, all giving it ultimate shine. Pair it with the matching end table (6924) and pendant lamp (84013). Also comes in brushed nickel (6921).

Made entirely from sheets of raw iron, this contemporary table is a stunner. An oblong top perches atop an angled pillar, connected and mounted internally to give it a sleek and seamless look. A warm antique brass finish give the table shine and natural texture that makes each piece unique. The base is also made of iron, but is blackened to give it extra durability and add contrast to the design.

The Watson Floor Lamp embraces two bold trends: mixed materials and exposed cords. A black marble base supports a bronze adjustable shade attached to a vintage silver rod. The exposed taupe cloth cord can be artfully wrapped around the rod or left to simply hang straight. Marble may vary.

Clean angles, interplayed materials and a dark, lustrous black-nickel finish give this floor lamp alluring appeal and understated elegance. A crisp white linen shade with ivory cotton lining rests effortlessly inside the geometric styled steel frame, standing tall on three round posts. Transitional in sensibilities, this design will feel right at home in virtually any room. The solid white marble base has natural variations in color and veining. Fitted with a full dimmer switch on a clear cord.

So contemporary, so modern—so stunning. This floor lamp has looks for days, crafted from blackened iron, which gives it a unique matte black finish, and is contrasted throughout the stem with polished brass orb accents. The cone shade features meticulous perforations that cast a subtle glow outwards. Also available as a sconce (DC42002).

Industrial meets mid-century modern on the Leeland Floor Lamp. The thick white marble base and dark bronze body are the perfect design counterparts to the opal glass globe shades with antique brass accents. Features a taupe cloth cord and three sockets. Marble may vary.

Bold. Exotic. Modern. These are just a few words to describe this stunning floor lamp. It’s crafted entirely from blackened iron, so it has a soft matte finish that is a wonderful contrast to the gilt welds. Topped with a linen and raw hemp shade with cotton lining and matching iron finial.

This sophisticated double socket iron floor lamp features a slender black column supported by a round foot in a vintage brass finish. Matte black steel shade is accented with a matching brass finial and pull chain.

Modern floor lamp with a black iron tapered slender vertical rod and a blade shaped vintage brass finish finial. A white linen cylindrical double shade with off-white cotton lining allows for directing task lighting. Full range dimmer.

Contemporary iron floor lamp with three black rods which form a tripod from the open circle brass base and connect at the top to an antique brass finish ball accent. Topped with a black shade with mustard gold lining and a matching brass ball finial. 3-way switch.

Contemporary iron floor lamp with three black rods which form a tripod from the open circle brass base and connect at the top to an antique brass finish ball accent. Topped with an ivory microfiber shade with matching lining and a matching brass ball finial.

Material mastery at its finest, Frank Ponterio has blended dueling design elements to create a classic yet intriguing floor lamp design. An exposed black cloth cord is guided down the hammered brass form, cascading with ease. Perfect for adding architectural sophistication to any space. Topped with an off-white linen drum shade.
Three light floor torchiere on a triangular marble base with staggered cylindrical frosted shades is mounted on black iron rods and accented with antique brass.

The sculptural formation of this floor lamp takes lighting design to the next level. Antique brass aluminum has been sculpted into a work of art and then sand-cast by hand, adding a textural element to the sleek yet dramatic angles that define it. This lamp is as much as a showpiece as it is a functioning luminescent, showcasing beautifully in ultra-modern spaces. Topped with a rectangle off-white linen shade with white cotton lining and a matching metal finial. Finish may vary.

Contemporary lighting is defined by our Tierney Floor Lamp. Three antique brass stems slightly intertwine with one another to create its super sleek form, each carefully fitted with an opal glass shade. The fixed-position luminary is delicately displayed on a bronze and white marble base. Its slender profile works well in small spaces and the neutral tones make it versatile. Not adjustable. Finish may vary.

Our Valdez Floor Lamp is highlighted by its subtle shape and blend of materials. The antique brass form has a bamboo-like column that delivers an organic touch to the sleek white marble base. A brilliant luminescent addition to traditional and contemporary spaces. Topped with an off-white linen drum shade with off-white cotton lining and a matching metal finial. Finish may vary.

The minimalistic artistry of this floor lamp is defined by a iron plated in antique brass stem accented with antique brass organ-like piping that staircases the frame—an eye-catching detail. A square white marble base secures and showcases this noteworthy piece. Great for formal and casual settings. Topped with a rectangle mellow buff linen shade with white cotton lining and a matching metal finial. Finish may vary.

Sleek and simple in form and aesthetic, this floor lamp exemplifies ultra-modern style. It’s built of steel to give it clean lines, perfectly angular joints and a shiny polish; the completely linear frame allows it to tuck neatly into a reading chair or sofa to reduce its footprint in the room. An LED strip is nicely concealed into the frame. To give the modern look a bit of a twist, it is entirely finished in vintage brass. Fitted with a full range dimmer on a black cord.

Tapering disks that form this lamp's base, which are elegant in form—look closer and notice even more detail. Full of organic shape and texture, the disks are inspired by the natural look of fungi, with nearly twenty in total, each molded and gold -leafed to create the stunningly vibrant overall look. The frame stands tall on a white marble base to up the elegance and add to the organic nature of the piece. It is topped with an ivory linen drum shade with white cotton lining. Marble may vary.

This unique spin on the popular tripod design is updated and modern, with the extra level of sophistication prevalent in the Arteriors look. It is crafted entirely from sturdy steel, which lends it a sleek finish and endless durability, with a antique brass tone that gives it a timeless sensibility. At the joint of the tapered form is a small accent of steel with a dark vintage silver finish. It is topped with an ivory cotton drum shade with navy detailing and white cotton lining.

Sleek and simple, this ultra-minimalist floor lamp has wonderful details that make it quite unique. The stainless steel frame is given warmth with an antique brass finish, with a matching finial so the shade seems suspended within the design. The disk base leaves a small footprint and is fitted with a clear plate of glass. Topped with a tapered, ivory linen shade and matching antique brass finial.

Poised in precision, the Lela Floor Lamp is the epitome of understated elegance. An ornate white marble base and rings on the antique brass body are unexpected. Topped with an off-white linen drum shade and matching antique brass finial. Marble may vary.

The Watson Floor Lamp embraces two bold trends: mixed materials and exposed cords. A white marble base supports a vintage brass adjustable shade attached to a bronzed steel rod. The exposed black cloth cord can be artfully wrapped around the rod or left to simply hang straight. Marble may vary.

Super slim proportions and flexibility distinguish our easel floor lamp. Steel finished in antique brass, it features a petite articulating spot light that can slide up or down. The adjustable clamps will hold your art firmly in place.

Clean angles, a thoughtful interplay of materials and a warm, hand applied gold finish give this floor lamp an understated elegance. The solid white marble base has natural variations in color and veining. A crisp white microfiber shade and hand-rolled edges rests effortlessly on four slender arms. Transitional in sensibilities, this design will feel right at home in any sitting room. Marble may vary.

A trio of clear seeded glass orbs sit on top of the staggered polished brass columns anchored to a round black marble base. Perfect indirect light source for those dark corners or hallways. Shown with radio bulbs.

Transitional floor lamp features a columnar glass tube that surrounds a steel metal neck finished in vintage brass and supported by vintage brass square foot. Topped with a white parchment drum shade. 3-way switch.

This vintage brass and white marble angled floor lamp is the perfect complement to any sectional. Featuring an on/off foot switch and up-and-down adjustment on the shade makes for easy, functional lighting control. The off-white linen shade houses two light bulbs. Marble may vary.

Sculptural form and luxe materials combine in this sinuous floor lamp. A single, solid twist of antique brass finished steel sits on a clear crystal square base. The lined drum shade is made of ivory microfiber and trimmed with a 1”-inch flat band at the bottom. Think of it as a floor sculpture that happens to also be a lamp.

Transparency continues to trend on the Jodi Floor Lamp. The polished nickel body is enclosed within a clear shell of ribbed glass. Topped with a box-pleated softback shade with a black satin exterior and white cotton interior.

Slender and sleek, brighten up with this modern steel floor lamp, which features a white marble base and a vintage silver-finished post that just every-so-slightly tapers at the top and bottom. The post is crowned with blade shaped finial to offset its soft lines. It’s topped with a tapered white linen shade with off-white cotton lining. Full range dimmer on a clear cord. Also available in black iron finish (79680).

Discover towering beauty in contemporary design with this steel floor lamp. Constructed with three pale brass rods which stand as a tripod, the form is contrasted with the open circle base and connecting ball accent that are finished in a handsome vintage silver. Topped with an ivory microfiber drum shade with matching lining and a matching ball finial. Also available with a black shade (79161-697).

Discover towering beauty in contemporary design with this steel floor lamp. Constructed with three pale brass rods which stand as a tripod, the form is contrasted with the open circle base and connecting ball accent that are finished in a handsome vintage silver. Topped with a black microfiber drum shade with metallic silver lining and a matching ball finial. Also available with an ivory shade (79161-396).

Sculptural form and luxe materials combine in this sinuous floor lamp. A single, solid twist of dark, vintage silver finished steel sits on a clear crystal square base. The lined drum shade is made of ivory linen, trimmed with a 1”-inch flat band, and matching ball finial. Think of it as a floor sculpture that happens to also be a lamp. Pair it with the matching table lamp (49917-824). Also comes in antique brass floor lamp (79986-386) and table lamp (49946-269).

Elements of old world charm lend an heirloom quality to this unique floor lamp. The driftwood-like form is accented with natural iron detailing for ultimate contrast. The exposed cord is wrapped in natural rope, adding rustic flair in tasteful fashion. Topped with a light beige linen drum shade.

Creativity and craftsmanship unite to make quite a statement under the guise of modesty. Made completely of arorog, a slender stem flows into a large, flared woven base that has a slight parasol shape. The fine execution of the handwoven details and the hand-applied rattan hackle-bindings on the joints are put on display when in use. Finished in a natural light brown stain to accentuate its natural textures. Topped with an off-white linen drum shade with white cotton lining. Finish may vary.

This floor lamp features an old-world style that’s captivating. The unique silhouette is created from a turned wood base, which has a dark gray, antiqued finish that gives it added character and warmth. Topped with a drum shade in natural linen with a one-inch bottom trim and cotton lining; matching wood finial. Also available as a table lamp (14221-497).

Mother Nature took the reigns to create this naturally forming floor lamp. Teak trunks are found and collected to create these unique pieces, so each is one-of-a-kind. Once collected, the wood is hand-sanded to deliver a polished quality to the heavily textured form and mounted on a natural iron base, but is otherwise left in its natural shape. Features a taupe cloth cord. Topped with an off-white linen drum shade with off-white cotton lining and a brass sphere finial. Finish may vary.

Exotic, sultry and inspired by Middle Eastern lanterns, this floor lamp delivers international flair. The voluptuous silhouette is made using metal rods that are powder-coated for durability. The highest quality rattan is hand-woven around the entire piece, and then stained, sanded and coated for even more resilience. A utility notch is carved out to replace the bulb, but it is finished and could also be showcased as a visual detail. The tulip base is fitted with a black chord.

The ultra-sleek profile of the Tremont Floor Lamp is defined by mixed materials and simple geometric details. The smoke crystal stem features an exaggerated fluted column accented pale brass spacers that interrupt its smooth form and deliver an unexpected stylish element. The pale brass circular base delivers a brilliant shine to the moody hue. Topped with a taupe sheer microfiber drum shade with dark silver microfiber lining and a matching metal finial.

Flecks of gray, charcoal and amber interact elegantly on this authentic floor lamp crafted from natural horn. The light-beige linen drum shade highlights the tan coloration in the horn. Also available as a table lamp (46755-923). Horn may vary.

This floor lamp reimagines tropical ratan as a modern form and gray parsons finish. The tone is deep and modern, which makes this piece flexible in coastal to modern environments. Artisans conceal metal tubing with three poles of rattan and a bent, circular base, which are all wrapped in several places with another rattan material, tapnigi. The entire piece is then layered with a protectant for extra durability. It is topped with a natural linen drum shade with offf-white cotton lining.
Wrought iron floor lamp in a black gesso finish features a thin spindle design with raised rings on the stem and a flat tripod stand. Topped with a white parchment drum shade. 3-way switch.
One arm floor lamp with a single square upright pole and an open 2-prong squared base of iron. Antique bronze finish with a clear glass drum shade.
Simple polished nickel floor lamp topped with an off-white crinkled linen shade. Full range dimmer.

This vintage silver floor lamp can be adjusted with a push of a button, and a light tug on the black cloth cord changes the position of the metal shade. The heavy black marble base anchors it. Marble coloration may vary.

Simple cone floor lamp fiinished in dove grey lacquer and mounted on a polished nickel base. Topped with a unique spider-like frame that supports the white tapered shade. No harp needed for this lamp. Dimmer switch.
Tall cylinder shaped iron floor lamp with interlocking open rectangles create a geometric cage-like pillar. Topped with an ivory drum shade with ivory cotton lining. 3-way switch.

This vintage silver, angled floor lamp is the perfect complement to any sectional – featuring a foot switch on the cord and up-and-down adjustment on the shade for easy, functional lighting control. Housing two bulbs, the off-white linen shade and the black marble base provide the perfect contrast to the lamp’s brass finish. Marble coloration may vary

Transitional floor lamp features a columnar glass tube that surrounds a steel metal neck. Finished in polished nickel and supported by a polished nickel square foot. Topped with a white parchment drum shade. 3-way switch.

Filled with visual and tactile textures, the Paxton Mirror is a beautiful work of craftsmanship. Every single knob is hand carved from solid wood, then affixed to the frame to be finished in a rich, black stain. The look is African-inspired, but with a modern leaning. Beveled mirror. Also available in a small version (4616).

Equal parts classic and masculine, this mirror is a simple design with a twist—literally! Bands of tobacco-hued leather surround the plain glass mirror and is topped with a brass- plated knob and matching leather loop, so it has an almost equestrian feel. The knob is purely decorative, though, because the base is mounted with a security cleat. It is also available in a smaller version (4712).

This artistically crafted mirror is a modern take on the centuries-old French sunburst design. Using hundreds of small metal spokes, the frame is handmade by welding each one to the base, then firing the natural iron to get an almost iridescent finish. In contrast to the spokes, the plain glass mirror is surrounded by brass welding for a fully finished and elegant look. Because of its completely handmade nature, slight variances will occur with each.

The Kensey Discs Mirror takes over 20 large discs of iron to make each mirror and each disc must undergo an intensive process in order to get their interesting oxidized look. Discs are hand-cut, forming the raw edges, then given an oxidized finish wi th a chemical-and-fire technique. This free-hand artistry comes together to frame an industrial, rich mirror. Available in a similar style with smaller discs (3132), as well as a series of wall plaques in small (3146), medium (3147) and large (3148).

A unique design that fools the eye, this piece is inspired by our popular, more rectangular Autero Mirror (DD2004). The spike holding the mirror appears to have been hammered into the wall, when in fact, the piece is actually suspended from a cleat on the mirror’s back, so it is purely decorative. The iron frame has intensely etched texturing and is finished in burnt wax, surrounding a flat mirror. Also available in a larger version (DD2614).

Equal parts classic and masculine, this mirror is a simple design with a twist—literally! Bands of tobacco-hued leather surround the plain glass mirror and is topped with a brass- plated knob and matching leather loop, so it has an almost equestrian feel. The knob is purely decorative, though, because the base is mounted with a security cleat. It is also available in a larger version (4711).

Featuring a natural iron frame, polished brass accents and a plain mirror, the Janey Mirror is a contemporary lesson in mixed materials. The open frame design gives this mirror dimension and depth, while the dual finishes make its simple form outstanding. Makes a grand statement as a pair or trio. Also available in round (4183) and square (4141).

Filled with visual and tactile textures, the Paxton Mirror is a beautiful work of craftsmanship. Every single knob is hand carved from solid wood, then affixed to the frame to be finished in a rich, black stain. The look is African-inspired, but with a modern leaning. Beveled mirror. Also available in a floor length version (4615).

Geometric design and minimalist styling give this simple, chic mirror modern sophistication. A frameless, irregular hexagon is suspended from an antique brass mounting hook by a strap of black leather. The plain glass mirror is mounted on a thick antique brass base, so it is raised about 2 inches from the wall, casting a slight shadow and adding dimension to a wall space. The narrow profile works well in a dressing room or powder room and looks extra-sleek when hung in a series.
Round mirror with black iron frame is accented with polished nickel hardware. Mirror hangs from a black leather strap and a polished nickel finish metal nob.
Rectangular wall mirror is crafted from distressed mirror pieces in a patchwork design boxed mounted on wood frame with stained wood edging.

A cousin to the rectangular Autero Mirror (DD2004), this round mirror is held by a spike that appears to have been hammered into the wall. However, the piece is actually suspended from a cleat on the mirror’s back, so it is purely decorative. The iron frame has intensely etched texturing and is finished in burnt wax, surrounding a flat mirror. Barry suggests using two over the double vanity in the master bathroom. Also available in a smaller version (DD2615).

Inspired by sophisticated jewelry design, this geometric mirror is an elegant accent for any space. A simple antique brass finish frame is decked in an outer iron trim of dual-sized blocks, each featuring rich texture in a natural finish that looks both raw and hammered. The combination of these metallic tones and contrasting surfaces gives the mirror an organic modern look. The rectangular mirror features a bevel.

Featuring a natural iron frame, polished brass accents and a plain mirror, the Janey Mirror is a contemporary lesson in mixed materials. Perfect as a pair or trio. Also available in round (4183). Hung with a security cleat attachment.

With its thick, blackened iron frame, this 82” rectangular mirror commands attention. Ideal for leaning against the wall or hanging with the security cleat attachment. The size is perfect for vertical or horizontal hanging.

A beautiful steel blue colored mirror frame accented with magnifying glass rounds set in antique brass. The center mirror is plain, so it is perfect for a hallway or powder room. Can be hung vertically or horizontally.
Individual iron rods are welded together and finished in antique gold leaf to create this fresh interpretation of the always popular starburst. The round shape looks great alone or in multiples.

Featuring a natural iron frame, polished brass accents and a plain mirror, the Janey Mirror is a contemporary lesson in mixed materials. Perfect as a pair or trio. Also available in square (4141). Hung with a security cleat attachment.
Part sculpture, part mirror. With its hammered iron frame and plain mirror, the Garza Mirror is all bold and beauty. Features a security cleat attachment. Finish may vary.

An intricate web is the defining element in this round wall mirror. The frame is made out of solid brass and each band is hand finished to give it a matte texture. Each band is then welded together to make an intricate web. Security cleat hanging hardware.

Versatile in form, the Belmont Mirror marries dueling design references to create a transitional piece fit for any setting. Decorative natural iron cleats create the illusion of suspension while the contemporary antique brass frame anchors the entire design. The frame also features hand-carved grooves along the perimeter, adding an element of artistry to the modern form. Make a statement by placing a pair in a master bath.

This softly shaped antique brass wire mirror has an elegant yet organic feel making it the perfect wall piece to hang over our Gunther Credenza (5359). The delicate undulating frame surrounds a beveled mirror. Features a security cleat attachment.
This round antique brass finished mirror is suspended by a chain featuring round and oval alternating links. Wall mount hook assembly.

This large, round, speckled antiqued mirror is banded with a narrow iron frame finished in gold leaf. Layer multiples and lean them on a large fireplace mantel or tall sideboard for a striking visual impact. Features a security cleat.

Make a big statement with the Sherman Mirror. With its large convex shape, the mirror will reflect the entire room in front of it. Hangs with a security cleat to allow for vertical display. Variations in the mirror may occur due to the large size.
No doubt this was geometric inspired…squares, rectangles and a circle all outlined in vintage brass. The mirror is plain with bevels.

Natural and geometric in form, this eye-catching mirror exhibits an earthy yet elegant element. A round beveled glass is encased by a square frame of thin, honey-brown stained rattan pieces that are delicately woven together in a web-like pattern. This unique piece will naturally open up and add character to a space. The Woodrow Mirror is crafted from naturally durable materials, making it a great piece for covered outdoor spaces as well.

One of the oldest forms of craftsmanship is showcased with the unparalleled design of this demanding piece. Fine wicker undergoes a unique washing process to create the rich hue of this large-scale oval mirror. The intriguing design of the wicker surrounding beveled glass delivers an urchin-like characteristic that brings a wall space to life. Security cleat hanging hardware allows for vertical or horizontal display.

A natural beauty, the Vendee Mirror stuns in simplicity. Crafted from golden stained pine, the border features natural rope that has been woven with expert precision. Security cleat for vertical or horizontal hanging. Finish may vary.

Neutral yet stoic,?the Lesley Mirror's light-walnut frame and plain mirror bring peace of mind with seamless symmetry. Also available in small (4107). Features a security cleat attachment. Finish may vary.
Large-scale oval wall mirror features a sunburst pattern with a rim of thin textured iron reeds in multiple lengths in an antiqued gold leaf finish.

A rectangular version of our Lesley Small Mirror (4107), the dark walnut frame and plain mirror bring peace of mind with seamless symmetry. Its neutral yet stoic façade delivers a certain charm to its demanding size. The stateliness of this piece makes it a great floor-leaning mirror as an alternative option. Security cleat hanging hardware allows for vertical and horizontal display.

Exquisitely crafted, the Alek Mirror by Frank Ponterio is sure to draw admirers. Faux quill detailing lends an heirloom quality to the black oak frame, versatile enough to sit in traditional or contemporary settings alike. Security cleat for vertical or horizontal hanging. Finish may vary.

Neutral yet stoic,?the Lesley Mirror's dark walnut frame and plain mirror bring peace of mind with seamless symmetry. Also available in large (4106). Features a security cleat attachment. Finish may vary.

Classic and chic, this full-length mirror lets you reflect on it all. The oblong shape lends a contemporary touch to its traditional style. The unobtrusive frame is crafted from iron with a vintage brass finish and the plain mirror makes this piece functional. Features multiple security cleats to hang vertically or horizontally.

Modern sophistication is at the core of this mirror’s inspiration—a play on rounded and angular geometric lines. The square mirror is slightly embedded into the thick circular frame, the inner edge trimmed in taupe lacquer, which matches the outer trim to add more depth and contrast. The frame is leafed in gold in a tiled pattern, each applied by hand and then polished-off with a clear lacquer finish. In the end, this mirror is shining and glossy from every angle when it is hung.

Industrial and contemporary in style, this striking mirror evokes the essence of unique design. A robust rectangular antique brass placted iron frame is adorned with a few etched plated brass disks, reminiscent of lily pads, in a bronze, silver and brass finish to create an intriguing and captivating looking glass. Perfect for adding a slight Art Nouveau touch to a space. Hung with a security cleat attachment.

The organic design of this slightly irregular circular-shaped mirror creates interest. A simple antique brass frame surrounds a beveled antiqued glass mirror. Features three security cleat attachments, so you can choose how to angle it. Whether you hang in multiples or solo over a vanity, this unique and off-kilter piece makes a great conversation starter.

Brilliant against an expansive wall, this modern piece solves a variety of design issues. The rectangular iron panel is entirely finished with gold leaf and frames a geometric overlay of intersecting circles, which have a layered interplay with the mirrors beneath. There’s no way you can have a bad day with this shiny and bubbly piece around. Designed to pair seamlessly with the left version (4623) for a continuous design. Gold leaf finish may vary.

A classic mirror redefined with bohemian flair. The Moon Glow’s stacked mirrors are a representation of a celestial space when the planets perfectly align - only seen through a clear night sky over the vast playa. The mini mirror balanced over the large circular antique brass frame features a deep plum hue while the large mirror boasts a stained antique finish. Antiquing is hand-applied and will vary. It hangs sturdy and flush to the wall using a security cleat mount.

Brilliant against an expansive wall, this modern piece solves a variety of design issues. The rectangular iron panel is entirely finished with gold leaf and frames a geometric overlay of intersecting circles, which have a layered interplay with the mirrors beneath. There’s no way you can have a bad day with this shiny and bubbly piece around. Designed to pair seamlessly with the right version (4624) for a continuous design. Gold leaf finish may vary.

Though it possesses a minimal aesthetic, this round mirror is a clean and sleek take on turn-of-the-century French Dormer windows. This version is modernized with an antiqued brass finish and fitted with bevel-edge mirrored panels—a combination of details that elevate the look. Hangs on a security cleat attachment.

Hovering ever-so-slightly against the wall, this brilliant mirror performs “depth-defying” feats in a space. Two antique brass brackets hold a plain glass mirror, which has rounded edges for a softer look. Can be hung vertically or horizontally depending on the wall space. Hangs on two security cleat attachments. Also available in polished nickel (6873).

Sometimes it’s just a simple twist on a traditional design that can refresh and elevate the look of a piece. A dual antiqued brass finish frame trims smoke glass mirrors, each possessing the secret of this mirror’s mystique: a sultry, smoky, sepia tone. This mirror hangs both vertically or horizontally to fit your space perfectly. Hangs on a security cleat attachment.

The Lianna Mirror's unique shape is a statement in itself, but combined with a hammered, gold-finished iron frame and black chiseled marble crown, it becomes a true focal point for any room. Features a security cleat attachment. Marble may vary.

A geometric pattern enveloped in a gold leafed iron finish, the Llewellyn Mirror is the personification of glamorously delicate design.?Features a security cleat attachment. Can be hung vertically or horizontally. Gold leaf may vary.

Surreal and alluring brass in a rose gold hue, the Eclipse Mirror is meant to bring creative energy to a space without taking over. Rose gold antiquing is hand-applied to the mirror and will vary. It hangs sturdy and flush to the wall using a security cleat mount.

A rounded corner, beveled, plain mirror sits inside a black nickel frame with polished brass accents. Perfect for a bathroom or over a console table to check yourself before heading out the door. Features a security cleat. Square Mirror with leather (DJ2050) also available.

The beveled Elton Mirror with its brass clad, textured frame inspires a feeling of warm tactility. The antique brass finish combines with the ridged border to create a piece that brings large-scale artisan quality to the home. Features a security cleat attachment. Clad may vary.

Inspired by the resilience of the sea, the Whitlock Mirror is a testament to nature's beauty. Rattan is woven and bound together with dark leather and then finished in a gray wash to create a classic yet intriguing design. The thick diameter of the rattan surrounds a large, round beveled mirror, creating a slight convex. Its stately frame is accompanied by a decorative top ring that delivers a nautical element to this natural piece. Finish may vary.

Like finding a needle in a haystack, the design of this mirror is quite rare. Rattan is first steamed and then wrapped by hand in a wheat sheaf fashion to create a starburst-like form that surrounds beveled glass. Fashioned onto the top of a rattan frame in a gray wash finish, the design produces a floating effect that delivers a unique visual appeal to a space.

The large scale Fallon Mirror boasts a fascinating frame made up of exaggerated facets and geometric shapes. The hand-applied gold leaf finish gives the mirror a luxe, elegant feel, while its sharp angles and subsequent shadows add a hard-edged dimension. Can be hung vertically or horizontally. Features a security cleat attachment.

Inspired by our Geoffrey Collection, this mirror is reminiscent of a ship's porthole—a round circular window—and works to deliver a nautical element to a room. The gray wash finish delivers a weathered look to the handcrafted wood and rusted iron frame that surrounds a plain round mirror. Accented with a decorative ring for an even more seagoing appeal. Hung with a security cleat attachment. Finish may vary

The Pacific Mirror was inspired by the exotic material used to make it: Kubu rattan. Weavers use this Southeast Asian cane because of its incredible malleability and durability, exhibited in this mirrors frame through an intricately woven series of layers. Before hand-weaving the structure, the rattan is immersed for several weeks in a dye that uses only local leaves, achieving the natural gray finish. The round mirror is trimmed in a bevel for an added sense of elegance.

The finishing details give this mirror unparalleled elegance and sophistication. Completely wrapped in split-leather gray suede, the mirror is softened by a velvetty texture. Each patch of suede is hand-cut and finished with a contrasting white top- stitch, adding a polished touch. Inset in the frame is a circular mirror, adding even more geometric styling to its classic look. The blend of masculine and feminine aesthetics creates a balance that blends seamlessly into just about any style space.

Three levels of wood-carved scallops form the frame of this exotic round mirror. Each scallop is carved with a hollow center to reveal the wall beneath, so it not only adds texture, but also dramatic depth. To create the unique finish, the wood is sandblasted to bring out the rich grain, then it is brushed with a gray wash to pronounce the intense graining even further. Also hand-finished is the silvered convex mirror, which will have slight surface variance in tone and reflection.

The epitome of extraordinary design, this striking accent mirror brings the wow-factor to a space. Framed in gray-finished wood, 31 mirror panels form a stunning radial pattern around a central round mirror, all of them with a rich, burnt antique finish. Features a security cleat attachment. Mirror finish may vary.

This unique mirror utilizes multiple styles, methods and materials to create the stained antique finish. Its solid glass bubbles are hand-applied, while the splattered antique finish is a product of a reaction between the raw glass and a chemical solution. Features a security cleat attachment. Antiqued finish and other details may vary. A rectangular version is also available (2236).

The art of distressing requires immense skill as evidenced in this handsome transitional mirror. Once the weathered gray finish is applied, each piece of cut wood is brushed in detail, adding a natural look to the frame’s modern silhouette. Fits perfectly in your space, displayed either vertically or horizontally. Hung with security cleat attachment. Weathered finish may vary.

Dramatically distressed, the Jeremiah Mirror may have a familiar rectangular frame, but when paired with the mirror's antiqued finish, the piece is anything but ordinary. Functional art that can be hung vertically or horizontally. Hung with a security cleat attachment. Finish may vary.

This unique mirror utilizes multiple styles, methods and materials to create its stained antique finish. Its solid glass bubbles are hand-applied, while the splattered antique finish is a product of a reaction between the raw glass and a chemical solution. Can be hung vertically or horizontally and we think it would be great in pairs. Features a security cleat attachment. Finish may vary.

This tall elegant oval mirror has an antiqued surface around the edges. The iron frame is hand finished with champagne leaf. Features a security cleat attachment and can be hung vertically or horizontally. Due to the craftsmanship of this mirror, the hand applied inner border and antiqued mirror may vary.

A truly one-of-a-kind piece, the Jude Mirror's starburst-patterned antiquing amidst a convex mirror draws attention from all angles. Also available in small (2865) and large (4113). Features a security cleat attachment. Finish may vary.
Large-scale oval wall mirror features a sunburst pattern with a rim of thin textured iron reeds in multiple lengths in an antiqued silver leaf finish.
Round wall mirror with thin aluminum frame and a mirrored center.
Rectangular floor mirror features antiqued mirror border over a wood frame with silver leaf edge finish.
Round beveled wall mirror is framed in iron with an antique nickel finish and hangs from hinge-like wall plate attached by a single oval chain link.
Terrace Bookshelf

Svelte and lean, this narrow console showcases beauty without a wide footprint. Its unique geometric design adds depth and intrigue; as you walk around the table, the perspective changes. The slender metal frame is finished in antique brass with clean welding joints that are a work of true craftsmanship. The crowning feature is an inset plate of clear glass with an elegant antiqued trim, creating a beautiful balance between old world and modern styles.
Bellamy Round Side Table

Our mantra in creating this basket-inspired weave was a marriage of global craft and modern geometry. Cast aluminum hexagons are combined into a circular form and then plated with brass and polshed to a high sheen. This makes for a very dramatic entry table. Base only. Think of this as jewelry for the home.
Kyra Cocktail Table

This antique brass coffee table melds artistry with function. A hand-etched design on the clad tabletop moves outward from where the four pieces meet, creating a visual ripple that draws the eye in. Look no more - this is the perfect statement piece for your living room. Finish may vary.

Craftsman style handiwork and modern elegance make a beautiful collaboration in this dynamic chair. It’s made entirely from solid oak and is finished in a dark umber veneer that has wonderful wood textures you can see and feel. Turned details and brass inlay in the top rail all bring a sense of sophistication and edge to the design. Also comes in Graphite Leather (8093).

The sophistication of art deco design gets an encore with this one-of-a-kind table. Crafted of solid oak, handsomely cut legs and radial-patterned top stay true to its inspired design, while the rich umber veneer elevates and updates the look. The legs are capped in aged brass and feature levelers to keep it steady.

This stately bookshelf is peppered with refined design details. Crafted from American walnut, it features a quarter-sawn grain and a silky satin warm walnut finish. English dovetail joinery on the soft close drawers and triple miter joints on the edges of the frame show exemplary craftsmanship. Line two or three in a row to frame a room.

Sleek and inviting, this Scandinavian-inspired coffee table is bound by delicate details. From beveled edges to antique brass ferrules, each element is enhanced by the satin walnut finished veneer. Finished with a natural lacquer stain to highlight the quarter-sawn grain. Style two facing opposite directions to create a rectangular configuration. Finish may vary.

Bronzed iron rods create linear movement in this gridded cocktail table design. Exposed brass caps sit atop the smoked glass top where the frame and tabletop meet. The glass has a subtle brown hue. Finish may vary. Also available as a side table (2982).

This tiered accent table is a mid-century dream. A clear lacquer was applied, leaving the grain on the satin walnut veneer table top exposed for a natural effect. The beveled, solid-oak black stained brim and antique brass legs are alluring. Finish may vary.

Sleek but layered with texture and interest this natural iron table, with antique brass nailhead details and an antiqued mirror top, allows lots of surface while taking up little visual space. Perfect as the center of a seating arrangement in any contemporary or transitional space, formal or informal, and so practical! Finish may vary.
Stanley Costello Cocktail Table

Modern minimalism at its finest. From the curved beveled edges to the slim bronze base, less is more on this petite oak cocktail table finished in an ebony stain. Position two side-by-side for larger living spaces.

Make a grand statement with this natural iron bookshelf, featuring five clear glass shelves. Oversized in scale, this is perfect for a large living area or library where you can flank two next to a window. Finish may vary.
Natural iron legs converge to create a modern web that is reminiscent of a computer grid. Clear glass top rests on polished brass caps. Finish may vary.

Whether a place to gather your things in an entryway or as a decorative seat at the foot of a bed, this handsome, mid-century modern inspired bench has one-of-a-kind looks. Bronze-finish tapered legs raise a plush, button-tufted seat, wrapped in unique, diamond-pattern chenille. The slight angles of the bench and updated upholstery give it a hint of contemporary style. Also comes in watercrest velvet (4549) and muslin (4551).

Celerie Kemble’s love of natural design shines through in this intricately crafted cocktail table. Mango wood is cut and carved by hand to create this rich design on all four sides. Then, the entire piece is finished in a handsome heritage gray, just enough to keep some of the natural wood details visible. Also available as a console (DC2005).
Step into the woods with the Garrix Console. The natural iron frame resembles a nest of branches that is slightly undone and romantic. Topped with clear glass. Finish may vary.

We've warmed this industrial design up with natural elements like cast iron and white marble. The iron legs feature hand-formed ridges that feel organic, which have been blackened then lightly polished to highligh the textured surface. Finish and marble may vary.

This chic bar stool features Art Nouveau vibes that will complement traditional or contemporary design schemes. Dove gray leather and vintage silver are a sleek pairing. Also available as a counter stool (4399) and in antique brass/black leather (4396). Leather may vary.
Keran Coffee Table

ItemName: Capri Chair Oyster Boucle Champagne Swivel
ItemDescription: Deep, elegant tufting comes together with soft curves and a champagne-finished swivel base to create the classically stylish Capri Chair. This updated take on the Springsteen Chair is covered in Oyster Boucle, highlighted by its looped or curled ply, further complementing the frame.
Julian Desk

A unique form, slightly angled edges and exposed bronze finished hardware are some of the standout details on this multi-faceted design. We love how the soft smoke finish allows the rift sawn oak grain to peek through. Nylon nail-in glides will protect exposed floors. Pair with 5515 to create a split-level cocktail table or use separately as side tables.

Pair with 5516 to create a split-level cocktail table or use separately as side tables.

ItemName: Mitchell Sofa Flint Velvet Matte Black
ItemDescription: The Mitchell Sofa has an understated prowess that gives it universal appeal. The curved arms and back soften the frame and add feminine flair to this traditionally modern silhouette. Gracefully poised on four steel legs that feature a matte black finish and antique brass cap.

This solid oak console doesn't need much stylingùthe design speaks for itself. While the back is straight, the front features a unique stair-step design that meets in the center, adding dimension. Each oak panel is finished in cerused gray and is ac cented with a blackened steel plate.
We love the bold lines and materials on this geometric design. The iron base is finished in a rich gunmetal that contrasts the lighter concrete top. Finish may vary.

This pair of cocktail tables takes a curtsey to midcentury design and they are ever so adaptable. Try slipping an extended leg under a sofa to bring its antiqued mirror surface closer. Or draw them closer together, the options are endless. Available in natural iron with antique mirror top we love these tables for their mix of modern design and traditional craft. Finish may vary.

ItemName: Mitchell Sofa Graphite Leather Matte Black
ItemDescription: The Mitchell Sofa has an understated prowess that gives it universal appeal. The curved arms and back soften the frame and add feminine flair to this traditionally modern silhouette. Gracefully poised on four steel legs that feature a matte black finish and antique brass cap.

This round cocktail table perfectly represents the essence of artisan design and craftsmanship. First, note the unique texture of the hand-hammered top, and then the solid iron bar that has been hand-forged into a curvaceous knot detail on each leg. The natural iron finish keeps it simple and reinforces the organic nature of the design. Round cocktail tables are inviting and without the sharp corners are children and pet friendly.
This cast iron whimsical dining table base is shaped like tree branches. A large round clear glass top rests on top of the base. Also available with 54", 60" and 66" glass
This cast iron whimsical dining table base is shaped like tree branches. A large round clear glass top rests on top of the base. Also available with 48," 54," and 60" glass.

A perfect display shelf made from textured iron bar stock and finished in bright silver leaf. The creative arrangement of the eight glass shelves helps you spotlight your collectables. We'd love to display a collection of handbags or shoes in a bedroom on this unique shelf.

The perfect armchair, Nicola is plush and inviting while maintaining a natural sense of refinement. The exposed solid maple frame is expertly crafted, featuring curved arms, legs and accents finished in a deep umber stain. The frame is further accentuated by the Paloma Chenille fabric, a textured blend with hints of grey and taupe.
This cast iron whimsical dining table base is shaped like tree branches. A large round clear glass top rests on top of the base. Also available with 48," 54," and 66" glass.

Create a modern statement with this signature iron sphere sculpture made of square bar stock and finished in gold leaf. Place a single one on top of a stack of books, or buy all the versions and fill a bowl. Available in two sizes and two finishes (burnt wax iron and gold leaf).
Zephyr Bench

The secret to this lovely, ethereal piece lies in a single, clear crystal ball foot that looks to seemingly suspend the end of bowl in midair. Lustrous brass is the perfect counterpoint to crystal, accentuating the sculptural effects of its organic, sensual shape. Use it for jewel-like effect as a catchall on a cocktail or side table, entry table, or dressing vanity.
Jensen Magnifying Object

Smooth cuts create the supple ribbed textures in this glass vase. The blend of matte and glossy finishes heightens the look, formed in smoky tobacco colored glass for even more luxury. Though it is made to fulfill a variety of purposes, it captures beauty even on its own. Also comes as a centerpiece (6899)

Smooth cuts create the supple ribbed textures in this glass centerpiece. The blend of matte and glossy finishes heightens the look, formed in smoky tobacco colored glass for even more luxury. Though it is made to fulfill a variety of purposes, it captures beauty even on its own. Also comes as a vase (6898).

Our variant on the monumental urn is modernized and unadorned, allowing eyes to focus on its unique form and finish. Super slim handles and a thin tablet plinth set off a smooth, lustrous brass exterior, while contrasting hammered brass dresses its interior.

Rendered in ethereal blue with clear glass, this footed bowl echoes the shapes of antique Roman glass. Pair two for a dining centerpiece beautiful as is, or as an extra-wide mouthed vase to keep blooms in place.

Inspiration can come from the wildest places. Crafted thoughtfully to look just like a true gazelle horn, this sculpture is an almost identical replica, with a natural finish that accentuates all the details. Up close you can see grooves and markings that have been artistically recreated for lifelike detail. Mounted to an inch-thick piece of cut crystal, it stands majestically at over two feet tall. Finish may vary. Also comes in an antique brass finish (9554).
Riya Container

This slender porcelain vase has so many unexpected features, you’ll forever be in awe. It is handcrafted in a super sleek and ultra-thin form, finished in a glacial blue reactive glaze that gives it an almost iridescent shine. The glaze also adds rich textures that occur naturally once it has been applied, and it’s these textures that accentuate the curves and lines in the porcelain. Glaze finish may vary.

This generous lidded, blackened iron box is the perfect storage space for magazines and the remote on a cocktail table. Use for glasses and barware at the bar, or as a desk caddy on a large home office table desk. Use your imagination!
Stead Sculpture

This magnificent piece is made using a very intensive glassblowing method, two thick layers of glass and a lot of ingenuity. The result is this chestnut-ombre coloration that almost glows through the top layer. Once the layers are united, the surface is hand chiseled creating the signature honeycomb surface texture

Revered in ancient Egypt, the scarab is a sacred status symbol that has adorned designs for centuries. The antique brass motif flanks a beautiful honed black granite tray. Perfect for candles, collectibles or a tasteful charcuterie spread. Granite may vary.
Lola Rectangular Boxes, Set of 2
Lupita Oval Tray
Keri Tray
Jasper Wine Cooler

Mirror and marble come together to create an instantly iconic piece. With its classic white marble base and gold leafed rim, the Irene Table Mirror is double sided to have either an antiqued or plain mirror reflection. Marble and finish may vary.
Jarvis Vase
This round marbled mercury glass vase is handcrafted so no two pieces will have the same surface pattern. Looks great when shown with DK6017 and DK6016.

Nothing has quite the polish like cut glass. This sultry vase, with its smoky gray tone and irregular diamond etching, holds a bit of mystery. What isn’t a mystery is how much class it will add to a space, no matter if you fill it with decorative accoutrements or leave it solo. Also comes in a centerpiece (6896).

What isn’t a mystery is how much class it will add to a space, no matter if you fill it with decorative accoutrements or leave it solo. Also comes in a vase (6897).

This unique, adjustable standing accessory features a convex mirror that adds interest and depth to any space. The natural cast iron frame is accented with polished brass detail for contrast. Perfect in a corner or at the end of a long hall.
Smoke toned art glass updates this classic footed bowl. Watch its hues shift from charcoal to ash as light plays across its gently ribbed surface, rendering the bowl almost too pretty to fill.
This irregularly-shaped gray smoked colored glass vase is mouth blown into a specially shaped mold. Sculptural enough to look beautiful without flowers.
Pilcher Bookends, Pair
Millicent Small Centerpiece

The long elegant neck on our smoke cased glass vase creates an ideal container for a single stem or branch. Beautiful alone, it's also intended to be clustered in numbers as a centerpiece.
