Up close you can see grooves and markings that have been artistically recreated for lifelike detail. Mounted to an inch-thick piece of cut crystal, it stands majestically at over two feet tall. Finish may vary. Also comes in a natural finish (9555).

A gleaming sphere rests on a cluster of natural iron thorns, perfect as a centerpiece or as a sculptural accent. The sphere breaks in half as two burnished gold finished bowls, one resting on the thorny stand and the other one nearby. Use your imagi
The gilded cousin of our natural iron thorn branch accessory, finished in gold leaf. Use it the same way but in a more formal setting. Also available in natural iron (DD2082). Gold leaf may vary.
Undulating porcelain cylinder shape has been finished with a white crackle. The tall drum white linen shade is lined in white cotton and has a porcelain finial to match.

With a strip of antique brass, the snowy white onyx Farrell Lamp continues the retro Hollywood glam found throughout the Fall 2016 collection. The Farrell's irregularly shaped base is made further intriguing with its hard edges and angular form. Perfect for adding subtle drama to a formal space. Topped with a rectangular ivory microfiber shade that is trimmed vertically to mimic the brass band.

Entirely unique, this terracotta lamp is made completely by hand. It’s first formed on the potter’s wheel, after which all of the banded textures are etched and stamped by hand. The admiral blue finish is formulated exclusively for this piece to accentuate and draw out all the handcrafted elements. It’s a remarkable design that brings artistic design to lighting. It is topped with a tapered navy linen shade with white cotton lining. Finish may vary.

With its lovely grainy textures and incredible malleability, we’re falling in love with terracotta—even as a material for our lamp bases. The Sachin Lamp is unique in its tribal-inspired designs, deeply etched grooves, and the slightly imperfect natu re of its handmade details. To accentuate all its finer points, potters finish the piece with a cortado matte glaze that really pulls out its strong features. It is topped with a light beige linen drum shade with white cotton lining. Finish may vary.

It takes excellence and expert knowledge in glassblowing to create patterned designs such as this. The cylinder design is made by hand from art glass, which is created by taking a base glass and then adding stems of colored glass to create unique patterns. This one has a clear base glass with soft, opaque swirls that make it ever-so-elegant. Topped with a microfiber drum shade in light cinder with an acrylic ball finial. Glass designs may vary.

Classic with a twist. This table lamp takes a geometric spin on the transparency of cut crystal; it is a towering masterpiece with sharp angles and multiple facets. The smoke crystal form mimics a traditional candlestick, though modernized with a streamlined look. The base is made of steel with a vintage silver finish, which pairs beautifully with the crystal tone. It is topped with a gray linen drum shade and fitted with a matching smoky crystal finial.

Built for the great outdoors, this versatile lantern pairs the resilience of industrial style with a modern aesthetic. The steel frame is finished in an aged iron, so it exudes a debonair attitude, but the clean lines andsimple construction allow it to blend in with any surrounding. The top is fitted with a handle accent, recalling a traditional lantern function, and the bulb is concealed in an opal glass sleeve, casting warm light all around. Also available in aged brass (49203).

Mercury glass has been used for centuries to create traditional décor pieces.This table lamp, featuring a moss green finish that’s matte and distressed to give it a handsome, aged look. It naturally creates drip textures that make it even more spectacular—when switched on, it almost has an iridescent sheen. The base is crafted from silver-leaf finished wood. It is topped with a taupe sheer microfiber drum shade with matching cotton lining. Finish may vary.

Sleek and modern in form, this piece has neutral tones and subtle details that allow it to work well in so many ways. The cylinder features two layers of bi-tonal lacquer, which are applied in the traditional -multi-layering method for a completely smooth finish. The light and dark taupe tones are separated by a thin line of inlay brass, that has a seamless weld. Topped with an off-white silk drum shade with an ivory cotton lining and cord detail to balance with the lamp design.

Utterly fantastical in its study of shape, this lamp is anything but ordinary. From every direction, the silhouette reveals three stacked rounded forms—cylinder, disk and cone—to showcase angular composition and balance. It has a mid-century feel, but its deep antiqued aluminum finish offers a new take on the style. It’s a bit small in scale, so it makes for a handsome task lamp. It is topped with a tapered linen shade in ivory with a white cotton lining.

Adding scale without the traditional visual weight of iron, here is a table lamp that provides an obscure form and brilliant function. The simple, open-form design is created by the seamless fusion of six posts, which connect two round outlines to form the cylinder shape, one that is a play on negative space. Once made, it is then finished in an antique brass to add a hint of grandeur to complement its presence. It is topped with an ivory linen drum shade with white cotton lining.

Elegant in style and simple in form, this table lamp defines traditional lighting design. Crafted from blown glass, this lamp features hand-etched bands that surround its circumference, which is both distinctive and intriguing. The iridescent arctic and frost glaze finishes lend a coastal and classic touch. Topped with a white linen drum shade with white cotton lining. Finish may vary.

The hue of this lamp's profile delivers a dynamic element to a space. Each is hand-pressed to create the vase-shaped base, and then handpainted with a volcanic glaze to deliver texture and bubbling to the surface. Gray and white peeks through the ash black matte finish that fades into a sheen. Works well to illuminate any setting, but its neutral tones allow it to easily coordinate with any style décor. Topped with a gray morn linen drum shade with gray morn cotton lining and a matching finial.

So many inspirations come to mind in this wonderfully whimsical porcelain lamp. Its handcrafted bottle form, hand-painted designs and contrasting tones lend an exotic, almost tribal air to the piece, though it is truly modern to its core. Note all the textures in the glaze—a natural occurrence in the process that makes it extra special. Topped with a navy blue linen drum shade with ivory cotton lining and an acrylic ball finial. Glaze finish may vary.

The rich textures in this porcelain lamp are created by hand and skill of artisan potters. After the porcelain is formed, they take small clay combs and create all the etchings, which is why, up close, you’ll notice slight organic details. The provincial blue glaze only adds to the textures and has a slight crackling where etchings are absent. Topped with a drum shade in white linen with cotton lining and an acrylic ball finial. Glaze finish may vary.

Frank Ponterio upped the ante with bespoke detailing and expert craftsmanship on this arresting lamp design. Simplistic in form, the frame is covered in rich black leather that has been embossed to achieve a shagreen effect. Antique brass wraps the edges for added flair. Topped with an eggshell-colored silk shade

Create a tranquil setting while delivering a luxe touch to a space with this delicately daring lamp. Featuring a conical-shaped pale brass top that funnels into a black marble form with a smoke crystal base.The warm glow of the lamp's light creates a desirable ambience for the space, while simultaneously accentuating the fluidity of the slight veining on the black marble. Topped with a gray morn linen drum shade with off-white cotton lining and a matching metal finial. Finish may vary.

Dark and mysterious, this table lamp brings light even with its own inky hue. It’s completely crafted from blackened aluminum, one of our first pieces to adorn this rich finish. The result is a sort of matte graphite look, with a bit of a raw effect, which brings out the industrial edge of this lamp. It is topped with an off-white linen drum shade with white cotton lining.

The Terrell Lamp raises the bar on industrial and modern lighting. Rough aluminum is welded together and then polished to present a slight texture to the structure. Antique brass and bronze finishes have been applied, creating a unique contrast. Its cinched waist creates a unique divergence of the metal form and delivers an airiness to the otherwise solid base. Topped with a tapered off-white linen shade with white cotton lining and a matching metal finial. Finish may vary.

Inspired by modern architecture, Frank Ponterio designed this statement-making lamp design with the grids of the Chicago skyline in mind. The streamlined steel form features glossy back enamel paired with a heritage brass overlay, cage-like in form. Topped with a black microfiber shade with a gold foil interior.

A work of art in process for thousands of years finally comes to fruition with our Valletta Lamp. Petrified wood is found and then skillfully cut into tiles to create this natural mosaic piece. The base is then polished in a dark natural finish for a handsome and quite befitting touch. Topped with a rectangle white linen shade with white cotton lining. Finish may vary.

The intriguing shape and use of traditional materials are sure to make our Vanna Lamp the focal accent of any space. The glass base of the tiered, cymbal-like form features a blackened-bronze finish that delivers a metallic luster. Mounted on an acrylic platform. Topped with an off-white linen drum shade with off-white cotton lining and an acrylic sphere finial. Finish may vary.

Though this lamp has a shape inspired by a traditional urn design, it has been styled through a modern lens to give it a little more edge and flair. It’s crafted from aluminum, which is polished with an oil-rubbed bronze finish and accented at the bottom with a band of antique brass finishing. Overall, it is an updated look with a touch of masculinity. It’s topped with an ivory drum linen shade and white cotton lining.

With its grainy textures and malliability, we've taken our terracotta-obsession to our lamp bases. The Saffron Lamp is unique in its deep, athena gray, hand-painted textures, and the curves of its hand-thrown construction. This terracotta piece is especially unique in that it has a fully polished look that is glamorous, but also accentuates and elevates its exotic look. It is topped with an ash gray microfiber drum shade with white cotton lining. Finish may vary.

The luxurious yet functional Raven Lamp uses an ancient Japanese process called eggshell inlay, where they layer the base with eggshells and cover them with a black finish. Then, it’s sanded down to reveal portions of both the eggshells and the black to give it textural depth. The back and base are finished in a smooth, solid, dark lacquer, a perfect counterpart to the ornate facade. It is topped with a black, rectangular microfiber shade with contrasting mustard lining. Finish may vary

There’s a wink and a nod to British colonial design in this lamp. Primarily crafted from blackened iron, which involves a finishing process that adds longevity to the metal and also adds a sleek, matte black finish. The palm leaf and ball accent are made of a warm, vintage-finished brass for the perfect amount of polish. Topped with a cylinder drum shade in cloud beige linen with ivory cotton lining and matching brass ball finial.

This deceptively simple design has many noteworthy details, from the clever open base, to the metal drum shade with a frosted acrylic diffuser, to the double socket with one pull chain. This is a modern classic

The Brutalist style is often characterized by abstracted organic forms, with rough textures; and a dark, earth-toned palette. The slight irregularities suggest a connection to nature and handcrafting rather than the sharp precision of machine production. This cast aluminum lamp finished in a dark antique bronze is a great example of the Brutalist design trend. It is topped with an off-white linen drum shade with hand rolled edges and is lined in off-white cotton.

Dark, modern metal contrasts with polished brass to form the look of elegance and sophistication in this urn lamp. The shining bronze accents in the base trim, stem fitting and urn lid perk up the glossy, polished black finish. Fitted with a drum shade in ivory microfiber with a one-inch flat hem on the top and bottom and ivory cotton lining. Topped with a matching bronze-finished finial.

Cylindrical with a twist, the Herschel Lamp is an iron, bronze-finished beauty that instantly adds weight and artisan-detail to any space. The hammered finish brings unexpectedness to the lamp's modified hourglass form. Topped with a natural linen drum shade and matching finial. Matching cocktail table (2824) and side table (2825) also available. Finish may vary.
Glass body table lamp with black and silver reactive marbled finish topped with a black linen textured paper shade with brushed silver paper lining and diffuser. 3-way switch. Finish may vary.

Almost Brutalist in its raw and powerful form, this lamp exemplifies eclectic style statements. The pillar is crafted from ceramic, as are the ridged, abstract accents, and the entire piece is brushed with a blackened pewter finish. The rich finish is applied by hand, evidenced in the bold brushstroke textures. Fitted with a black linen drum shade with light silver microfiber lining for added reflective light. Topped with a matching ceramic finial. Finish may vary.

The sculptural form of this natural iron lamp is full of life. It's arresting features will pair well with a minimalist side table or console. Topped with a textured natural linen, rectangular drum shade with a taupe cotton lining. Also available in gold leaf (43002-847). Finish may vary.

Unique and intriguing in form, this modern marvel of a lamp is rich with details. The sculptural aluminum base has been sand-cast to create all the metallic textures, as well as highlight the heavily antiqued finish. It’s just the sort of lamp that brings light to a room, but with a presence that stands all on its own. Topped with a textured natural linen drum shade with an ivory cotton lining.

Equally modern and tribal, incorporate this table lamp into any space for a bit of eclectic flair. Sleek angles are molded from porcelain to form the base. The round base and tapered top are glazed in a saturated hue that is almost inky black, which surrounds a geometric indigo design. Topped with a drum shade in white linen with cotton lining and an acrylic ball finial. Glaze finish may vary.

Elegant in form and style, this table lamp defies the standard in lighting. Crafted from porcelain, it is finished in an uncommon chambray texture, which is both unique and alluring. It rests on a round, acrylic disk base. Topped with a tapered barrel shade in soft gray linen with cotton lining and an acrylic ball finial. Glaze finish may vary. Also comes in satin papyrus and gold (11020)

From organic impressions that resemble waves, to the rich sapphire hue, Lainey is wrought with elements from the deep blue sea. The bubbled surface texture even features subtle metallic highlights, resembling the glistening ocean at starlight. Paired with a clear acrylic base and an ivory microfiber drum shade. Finish may vary.

Brilliant not only due to its illuminating powers, but also its bright aquatic hue, here is a lamp with personality and zest. The reactive glaze finish covers every rib and taper, so it has texture to the touch and to the eye. Crafted from porcelain with rich details. Topped with a tapered barrel shade in white linen with cotton lining and contrasting brushed nickel ball finial. Glaze finish may vary.

The porcelain base of this lamp recalls the double gourd vases of Ancient China, some relics found go back to the Song Dynasty of the late 13th century. It’s been updated with strokes of indigo and a clean, polished white base, giving it a more modern look. Topped with a tapered empire shade in white linen with cotton lining and acrylic ball finial. Glaze finish may vary.

There's a quiet allure to the Kali Lamp. From the tapered collar, to soft metallic highlights speckled throughout the sapphire glass, to the clear acrylic base, delicate details add sophisticated charm. Topped with a white microfiber drum shade with a blue velvet trim. Also available in amber glass with metallic highlights (17406-532). Finish may vary.

This tabletop version of one of our most popular floor lamps (79680) is perfect for desks and nightstands. The antique black iron and antique brass design exudes a modern sensibility. The off-white linen shade swivels and houses two light bulbs, creating an even light source. The on/off switch is on the cord.

Rich textures and color give this lamp natural vibrance. It’s crafted from porcelain, with soft, round lines and scalloped ribbing that set it apart from ordinary lamps. The reactive glaze is such that it naturally forms a speckled texture, creating varying hues of blue throughout. Topped with a tapered barrel shade in white linen with cotton lining and contrasting brushed nickel ball finial. Glaze finish may vary.

The svelte neck on this refined ceramic table lamp draws the eye upward, a feature that will add height to any space. Finished with a zaffre blue reactive glaze, an earthy hue with visual texture. Topped with a tapered, off-white linen drum shade and matching ceramic finial. Finish may vary.

This classic ceramic form gets an update with an icy blue glaze. Perfect for coastal environments or any space that needs a subtle stroke of color. Topped with a white linen drum shade and matching ceramic finial. Finish may vary.

This ceramic Lorna Lamp features unnatural and irregular vertical stripes and ridges that clash with its otherwise warm and simple glacial reactive glaze finish. Topped with an off-white linen drum shade. Finish may vary.

Oceanside reactive glaze gives the cylindrical Laurel porcelain lamp its striking finish. Due to a chemical reaction during the lamp's firing, the glaze yields an arresting blend of blues, greens, and shades of white. Topped with an off-white linen drum shade. Finish may vary.

Grand curvatures and modern gray tones make for an inspiring place to work. The frame is coated in an exclusive, charcoal lacquer, rounded to give the desk a uniquely updated design. On the wide work space is a lacy and light, tropical ofram wood ven eer in chateau gray, laid with a slip matched technique where the slices are patterned in the same way, rather than alternating. In keeping the façade clean and sleek, the drawer features a recessed handle, with single extension, soft-close glides.

An oblong porcelain body is stacked on a matching porcelain base to create the simple, yet regal Kassy Lamp. The pill-like column features a striking teal reactive glaze finish, further complemented by the base's gunmetal reactive glaze. Topped with an ivory microfiber drum shade. Finish may vary.

Good looks and expert craftsmanship make this desk a brilliant balance of work and play. Built from solid oak, it’s finished in a deep umber veneer with natural wood textures for polished, sophisticated style. Find inspiration in the handcrafted marquetry inlay, made from top-quality rift-cut oak that gives the wood even textures and a clean grain. The legs feature levelers to keep it steady.
Iron writing desk on an “X” iron base in a natural iron finish and features three storage drawers with hooded pulls.

This handsome writing desk looks great on its own but can also handle sprawling paperwork given its generous surface area. The top features a rift-sawn oak grain and solid 3 band framing the edge. Antique brass ferrules and hardware glisten against the dark ebony stain. We've also added adjustable levelers on the feet?it's all in the details!

This petite desk exudes a brilliant balance of form and function. The seamless curvature of the solid walnut frame flows fluidly around the desk's top, creating a cohesive and streamlined look. The contrast of the black lacquer and satin walnut hues along with the antique brass hardware draws attention to its slender profile. Features three functional drawers for storage.

The stout stature and moody hue of this lamp delivers a distinct and dynamic element to a space. Each is hand-pressed into a mold to create the robust base, and then painted by hand with a matte charcoal finish that easily coordinates with any style décor. Crafted from terracotta, the handmade details and rich textures are illuminated when in use. Topped with a tapered off-white linen shade with off-white cotton lining and a matching terracotta finial. Finish may vary.

Mercury glass has been used for centuries to create traditional décor pieces. This table lamp features an ocean blue finish that’s rich and distressed to give it a handsome, aged look. The process naturally creates watercolor textures that make it even more spectacular—when switched on, it almost has an iridescent sheen where you can see small silver flecks. The base is crafted from gold-leaf finished wood. It is topped with a tapered gold silk shade with taupe cotton lining. Finish may vary.

Minimalism meets luxury in this seemingly simple column lamp, combining a powder blue porcelain body and a lustrous, gold raised pedestal stand. Pebble microfiber lining details its square ivory shade for extra subtlety.

This table lamp is a textural wonder visually and to the touch. All the etchings and divots are made in a ceramic base. The indigo reactive glaze accentuates these details. For more shine, it has been mounted to a champagne-leafed wooden base. It is topped with a deep blue velvet drum shade.

Sleek and modern in form, this piece has contrasting tones and subtle details that allow it to work well in so many spaces. The block base features two layers of lacquer in navy and taupe, which are applied in the traditional, multi-layering method for a completely smooth finish. The lighter and darker tones are separated by a thin line of inlay brass that has a seamless weld. Topped with an off-white silk rectangular shade with a white cotton lining.

Though simple in form, this table lamp has contrast and organic pottery textures that make it outstanding. Crafted from ceramic, it is finished in a slate blue reactive glaze that reveals an incredible variance and reactive coloring. One of the hidden details of this lamp is embedded in the glaze: during the firing process, crystalized flecks forms that add a slight sparkle. Topped with a tapered ivory linen shade with a white cotton lining. Finish may vary.

It is the artistry of glazing and in the organic layers that make this piece so special.The lapis reactive glaze is the meeting of two different finishes, one a reactive glaze, the other a matte lava glaze, creating depth, texture, dimension and tonality that makes for a remarkable lamp. Though the ceramic form is simplistic, this unique blend makes each one a wonder to behold. It is topped with a white parchment paper drum shade. Finish may vary.

This porcelain cylinder lamp, inspired by geometric shapes, has a surface pattern of concave divots that have been finished in a sky blue reactive glaze to create the spot-like pattern. The drum shade is made of a white microfiber, lined in gray microfiber.

The embodiment of artisan techniques, the Homer Lamp's ceramic body, finished in a celadon wash, features a uniquely simple ridged, layered surface texture. Topped with an off-white linen drum shade, lined in off-white cotton. Finish may vary.

Though the silhouette of this ceramic lamp is handcrafted in a unique, modern design, its muted blue reactive glaze lends a touch of traditional pottery style. Up close, you’ll notice fine texturing and subtle details that occur naturally and are different in each piece. Topped with a tapered, natural linen drum shade with ivory cotton lining and matching ceramic finial. Glaze finish may vary.

Who knew that leather and metal could make such a sophisticated pairing? Brushed brass forms the structure, indigo leather wraps it, stitched together with an exposed hem to add a handsome finishing touch. Topped with a tapered, white linen barrel shade with a cotton lining and matching brass ball finial. Also comes in cognac leather (DC12012), as well as a floor lamp version in cognac leather (DC72014) and indigo leather (DC72015). Leather finish may vary.

Truly a masterpiece, the Nigel Lamp pairs a classic silhouette with artful craftsmanship. Up close, you’ll notice thousands of midnight blue dots speckled across the milky porcelain base. Its extra-sensory details make it a piece you’ll want to see and touch. Topped with a tapered barrel shade in white linen with cotton lining and matching ceramic finial. Also available as a vase (7418).

This earthy lamp has vintage character with modern sensibility. It is completely handcrafted, down to the accents and final polish. It’s unique coloring is due to the glacial blue reactive glaze, which adds rich textures that occur naturally once it has been applied. It’s these textures that accentuate the curves and details in the porcelain. Topped with a drum shade in white cotton with ivory cotton lining and matching ceramic finial. Glaze finish may vary.

Sleek angles and planes make this lamp a geometric wonder. Handcrafted in porcelain, its modern aesthetic is given a traditional twist—a celadon glaze that recalls ancient Han dynasty pottery. Up close, you’ll notice a slight crackle texture in the finish. Mounted on a square acrylic plaque. Topped with a drum shade in light gray cotton with white cotton lining and matching ceramic finial. Finish may vary.

Sultry, wine-colored glass is hand-blown to form this bottle-vase lamp. The iridescent, deep lavender hue casts a natural allure that captivates the senses. It rests on a round base with a warm, antique brass finish. The combination of sleek design, rich tones and modern sensibilities make this an impactful piece. Topped with a tapered, beige linen barrel shade with ivory cotton lining and acrylic ball finial. Metallic finish may vary. Also available in gold (DC42001-387).

Flourishing with an organic leaf pattern, this lamp is a natural relic. Handcrafted in porcelain, its modern aesthetic is given a traditional twist—a celadon glaze that recalls ancient Han dynasty pottery. Up close, you’ll notice a slight crackle texture in the finish. Mounted on a round silver leaf base. Topped with a drum shade in ivory cotton with ivory cotton lining and matching ceramic finial. Finish may vary.

The beauty of handcrafted ceramic joins forces with modern design to create this classical table lamp. The muted, shadow blue reactive glaze accentuates the ribbed and button details, as well as adds even more character to its unique shape. Topped with a tapered, ivory linen drum shade with navy piping detail, ivory cotton lining and matching ceramic finial. Glaze finish may vary.

The classic teardrop gets an extraordinary update in this table lamp. It’s made by expert glassblowers using a coarsely seeded technique, and then they add stems of glass to create the rippling, rib textures on the exterior The deep, aqua blue tones are accented with bronze-toned metallic flakes, so the lamp shimmers when it’s on. Topped with a drum shade in light tan silk with light gray cotton lining and an acrylic ball finial. Finish may vary.

Bright color and gilt colorblocking make this lamp modern and charming. Its unique silhouette is handcrafted in porcelain with a glossy glaze. This table lamp makes a vibrant addition with tons of character. Topped with a tapered barrel linen shade in ivory with ivory cotton lining and matching icy blue ceramic knob finial.

We've taken a classic form and infused it with inviting texture and color on the Kiki Lamp. Ribbed glass cascades down the piece, softening as the color fades to reveal an ombre smoke effect. The clear acrylic base adds contemporary flair to the design. Topped with a sheer, white microfiber drum shade. Also available in ombre boysenberry glass (17404-159). Finish may vary.

The Josef Lamp brings the outside in with its organic form and antiqued finish. Cast aluminum is another reference to the natural world, with every impression mirroring the markings on bark or stone. The tone and texture will stand out. Topped with a sheer, light silver gray microfiber shade. Finish may vary.

This slender oblong lamp is a bright and refreshing light, full of character and color. The base is made from hand-blown glass, which is finished in a variety of blue hues and oxidized bronze metallics to create its vibrant look. To the touch, you’ll notice even more textured details. Mounted on a round acrylic base. Topped with a drum shade in cloud beige linen with ivory cotton lining and an acrylic ball finial. Finish may vary.

Cool, calming blue radiates through this table lamp, swirling and flowing within the hand-blown glass. Subtle textures from its handcrafted design are prevalent, especially when the lamp is switched on. Its form is classic and refined, the bottle base embellished with sleek ribbed styling. Fitted with a textured, ivory linen barrel shade and acrylic ball finial. Glass tones may vary.

Cool, calming blue radiates through this table lamp, swirling and flowing within the hand-blown glass. Subtle textures from its handcrafted design are prevalent, especially when the lamp is switched on. Its form is classic and refined, the bottle base embellished with a brushed nickel top. Fitted with a white linen barrel shade trimmed in a one-inch flat hem and brushed nickel finial. Glass tones may vary.
Brutalist themes have been paired down on this antiqued aluminum table lamp. We intentionally left one of the figures exposed, topping the design with a narrow, white linen drum shade.

A vision of decadence, the Kacee Lamp is over the top in all the best ways. From the bulbous body made from frosted smoke glass to the antique brass base and oversized shade, rich details prevail. Topped with a black microfiber drum shade with a white cotton interior.

Alternating gold and gunmetal finishes are enhanced by linear grooves, creating natural dimension on this porcelain design. Topped with an off-white linen drum shade and matching ceramic finial. Finish may vary.

Decked in drama, the Khaled Lamp features a dark gunmetal glaze on its ceramic form. The gold band in the center of the piece accentuates the tapered edges. Topped with an ivory microfiber square shade and matching ceramic finial. Finish may vary.

Traditional form with an atypical finish. The Gerlich Lamp is the composite of three separate segments of smoked crystal, a cylinder entrenched between two champagne crystal discs. Connecting the segments is an antique brass rod, that also acts as a contrast to the smoked glass, as well as two champagne crystal disc separators. Topped in an ash microfiber shade with trim and matching smoked crystal finial.

With its smoked crystal base and pale brass neck, the Gemma Lamp beautifully toes the line between moody and glamorous. Beyond its contrast in materials, the seemingly randomness of the crystal's diamond-like facets are a stark contrast to the neck's classically chic pale brass finish. Topped with a cloud gray microfiber shade and matching pale brass finial.

A more contemporary take on the Art Deco-inspired Dustin Lamp. The Jorge Lamp's fossil grey finished concrete body is broken up into two larger sections by a smaller, cinched segment in the middle. Topped with a white linen drum shade.

Pascal is a totally unique table lamp that will draw attention and admiration from all sides. Antique brass in combination with smoked glass discs add layers of interest in any room. Redesigned with an ivory microfiber, round drum shade with matching cotton lining for a more contemporary look.

A cleaner, simpler take on the mixed materials trend, the Norman Lamp has a polished nickel-finished steel rod encased in a clear glass tube. The matching finial and ash microfiber drum shade with white microfiber lining complete the new contemporary classic.

The Ferris Lamp and its combination of smoked and champagne colored crystal instantly captivate by appealing to our natural curiosity. The transparent finish creates reflections and shadow play. The clean theme is continued throughout with the rectangular, cloud gray microfiber shade which is lined in a white microfiber.

Sharp angles and etched ridges combine to create the multifaceted Foster Lamp. The smoked glass finish adds to the modern, dramatic tone set by the lamp's geometric form. Topped with a tapered, ash microfiber shade and lined with white microfiber.

The artisanal weave of our Elis Bench is refashioned as a table lamp, interlacing gray suede over a minimal solid brass frame. A combination of equestrian-inspired handwork and pure geometry, its juxtaposition of materials layer warmth and texture over modern polish. Topped with a rectangular ivory microfiber shade that is lined in gold foil.

The exquisite finishing on this fluted glass lamp is hand-applied to the exterior. It is first acid washed, then hand-applied with silver and purposefully disturbed, distressed and reapplied to create the random pattern. The tapered ash shade is lined in the same fabric. 3-way switch.

This irregular mouth blown smoke luster glass lamp is a great neutral option for monochromatic interiors. The lined putty microfiber shade with hand rolled edges blends perfectly with the glass color.

Clean. Sleek. Modern. This lamp is the epitome of industrial refinement, with a silhouette and edginess that’s characteristic of the era, updated with the clean lines and polished finish of more modern design. The brushed bronze finish makes the porcelain structure look metallic, especially with the hand-etched knurling in the bands that wrap around the neck. It is topped with a natural linen drum shade with an ivory cotton lining. Finish may vary.
Oval mercury glass table lamp features distressed silvery ripples. Topped with an ivory microfiber drum shade and clear acrylic sphere finial. 3-way switch. Finish may vary.

Box design iron table lamp features a reptile-like pattern in a natural iron finish with antique brass edges atop a black marble base. Topped with a white rectangular shaped shade and matching square shaped finial. 3-way switch.

Box design iron table lamp features a reptile-like pattern in a natural iron finish with antique brass edges atop a black marble base. Topped with a black rectangular shaped shade with dark silver sheer lining and matching square shaped finial. 3-way switch.

Undulating porcelain cylinder shape has been finished with a metallic gunmetal reactive glaze. The tall drum white linen shade is lined in white cotton and has a porcelain finial to match. Every piece features a hand applied glaze and may vary slightly.

Who knew that leather and metal could make such a sophisticated pairing? Brushed brass forms the structure, cognac leather wraps it, stitched together with an exposed hem to add a handsome finishing touch. Topped with a tapered, white linen barrel shade with a cotton lining and matching brass ball finial. Also comes in indigo leather (DC12013), as well as a floor lamp version in cognac leather (DC72014) and indigo leather (DC72015). Leather finish may vary.

Handwoven, rattan wicker is just as Caribbean in its style as it is sophisticated. The shade and base are both made of natural rattan; the shade features an exaggerated scallop edge while the base conceals a steel plate. The stem is crafted from stainless steel, finished in a warm antique brass that contrasts the whimsical silhouette. Two bulbs are set to a dimmer switch, so you can set the mood however you like.

The raw look of jute rope fully wraps the stem of this slender table lamp. Natural fibers give the design an organic edge and an incredible amount of texture you can see and feel. It’s mounted in a plate of walnut finished wood, which helps conceal the clear cord for a streamlined look. Topped with a tapered drum, slip uno fitter shade in ivory linen with ivory cotton lining. Also available as a floor lamp (DC79000).

This smoky caramel lamp is simple and stunning. It is hand-blown with toned glass, then given a luster finish with a special glaze that makes it just a little opalescent. Watch it glow brilliantly in the light. The brass base is designed todesigned flow seamlessly with the glass, almost monochromatic in a vintage finish. Fitted with a drum shade in cloud beige linen with a one-inch flat bottom hem and white cotton lining. Topped with an acrylic ball finial. Luster finish may vary.

Soft, neutral and chic, this ombre lamp is simple and stunning. It is hand-blown with toned glass, then given a luster finish with a special glaze that makes it just a little opalescent. Watch it glow brilliantly in the light. The brass base is designed to flow seamlessly with the glass, almost monochromatic in a vintage finish. Topped with a tapered barrel shade in taupe microfiber with ivory cotton lining and an acrylic ball finial. Luster finish may vary.

Mystery and allure inundate this vase in its smoky tones and sultry design. Heavily seeded glass is hand-blown by glass artisans, meticulously crafted to get the richly seeded textures you see here. The base features a thickly weighted bottom and is topped with antique brass finish accents. Fitted with an oval barrel shade in sepia linen and ivory cotton lining with an acrylic ball finial. Seeded glass textures may vary.

This lamp features an old-world style that’s captivating. The unique silhouette is created from a turned wood base, which has a dark gray, antiqued finish that gives it added character and warmth. Topped with a drum shade in natural linen with a one-inch bottom trim and cotton lining; matching wood finial. Also available as a floor lamp (74200-831).

A touch of mid-century glamour is in the design of this shapely bottle lamp. The wide base and drum shade create balance with the slender neck, and the warm ivory glaze has subtle patterning you can only experience up close. Topped with a linen and raw hemp drum shade with cotton lining and acrylic ball finial. Glaze finish may vary.

Experimenting with reactive glazes is a true art form that can create unexpectedly striking finishes. The juxtaposition between metallic bronze and iridescent mint is magnetic on this ceramic lamp. Topped with a beige linen drum shade. Finish may vary.

There's a quiet allure to the Kali Lamp. From the tapered collar, to soft metallic highlights speckled throughout the amber glass, to the clear acrylic base, delicate details add sophisticated charm. Topped with an ivory microfiber drum shade with a taupe velvet trim. Also available in sapphire glass with metallic highlights (17408-416). Finish may vary.
Lloyd Lamp

The slight curve of the Tonto Lamp's tiered base creates a simple yet stunning silhouette. A teal reactive glaze crackle finish cascades down the ceramic and plays on the angular design of the form. A silver leaf wood base elevates this piece, as a platform and as an accent to the vibrant finish. Topped with a white linen drum shade with white cotton lining and a matching ceramic finial. Finish may vary.

We've updated our Rendon Lamp with a dusk lagoon reactive glaze finish that reveals a beautiful variance and reactive coloring that contrasts with its simple form. The organic pottery textures that make it outstanding are revealed when in use. Topped with a tapered cloud-beige linen shade with white cotton lining. Finish may vary.

The use and perhaps creation of earthenware pottery dates back to roughly 400 B.C. Continuing this tradition in new form with updated materials, we've crafted the Torrance Lamp in the same fashion. Ceramic has been spun to resemble the visual and textural aspects of clay pottery. A cerulean haze reactive glaze breaks over the textured form, leaving sand-colored reliefs peeking through. Topped with a light-beige linen drum shade and a matching ceramic finial. Finish may vary.

Elevate your space with the natural elegance that distinguishes the Tilford Lamp. A deep indigo leather is finely framed around an antique brass base, and is accented with a brushed brass belt for a refined touch to its rustic materials. A sophisticated lighting option for a study or an office. Features a brass pull-chain. Topped with a white linen drum shade with white cotton lining and a matching metal finial. Finish may vary.

This gently tapered wood slat column is finished in a washed tobacco stain that enhances the grain pattern. We like its effortless casual vibe that is perfect for so many homes. The off-white linen shade is lined in cotton.

The irregular angles and distinct lines of the multifaceted surface work together to create the Townsen Lamp. The icy morn finish lends a cool touch to its dramatic geometric form. Up close, you'll notice a slight crackle texture in the finish. Topped with an ivory microfiber drum shade with white cotton lining and matching ceramic finial. Finish may vary.

It’s a skilled glassblower that can make such beautiful cased-glass pieces like this teardrop lamp. It’s formed by fusing two layers of glass together and etching into the top layer to create the signature honeycomb pattern. The end product is a lamp rich in texture with a matte, slightly opaque finish. Topped with a tapered barrel linen shade in soft gray and an acrylic ball finial.
Hastings Lamp
Lilian Lamp
Kamal Lamp

The clear crystal Frye Lamp features an unexpected second material...brass sheet that has been cut to look like a cap of dripping vintage brass. A beautiful and striking example of unique pairings and mixed materials. Topped with a rectangular, ivory microfiber shade lined in white microfiber.

Classic with a twist. The Grace Lamp takes a hard angle on the transparency trend in design, literally. The lamp's body is a geometric masterpiece with sharp angles and multiple facets. Grace's clear crystal form is accentuated by the pale brass rod extending all the way from its base to its matching crystal finial. Topped with an ivory microfiber drum shade and contrasting velvet cord at top and bottom.

With a body made of clear crystal, the Eli Lamp draws inspiration from the works of renowned transparent designers Charles Hollis Jones and Joseph Eichler. The lamp's transparency is accented by its etched ridges and antique brass neck and base. Topped with a rectangular, ivory microfiber shade that is lined in the same.
A tall clear glass bottle embellished with hand applied 'dollops' of navy blue glass. The tall white drum shade is lined in cream cotton.

Featuring a simple, cylindrical glass body, the Dale Lamp takes transparency and simplicity to the next level. Lacking a base and a formal cap, the Dale uses negative space and transparency to actually add more to a space. Replacing the traditional cap is an antique brass claw-like top that gives way to the neck and ivory microfiber, drum shade with white microfiber lining.

Sculptural in form and unique by design, this lamp delivers a dash of drama with a hint of sophistication to a space. Glass is skillfully air-infused with a bronze finish to create a pitted metallic luster, which is illuminated by the lamplight. Establishes a brilliant visual texture for any room it occupies. Topped with an taupe sheer microfiber drum shade with dark silver microfiber lining. Finish may vary.

The Vega Lamp offers a modern yet minimalist approach to table top lighting. A slender oak column with a smoke gray finish has been fitted with an antique brass inlay that traces the middle, lending a modern and geometric quality to its rustic form. A great bedside or desktop lighting option for masculine and feminine spaces. Topped with a round off-white linen shade with off-white cotton lining and a matching wood finial. Finish may vary.

The Talman Lamp is a work of art created by Mother Nature herself. Natural teak wood is found and reclaimed to create this organic piece, which is accented by its natural deterioration. A hand-sanding technique has been applied to create a more rustic look. Iron base lends a contemporary touch to its natural form. Topped with a white linen drum shade with white cotton lining. Features a taupe cloth cord. Finish may vary.

As a nod to the urban spirit of Chicago, Frank designed a tattoo-inspired emblem that was hand-carved on this alluring table lamp. The perfect balance of graphic refinement, featuring a rich bronze ceramic form contrasted with an off-white silk drum shade. Each piece will be hand-done, lending a one-of-a-kind quality to the design.

It’s almost unreal how exaggerated the textures are in this natural wood table lamp. It’s made from pine wood, with its signature wide graining, which is torched to accentuate the organic textures even further. The column shaped carving is classical in style, but the rich tones in the wood make it warm and masculine. Its handsome aesthetic blends nicely in a modern space. Topped with a natural linen drum shade. Wood grain may vary.

There are times where simple beauty takes a little extra effort to achieve. This table lamp, though seemingly simple, is made by hand. From the blown glass form to the thistle finish with metallic bubble highlights, it's wrought with artisanal intention. The interesting texture is created by adding a layer to the glass that spreads and creates a dewy, speckled design. It is topped with a tapered ivory microfiber shade. Finish may vary.

The table version of our Malin Floor Lamp, this smaller take is just as sleek and simple as its predecessor. The steel frame is given warmth with a heritage brass finish. A matching finial creates the illusion of the shade being suspended within the design, and the disk base is fitted with clear glass that offers an airy quality. A small footprint lighting solution for any space. Features a brass pull-chain.

Slender in form, this lamp blends the aesthetics of rich wood and warm brass to create stylish elegance. The hourglass base is finished in a dark walnut and is accented with brass-finished details for a look that is polished and sleek, bringing a rich sophistication to a space. Its narrow footprint makes it ideal for a desk or buffet. It is topped with a tapered, off-white linen shade with matching cotton lining. Wood grain may vary.

The artisanal weave of our Elis Bench is refashioned as a table lamp, interlacing white leather over a minimal rose gold frame. A combination of equestrian-inspired handwork and pure geometry, its juxtaposition of materials layer warmth and texture over modern polish. Topped with a lined rectangular ivory microfiber shade.

Built for the great outdoors, this versatile lantern pairs the resilience of industrial style with a modern aesthetic. The steel frame is finished in an aged brass, so it exudes a debonair attitude, but the clean lines and simple construction allow it to blend in with any surrounding. The top is fitted with a handle accent, recalling a traditional lantern function, and the bulb is concealed in an opal glass sleeve, casting warm light all around. Also available in aged iron (49202).

In this simple, charming table lamp, we find an interplay of shapes that establishes a design that is fun, but still with a level of elegance. This elegance comes from the materials used; steel finished in antique brass forms the open arch, the most characteristic part of this piece; a foundation of white marble elevates the look and also adds a touch of organic texture. It is topped with an off-white linen rectangular shade with a white cotton lining. Marble may vary.

Just like the sands of time, this table lamp has desert-inspired hues and moody overtones. The ceramic bottle base is first finished in a bronze and rose glaze that naturally react with each other and drip to form different tonal layers Once the bronze metallic glaze is added, even more reactive effects are created, so the overall piece ends up with layers upon layers of interesting details. It is topped with an off-white linen drum shade with white cotton lining. Finish may vary.

The unique shapes in this aluminum lamp have a slight Brancusi-inspired aesthetic: rounded, curvy and very modern. Almost sculptural in form, it functions as more than merely a light, but also an art piece. It exudes elegance with a hand-applied gold-leaf finish and white marble base. It is topped with an off-white cotton rectangular shade with matching lining. Finish may vary.

Iridescent, gold-colored glass is hand-blown to form this bottle-vase lamp. The speckled luster finish casts a natural allure that captivates the senses. It rests on a round base with a warm, antique brass finish. The combination of sleek design, rich tones and modern sensibilities make this an impactful piece. Topped with a tapered, beige linen barrel shade with ivory cotton lining and acrylic ball finial. Metallic finish may vary.

Sleek, slender, svelte; this handsome stainless steel table lamp brings light and looks to a space. A tapered stem features an antique brass finish and five tiers of celestial blue crystal disks. The design is fantastically modern and the mixing of crystal and stainless steel is utterly unique. Topped with a microfiber drum shade in ivory with cotton lining and a matching antique brass finished finial.

Sculptural in form, this lamp blends the beauty of wood, brass and marble to create stylish elegance. The tapered wood base is finished in walnut and is fitted with a brilliantly gilt eyelet design, almost flowing through the shade to the matching finial. Mounted to a square plaque of natural white marble. Topped with a rounded rectangular linen shade in ivory with ivory cotton lining and an antique brass keyhole finial. Marble tones and grain may vary.

Cool and collected, the Locklan Lamp features vintage references with modern appeal. The mix of antique brass, bronze and white marble is surprisingly streamlined given the delicate shape. The taupe cloth cord adds a chic touch. Also available in vintage silver (49146). Marble may vary.

Elegance in true form, Kaylan walks the line between old and new. The seedy luster glass has an iridescent smokey hue that feels other-worldly. Topped with an off-white linen empire shade. Finish may vary.

This intricate table lamp is truly a work of art! The delicate antique brass twigs juxtaposed with the clear crystal base create a beautiful disposition that is anything but rustic. Paired with a black microfiber drum shade lined with gold foil and topped with a matching brass twig finial.

Champagne crystal and gemstone-like angles create a prismatic effect on this petite lamp. The crystal prisms will catch the soft light dance within the piece, enhancing all the beautiful edges. The lustrous crystal is mounted to a pale-brass finished steel stem and base. Topped with an oval, white linen shade with white cotton lining and matching crystal finial.

The sculptural form of this gold leaf lamp is full of life. It's arresting features will pair well with a minimalist side table or console. Topped with a white, linen oval drum shade and matching gold leafed finial. Also available in natural iron (43001-161). Gold leaf may vary.

A white marble base takes centerstage in this design, a heavier, more dramatic take on the Gawlik Desk Lamp. The Hargis version features a much more striking and prominent contrast between the pale brass-finished steel cylinder housing the bulb and the geometric marble base. Marble may vary.

The Harley Lamp takes the same mid-century inspiration found in the Dallas Chandelier's Sputnik-like form and makes it much more personable. Harley features three pale brass-finished steel arms extended from its white marble base. Each extension is topped with a seedy glass sphere housing an individual bulb. Marble may vary.

Pillow shaped amber crystal blocks are stacked to form a light-refracting elegant column lamp. Antique steel base finished in antique brass anchors the chic, modern look. A lined ivory oval drum shade made of microfiber completes this sophisticated design.

The Norman Lamp is a classic - perfect for so many of your design projects. The antique brass finish contrasts with the clear glass to create a clean and simple form. Topped in an ivory microfiber drum shade with white microfiber lining and matching finial.

Sculptural form and luxe materials combine in this sinuous table lamp. A single, solid twist of antique brass finished steel sits on a crystal square base. Beautiful from every angle. The ivory microfiber oval drum shade is lined in cotton and trimmed with a 1.5" flat band at bottom.
This wedge shaped porcelain table lamp features a textured surface with gilt horizontal striations. Topped with a rectangular taupe sheer shade with dark silver sheer lining and a matching finial.

If you watch The Good Wife you might recognize this lamp, set on an entry table under the firm's sign. The clean lines and double sockets make this antique brass lamp appropriate for night stands, desks, side tables or buffets.

A relative of the Ferris, the Foley Lamp is another take on the transparency trend. The Foley's colorless champagne crystal helps it play nicely with any other finish and color. The barely-there crystal discs are accented by the antique brass pipe and ivory microfiber drum shade, lined in the same.

A study in optics takes place with our Willard Lamp. Clear glass forms are mouth-blown into a stacked structure around a brass base and are accented with delicate antique brass belts. When in use, the textured details are enhanced. Sit it near a window, and the textured glass works well to refract natural light. A perfect lighting solution for classic and contemporary settings. Topped with an off-white linen drum shade with off-white cotton lining and an acrylic sphere finial.

The tapered rectangular shape lends itself to spaces that demand a smaller footprint on the surface…night stands, buffets, credenzas. The snakeskin pattern on the surface is finished in gray metallic. Sheer silver shade with a lining to match. 3 way switch.

Ombre is an important trend this season, and we especially like how this mouth blown glass lamp base fades from clear to dark gray. Note the detail of the rolled bottom edge, and that the cord exits from the socket. The ash microfiber shade reinforces the subtle color variation.
Porcelain table lamp features silver snakeskin-like etched mesh pattern and a white shade with metallic silver shimmer lining. 3-way switch.
Sabine Lamp

The tapered oblong shape of this lamp is full of character and style. The base is formed from cast aluminum, which is finished in antique brass to create its vibrant iridescent luster. Its ribbed form delivers textured details that are accentuated when lit. Mounted on a clear acrylic base that produces a floating effect. Topped with a tapered cloud-beige linen shade with off-white cotton lining. Finish may vary.

The Tipton Lamp defines luxe lighting. Snow marble shades grace the two-light fixture that is suspended by a slender antique brass steel frame and mounted on a clear crystal base. The utilitarian profile is adjustable, so you can direct the flow of light with a simple pivot. An opulent lighting solution for modern spaces. Finish may vary.

The table version of our Malin Floor Lamp, this smaller take is just as sleek and simple as its predecessor. The ultra-minimalist design of the steel frame is given warmth with an antique brass finish. A matching finial creates the illusion of the shade being suspended within the design, and the disk base is fitted with clear glass that offers an airy quality. A small footprint lighting solution for any space. Features a brass pull-chain.

The elements of fine lighting are procured in this one piece. A simple polished brass form takes the stage of a polished white beveled marble base. The candlestick silhouette features small textured details that recall old-world French design. A great addition to traditional settings. Topped with an ash microfiber drum shade and a matching metal finial. Marble may vary.

The unconventionality of this lamp's shape delves into the depths of sculptural design. The slightly tapered oblong frame is constructed from hammered iron and features brass spheres that playfully accent the edge. The entire form is finished in antique brass that delivers a luminescent shine which is heightened when in use. Topped with an off-white linen drum shade with off-white cotton lining and a matching metal finial. Finish may vary.

A classic lamp base form gets a daringly dynamic update with our Wheeler Lamp. It is made of hand-hammered brass and features a brass sheaf-like design that contours around the frame. The antique brass finish works to soften and accentuate the form's rich textures, especially when lit by the lamp's warm glow. An illuminating anchor for an entryway console or side table. Topped with a tapered off-white linen shade with white cotton lining and a matching metal finial. Finish may vary.

The leaf-like motif and sculptural form of our this lamp lends a natural and artistic element to a space. The expressive aesthetic of this piece is thanks to a cast aluminum construction with an antique brass finish that is gracefully exhibited on a polished white marble base, which has been beveled around the edges for a hint of added texture. Topped with a rectangle off-white linen shade with white cotton lining and topped with a matching metal finial. Finish may vary.

Art's true form is realized with the impeccable craftsmanship of this lamp. Clear glass is skillfully blown into the spaghetti-like formation that surrounds an antique brass steel base. The free-form design creates a unique dimensional characteristic that adds depth, while delivering a sculptural quality to a space. Topped with an oval off-white linen shade with off-white cotton lining and a matching metal finial. Finish may vary.

A piece that is voluptuous and modern, this lamp is ideal for a space that needs brassy boldness and elegance. Illuminate a photograph or line drawing with this architectural steel table easel in antique brass. Adjustable and well proportioned on a white marble base, it’s the missing piece in any room. Marble may vary.

Unique and intriguing in form, this modern marvel of a lamp is rich with details. Classic, ceramic textures and a warm, natural finish make for fine details in this table lamp. Elegance in true form, the Sarah Lamp is a cross between styles old and new. The jade, seedy luster glass has an iridescent finish that feels retro, yet modern. It is topped with a beautifully embroidered drum linen shade that gives the final look an almost bohemian air. Finish may vary.

This diminutive bottle lamp is a bright and refreshing light, full of character and color. Remarkably life-like and wonderfully crafted, this brass lamp is unique and stunning, ripe with natural inspiration. Bold in its modern form and style, this vibrant lamp takes the limelight. The sleek, angular frame is finished in a citrusy yellow glaze for a bright punch of color. This slender teardrop lamp is a bright and refreshing light, full of character and color. If you think this table lamp is attractive without light, just turn on the switch and watch it become a work of art. Like a Grecian goddess, this lamp has beauty and grace that make it muse-worthy. This slender bottle lamp is a bright and refreshing light, full of character and color. This elegant porcelain form features contrasting design elements. The ceramic Hazle Lamp is a near-monochromatic Dark Matter beauty. Visual art becomes functional with this porcelain table lamp. The cylindrical ceramic Keelan Lamp is finished in a misty jade reactive glaze to create the perfect combination of warm pastels and soft curves. Keelan helps foster a light and airy vibe no matter its placement. Topped with a light grey cotton drum shade. Finish may vary.

Old-world pots, similar in shape to the base of this lamp, were used throughout the ancient world, crafted by artists who still use techniques just like the originals. Topped with a linen and raw hemp drum shade with cotton lining and acrylic ball finial. Glaze finish may vary.

The Whitcomb Lamp naturally elevates traditional design with a wicker rattan weave. A dark gray finish lends a moody touch to the textured base and brass accents. With its lovely grainy textures and incredible malleability, we’re falling in love with terracotta—even as a material for our lamp bases. Made by molding and detailing terracotta by hand, this lamp is rich in textures and character. With its lovely grainy textures and incredible malleability, we’re falling in love with terracotta—even as a material for our lamp bases. Visually intriguing in tone and depth, the Pompeii Lamp is crafted from ceramic, the wide, ovular shape is formed with a delineating ridge that separates the dark and light spaces. What a wonderful geological find this lamp is. The faux concrete base looks just like the real thing, but it’s been crafted to be lighter and more gentle on table tops. Topped with a slip uno fitter oval shade in white linen with ivory cotton lining. Equipped with a full range dimmer switch. Finish may vary.

This rich stone lamp evokes artisan aesthetics. The visible grainy texture in the surface is from sand that's incorporated into the clay before it's molded. Champagne crystal and sharp angles create a prismatic effect on this petite lamp. The crystal prisms will catch the soft light dance within the piece, enhancing all the beautiful edges. It takes excellence and expert knowledge in glassblowing to create patterned designs such as this. We've taken a classic form and infused it with inviting texture and color on the Kiki Lamp. Ribbed glass cascades down the piece, softening as the color fades to reveal an ombre boysenberry effect. Justine Lamp

Mid-century in form, but with a softer side, this is a blushing beauty—just turn on the switch and watch it shine. Bright color and gilt colorblocking make this lamp modern and charming. Its unique silhouette and ribbed design is handcrafted in lilac porcelain with a glossy glaze. Lorraine's beauty is the understated kind that reveals itself over time. The hand-blown silhouette features a soft thistle finish with metallic bubble highlights. Topped with a sheer, beige microfiber empire shade and French-wired with a taupe cloth cord. Finish may vary.

The traditional base is first crafted from terracotta by one artist, then a second craftsman applies a rich, salmon colored finish through an ancient practice that must be done by hand to create the unique textures. Crafted with a quiet reverance, master artisans have applied delicate vellum to this streamlined lamp form. Let this lamp create a natural narrative while offering an organic ambience to your desktop or entryway console. The subtle grooved surface pattern on this porcelain table lamp adds a dimensionality that is further enhanced when the hand applied blue wash glaze is applied over the ivory crackle finish. Curvy bottle shaped porcelain table lamp in a glossy, textured, stained ivory crackle finish with matching sphere finial. Topped with tall putty colored fabric shade with light gray cotton lining. 3-way switch.

Each contemporary lamp uses the centuries-old engobe technique. In this process, the greige and denim base accents are applied before the satin papyrus porcelain is kiln-fired. Then, artists take each one and add black stroke details, which end up a shade of indigo once dried. The base is crafted from wood and finished silver leaf, elevating the look and adding a hint of shine. Topped with a tapered, taupe sheer microfiber shade with an ivory cotton lining. Handmade details and finish may vary.

Delicate tones of soft pink and ivory envelope this porcelain crafted table lamp. Adding to this unique petal ombre finish is a subtle crackle-glaze texture that covers the top and bottom layers. It is topped with a smoke petal cotton drum shade with contrasting white lining,

The beauty of handcrafted ceramic joins forces with modern design to create this serene table lamp. With a deep visual aesthetic, the eye-catching architectural shape of this lamp commands a room. A sui generis way to offer depth and dimension to a space while adding the right amount of light. Thick irregular horn discs make up the body of this very authentic looking lamp that can hold its own next to the real thing. A great choice for a desk, credenza or buffet. The lined euro taper cotton shade highlights the tan coloration in the horn. Finish may vary.

A modern twist on a conventional shape, the Verde Lamp showcases a simple yet stunning silhouette that is reminiscent of traditional Chinese ginger jars. The intriguing form of this tower-esque lamp is rich with details and color. Destined to be a porcelain classic, or at least everyone’s new favorite. The design is further enhanced by the ivory crackle finish and the tall ivory drum shade with 3 inch flat-band trim on the bottom only.

Fringe is a fashion favorite, and Laura Kirar has taken it into the home. This ivory "tassel" lamp has an ivory microfiber shade and is lined in ivory cotton. It also has a top diffuser. 3-way switch.
Double socket snow marble and brass table lamp features a pair of decorative brass pull chains and matching finial. Topped with a putty colored fabric shade with cream cotton lining and rolled edges.
This double urn shaped porcelain table lamp in an ivory aged crackle finish is topped with a putty drum shade featuring contrasting a darker trim band at the top and bottom. 3-way switch.

Boasting a peacock reactive glaze with a crackle finish, that beautifully breaks over porcelain, this unconventionally shaped table lamp becomes functional earthenware. Like the gathering of storm clouds, this lamp brings mystery and moxie. The fine art form of this ceramic lamp's column silhouette is as much of a showpiece as a functional fixture. Curate a space with functional luminary art. The blown art glass base features a silveria and frosted stripe finish that creates an iridescent luster, which is both elegant and engaging.
