Displayed on a clear crystal base for an extra element of elegance. Topped with an olive gray microfiber drum shade with dark silver lining and a matching metal finial. Finish may vary.

Industrial elegance takes shape with the geometric stylings of this reflective lamp. The octagonal shape is framed in dark natural iron and is faceted with beveled antique mirrors on all sides, delivering a significant reflective quality when its lit . Place near a window, and this piece works to break up natural light and scatter it around the room. Topped with gray morn linen drum shade with gray morn cotton lining and a matching metal finial. Finish may vary.

A traditional lamp base gets a modern makeover with a Pollock-esque swirl pattern. After the clear, mouth-blown glass is created, another layer of blue and brown colored glass is swirled onto the top, which is what creates the layered designs. Since you can see through the form, this piece has a lot of dimension and texture, visually and to the touch. Topped with an off-white linen drum shade with off-white cotton lining. Finish may vary.

We've updated our Edge Lamp with a smoke finish and amber glass dollops for a warmer take on the cool façade. The glass base of this lamp creates a moody stage for the hand-applied embellishments to be presented on. Topped with an oval olive gray microfiber shade with dark silver microfiber lining. Finish may vary.

The Washburn Lamp is both simple in form and classic in style. A dovetail gray ombre finish divides the glass and creates the appearance of white-capped waves breaking against the water. A great addition or update for coastal décors. Topped with a tapered off-white linen shade with off-white cotton lining. Finish may vary.

This simple two-tone ceramic base features both matte ivory and slate gray glaze finishes…think colorblocking. The two-tone finish and ivory microfiber drum shade create an understated and classic form. The smaller footprint makes it a good option for smaller tables and night stands. Finish may vary.

The unique play on geometrics and the unconventional design make this lamp is far from ordinary. An irregular bullseye pattern in black is a stark contrast to the ivory gloss that paints the ceramic and delivers a bold graphic statement to a space. Showcased on a square acrylic base that creates a floating effect and draws attention to its eccentric shape. Topped with an oval off-white linen shade with off-white cotton lining and a matching ceramic finial. Finish may vary.

A delicate take on abstract expressionism, this lamp demands attention in the space it occupies. The gourd-like ceramic base is finished in greige with a hand-splattered denim reactive glaze that glistens when in use. Raised on a gunmetal base that works to accent the neutral colors. Topped with an off-white linen drum shade with off-white cotton lining and a matching ceramic finial. Finish may vary.
Simple and elegant, the Carson is defined by a rectangular slab of snow marble atop a brass base. Topped with a rectangle ivory microfiber shade lined in cream cotton.
Collected driftwood is hand assembled and then painted white to create this unique table lamp. The square linen shade also has a top diffuser. 3-way switch.

Form meets function with this sophisticated yet playful piece.Crystal orbs with a light smoke finish are artfully arranged around pale brass steel, appearing as if they are floating. The presentation of the spheres works well to break up natural light, but looks especially stunning when illuminated by the soft glow of the lamp. Topped with an off-white microfiber drum shade with off-white cotton lining and a matching metal finial. Finish may vary.

Cylinder shaped glass table lamp features etching on the base detailed to look like textured linen and is topped with a white silk shade with reflective silver foil lining and sphere finial in brushed nickel finish. 3-way switch.

A towering example of the magnificence of crystal, this table lamp not only exudes a modern aesthetic, but also finds inspiration in an unlikely place. It takes its cue from the far-reaching peaks of a city skyscraper, urban in style, with a tapered, smoke crystal base that seems to reach all the way up to the matching crystal finial point. It is topped with a light, silver gray microfiber drum shade with white cotton lining.
Rectangular snow marble table lamp sits on an elevated vintage brass pedestal. Topped with a rectangular ivory shade with cream cotton lining.

Finely crafted in smooth porcelain, this lamp has polish and intrigue. The porcelain is first thrown by hand, and then detailed etchings are engraved to give it faceted texture. The final touch is the silver metallic glaze, an even finish that makes the carvings shimmer in the light. Topped with a tapered, white linen barrel shade with cotton lining and matching ceramic finial.

Sleek, slender, svelte; this handsome stainless steel table lamp brings light and looks to a space. A tapered stem features a dark, vintage silver finish and five tiers of black crystal disks. The design is fantastically modern and the mixing of crystal and stainless steel is utterly unique. Topped with a microfiber drum shade in black with cotton lining and a matching vintage silver finished finial.

Sculptural form and luxe materials combine in this sinuous lamp. A single, solid twist of dark, vintage silver finished steel sits on a clear crystal square base. The lined drum shade is made of ivory linen, trimmed with a 1”-inch flat band, and matching ball finial. Think of it as a floor sculpture that happens to also be a lamp. Pair it with the matching floor lamp (79985-724). Also comes in antique brass floor lamp (79986-386) and table lamp (49946-269).

With its dual steel and crystal structure, this table lamp is a modern play of geometric design intrigue. The base is finished in a dark vintage silver, which not only elevates its style, but also adds a uniquely sophisticated polish to the look. In contrast with the ultra-sleek metal, the design features alternating panels of opal swirl crystal that add a lovely texture. It is topped with a rectangular shade in ash gray microfiber. Finish may vary.

The Humphrie Lamp is tumbled industrial design personified. A multifaceted lesson in geometry, the soft silver finished Humphrie screams space-age sheen. The design is brought together with its rectangular off-white linen shade lined in matching cotton, and matching finial.

With its lovely grainy textures and incredible malleability, we’re falling in love with terracotta—even as a material for our lamp bases. The Rosie Lamp is unique in its heavy clay texture, strong angles, and the cloudy white drip glaze that is accented at the top. To accentuate all the details, potters finish the piece with a soft, frosted petal glaze that really pulls out its strong features. It is topped with a soft sand microfiber drum shade with white cotton lining. Finish may vary.

Bright color and gilt colorblocking make this lamp modern and charming. Its unique silhouette is handcrafted in ceramic with a glossy glaze. This table lamp makes a vibrant addition to a space and adds a warm light. Topped with a tapered barrel microfiber shade in white with reflective gold foil interior for added glow. Matching petal pink ceramic knob finial.

The marriage of industrial style and modern form comes together to create this handsome block lamp. Crafted from aluminum, it has a rich and dramatic distressed copper finish that gives it distinction and sophistication It is short in stature, which makes for a nice light for a desk. It is topped with a rectangular shade in putty microfiber and ivory cotton lining. Finish may vary.
This tapered glass table lamp in a silver and gold iridescent finish sits atop a round brass base. Topped with a khaki shade with beige leopard print lining. 3-way switch.

The latest and most petite relative in the Hanley family. The Hanley Mini Chandelier brings out the approachable, functional side of the popular starburst design. Features eight lights and clear fluted glass rods, the perfect complement to the polished nickel-finished steel sphere. Perfect as an arresting statement piece in close quarters, or even as multiples. Additional pipe available (PIPE-100). Also available in antique brass (89430). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

The popular Wahlburg Chandelier (89026) levels up, literally, with the large-scale Wahlburg Two-Tiered Chandelier. The chandelier features 16 stationary lights, all inside opal glass globes to complement the chandelier's vintage silver finish. Perfect to provide plenty of wattage over a table in a grand dining room. Additional pipe available (PIPE-126). Also available in antique brass (89434). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Thirteen opal glass spheres descend effortlessly from a vintage silver canopy, eliciting a weightlessness as if they were floating through the air. Perfect for a staircase or other vertical space that needs drama and light. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

In a ring of brilliant design, this chandelier sheds light on a whole new level of beauty. Handcrafted iron posts slope dramatically outward in a round presentation to hold 12 antique brass perforated cups. The natural iron finish gives the chandelier an almost medieval feel, as well as all the thoughtful, handcrafted details prevalent throughout the piece. Additional pipe available (PIPE-198). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Cascading flat iron rods finished in antique brass form the cylindrical base of this graphic chandelier. Six lights descend in a stair step fashion each topped with an ivory microfiber shade. Also available in vintage silver (89048). Additional pipe available (PIPE-101).

This chandelier is modern in every way. In structure, it features two tiers of three lights, each encased in a hexagonal glass shade of frosted glass. Its linear design is edgy and updated, but the antique brass finished steel softens the look and adds a timeless elegance. The hexagon canopy mimics the light shades. Additional pipe available (PIPE-208). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Adding intrigue to simplistic design is an effortless feat in our Dante Chandelier. From the suspended pendant to overlapping black nickel bands across the side, every design feature is spot on, under this bold, almost-brutal umbrella. A frosted acrylic diffuser tones down the glow of five hidden lights. Additional chain available (CHN-145). Also available in small, vintage silver (89449) and large, antique brass (89702). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Whimsy and classic glamour all in one. Clear glass diamonds adorn the four-light, antique brass-finished wind chime design. The Kristen Chandelier is a close relative of earlier Arteriors favorites like the Tiffany and Eloise Chandeliers. Shown with clear tubular bulbs. Additional pipe available (PIPE-101). Also available in brushed nickel (89436). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Our mantra in creating this fixture's basket-inspired weave was a marriage of global craft and modern geometry. Hexagons combine into circular form, suspended from matching polished brass chain links as an essential part of its design. Think of this as jewelry for the home. Additional chain available (CHN-126). Shown with a 3

We took the ever-popular design of our Celeste Accent Table and updated it with a solid white marble top and base and a fixed-position black iron leg, to create this pub table version. The beveled edges of the marble top add depth to the slight veining that moves freely across the surface. Though larger in size, this table has a small footprint like its predecessor, making it a great piece for small space.

Five tiers of clear seedy glass plates come together to form the arresting three-light Larie Chandelier. The steel frame's antique brass finish sets a stylish and graceful tone, while the unique glass plates add a touch of curiosity, with varying finishes and no two being exactly alike. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Finish may vary.

Crafted entirely from different forms of rattan, this is a cocktail table that’s both resilient and stylish. The reeds are formed from the top in a radial pattern in bent rattan, with a peel wrap that delineates each section to create the open design and quadrants. In staying true with the organic aesthetic, the materials are left in their natural state, raw and unfinished. Don’t let the delicate form trick you—it’s sturdy enough to hold books and trays for function or beauty.

The aged charm of a patinaed vintage nickel finish and hammered iron give this table a unique elegance. It takes extra care to create each table, but the result is a beautifully crafted piece that exudes artistic charm. Also available in large cocktail table in burnt brass (2038). Vintage nickel finish may vary.

A representation of modern sophistication, this multi-light electrolier defines a space. Varying sizes of seedy smoke glass globes embellish a sleek and slender steel frame that works to ground the slightly whimsical design. Small, clear crystal knobs contrast beautifully with the brown nickel finish and with the visual textures presented by the smoke finish that graces the glass. Glass will vary. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Additional pipe available (PIPE-103).

The smaller space with lower ceilings finally has its focal point with the Nessa Small Chandelier, a more modest take on the larger Nessa Chandelier (89009). The antique brass oval frame is adorned with clear fluted glass rods, all individually attached, adding to the design's glam quotient. Shown with small clear tubular bulbs. Additional pipe available (PIPE-101). Also available in polished nickel (89429). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

The Kelsie Cocktail Table is the epitome of quintessential design and shape, as round black marble rests atop a three-legged brushed natural iron base. Inspired by the unique veining that moves fluidly on the table's top between shades of black, gray and white, we've deemed this blend 'Galaxy Marble'. For a full classic and subtly cosmic effect, gather with the matching side table (6905) and accent table (6906). Also available in white marble. Finish and marble may vary.

Entertainers will love the versatility of this modular design. The dual geometric tables can be separated to reveal two pieces that can be moved throughout a space or styled side-by-side—the possibilities are endless. They are crafted from iron that’s seamlessly welded together and finished in a classic, neutral vintage silver. Also comes in an antique brass finish (4520).

Imagine a functional table with both elevated looks and unique charm. Wonderfully playful curves dance around the entire structure of this cocktail table, softening its skilled metal craftsmanship. Look closely and discover a rich bronze finish, with striking elements of the handmade-such sophistication! Also available in a warm, antique brass finish (2100).

Clear glass plates with a slightly-scalloped edge hover beautifully down this round chandelier. It’s the single-tier version in our collection of Eloise lighting collection. The antique brass framework peaks through the cloudy glass, giving the piece a sense of nostalgia. Additional pipe available (PIPE-112). Also available in a three tier (89451) and five tier (89701) version.

Narrow wood slats wrap up the sides of this gently curved round cocktail table. The top is solid wood and the entire table is finished in a new tobacco wash we developed specifically for this season. Combine with the Kai Bookshelf (4306) for a cohesive look.

Geometric angles, super sleek lines and a deep finish make this a standout cocktail table. The light catches angled planes to reveal a tapered design from outside in, with asymmetrical legs that lend a contemporary edge. The blackened iron finish, almost mesmerizing, is a chemical reaction finish that not only gives it a moody side, but also keeps the table from corrosion. This is a statement piece for any space. Pairs perfectly with our Mckinley Console Table (2240).

Whether viewed straight on or from a different perspective, the Shelby Cocktail Table plays with negative space to deliver a unique silhouette that wows from any angle. As if the form wasn't enough, designer Frank Ponterio upped the ante with bespoke detailing and expert craftsmanship. The frame is covered in rich black leather that has been embossed to achieve a shagreen effect. Hand-hammered brass wraps the edges along with a decorative post for added flair. Leather may vary.

A contemporary style with classic proportion and scale, the Lawson Cocktail Table is a perennial favorite with universal appeal. Bullnose edges and a burnished gold leaf sabots highlight the soft ebony stained oak grain. Nylon nail-in glides will protect exposed floors.

We love the yin and yang on this transitional cocktail table. Hand-forged black iron legs are delicately tapered creating the perfect base for the chunky white marble top. Also available as a side table (4391). Marble may vary.

Crafted from solid oak, this coffee table features a captivating cathedral pattern on the ebony stained table top. Beveled edges make the surface appear thinner, almost floating above the natural iron pedestal. Layer with the smaller version in a contrasting smoke stained finish (4548). Finish may vary.
This iron cocktail table features an antique bronze finish and repousse ringed detail. Coordinates with Clint End Table #2034.

Varying elements make the Higgens Cocktail Table a fast favorite. Indentions on the natural iron frame and divets on the antique brass clad tray lend a natural quality to this transitional design. The tray isn't welded to the frame. Finish and clad may vary.

Exquisitely crafted, the Alek Cocktail Table by Frank Ponterio is sure to draw admirers. Faux quill detailing lends an heirloom quality to the black oak frame, versatile enough to sit in traditional or contemporary settings alike. A bamboo-like motif dances along the edges, hand-carved by master artisans with the utmost care. Finish may vary.

Cylindrical with a twist, the Herschel Cocktail Table is an iron, bronze-finished beauty that instantly adds weight and artisanal detail to any space. The hammered finish brings unexpectedness to the table's modified hourglass form. Matching side table (2825) and lamp (42069-622) also available.
White marble and burnt wax give a modern update to this classic color combination. The oversized iron legs have a slight hammered effect. Marble may vary.

Artisan technique takes hold in the compelling design of our Daryl Side Table's counterpart. The solid wood top has been carved with a rhythmic design then clad in antique brass sheet. A slim and short tapered aluminum base is finished in antique bronze and works to complement the top with a striking contrast in color and materials. Clad finish may vary.
This white marble and black iron cocktail table has a graphic quality with the larger top and narrow bottom. Finish and marble may vary. Also available as a side table (6581).

This iron drum shape has been finished in antique brass with a bronze plinth to give it an artisanal effect that will only get better with time. Finish may vary. Also available as an end table (2860).

An extension of our Nikita Collection, this modern piece solves a variety of design issues and looks brilliant in almost any space. The rectangular iron frame of this cocktail table is entirely finished with gold leaf and surrounds a geometric overlay of intersecting circles and clear glass. There's no way you can have a bad day with this shiny table around. A great focal point for a living room or den. Gold leaf may vary.

The unity of true craftsmanship and utility is a match made in heaven. This cocktail table is just that, with a feature you wouldn’t expect. It’s built from iron, which has been expertly hammered and antiqued to give it an texture and color. Then, it’s topped with a solid plate of mirrored glass that features a bold bohemian pattern. Here’s the surprise: the quadrants below fit our wedge ottomans (DC2002), so you can tuck some extra seating. Antiqued mirror finish and pattern may vary.

Imagine a functional table with both elevated looks and unique charm. Wonderfully playful curves dance around the entire structure of this cocktail table, softening its skilled metal craftsmanship. Look closely and discover a warm antique brass finish, with striking elements of the handmade-such sophistication! Also available in a rich, bronze finish (2101).

This exquisite cocktail table is like bringing the brilliance of the sun into a space. Honed hexagonal white marble is inlaid with 30 slices of polished brass, forming a shining sunburst design that is elegant and oh-so-sophisticated. It’s truly a feat of daring craftsmanship. The six-leg base is smithed from iron and finished in an antique brass finish, with a silhouette that has a slightly Moroccan feel. Also available as an end table (6880). Marble tones may vary.

This box frame coffee table is a blank slate, its glass surface the perfect platform for showcasing your most coveted collectibles. The thick glass table top is capped with iron sleeves finished in a silky antique brass.

Geometric shapes and defined lines make this a notable console table. A rich brindle finish graces the eucalyptus veneer that forms the sizable surface of this piece. The large antique brass ring that surrounds the bottom of the wide pedestal base lifts the deep color and delivers a refined element to its wooden façade. Versatile in style and function, the Violi Console Table works in a variety of settings.

We love the juxtaposition of the industrial natural iron cocktail table base with the elegant and decorative kidney shaped top. The unique top is made of solid wood that has been scored, then clad in brass sheet and antiqued to enhance the carved pattern. This shape is ideal to use with a sectional or small settee. This brass surface will patina over time.
Iron coffee table with slender vertical supports in an antique brass finish with antiqued mirror inlay top.

This voluminous drum cocktail table is made of iron then finished in burnt brass, a golden finish a bit lighter than antique brass. We love the artisan look and feel. Coordinates with side table #2418.
Entertainers will love the versatility of this antique brass design. The iron cocktail table can be separated to reveal two pieces that can be moved throughout a space or styled side-by-side.

Rattan is just as organic in its style as it is sophisticated. The large sprawling surface of the large top features a hand-applied woven herringbone pattern that highlights the precise execution needed to excel in rattan craftsmanship. Crafted entirely from natural materials, thick and sturdy rattan poles form an x-shaped base that supports the quadrate frame of this stately piece, kept completely intact by thinner pieces of wrapped rattan. Rattan may vary.
Scalloped iron stacks to form a scale patterned base with gold leaf detailing for this cocktail table. The round black top is rough hewn marble.
This iron cocktail table features a vintage nickel finish and repouss? ringed detail on the top surface. Also available in large (4413) and side table (4503). Finish may vary.

Refined and rustic elements are showcased through the mixture of materials that compose this stately cocktail table. A solid oak frame in an umber finish is accented with a simple antique brass inlay that delivers a refined element to its rustic form. Sharply angled legs lend a dramatic juxtaposition to the sprawling rectangular top. This well-formed piece delivers a polished aesthetic to a living or dining room.

The aged charm of a patinaed bronze finish and hammered iron give this table a unique beauty. Over 20 rings are worked into the tabletop using a repoussé and chasing method, where the line detail is crafted with the use of embossing and reverse relief. The result is smooth, channeled, low-relief design that works perfectly for functional use. Also available in large cocktail table (4007) and side table (2034). Bronze finish may vary

Modern elegance and industrial style blend seamlessly in this table. In the base, you’ll find the stainless steel structure of industrial craftsmanship, but with a sleek and glam brushed nickel finish. The top also holds this balance in dichotomy; handmade and hand-applied fossil gray concrete is formed into tiles that are laid in a mosaic pattern. This design is adventitious, lending a bit of a bohemian flair and allowing each table to be just a little unique from one to the other.

This box frame coffee table is a blank slate. Its large square surface is the perfect platform for showcasing your most coveted collectibles or living room essentials. Iron sleeves finished in bronze cap a thick, clear glass top that creates contrast and delivers an airy effect that helps open up a space. The classic style and design of this coffee table makes it a perfect fit for any décor.
This iron cocktail table features a vintage nickel finish and repoussé ringed detail on the top surface. Also available in small (4414), side table (4503), and bronze (4007). Finish may vary.

Celerie Kemble’s love of natural design shines through in this intricately crafted console. Mango wood is cut and carved by hand to create this rich design on all four sides. Then, the entire piece is finished in a handsome heritage gray, just enough to keep some of the natural wood details visible. Also available as a cocktail table (DC2004).

We love the juxtaposition of the industrial iron base with the elegant and decorative top made of solid wood that has been scored and then clad in brass sheet, which we then antique. This brass surface will patina over time.

Reflective and ever-so intriguing, this square coffee table is crafted from distressed mirror tiles, artfully inlaid within an iron trim to form a patchwork design. Set in a wood base and supported by four bronze-finished pillar legs, its simplicity is what gives it such sophistication. Pair it with the matching Luxembourg Mirror (6479) to bring in even more light and style. Natural iron finish may vary.
Round iron cocktail table of darkened silver with brass accents finish.

The Dallas and Karrington Chandeliers have become Arteriors icons with their unique takes on the Sputnik design. Now, the Linkka Chandelier offers perhaps the most distinct version of the caviar-like trend. Six bulbs, each with opal glass shades are spread across three different tiers, yielding an unexpected vertical and slim silhouette. Finished in heritage brass. Additional pipe available (PIPE-172). Also available in vintage silver (89460). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Rustic meets classic with this well-defined chandelier. Rough and crude iron with refined flutes shape this large circular frame that is suspended by a purposely antique brass chain that helps to play up the industrial feel. Makes quite the statement when hung over a dining table or suspended in a high ceilinged room. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Additional chain available (CHN-207).

Crafted from solid oak, this coffee table features a captivating cathedral pattern on the smoke stained table top. Beveled edges make the surface appear thinner, almost floating above the natural iron pedestal. Layer with the larger version in a contrasting ebony stained finish (4547). Finish may vary.

A large-scale, updated take on the popular Royalton design, now featuring 12 lights instead of four. Smoke glass rods lend a transitional feel to this modern, brown nickel-finished steel design. Shown with frosted globe bulbs. Additional pipe available (PIPE-103). Also available in soft silver with clear glass (89423). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

The popular Waldorf's spherical form gets turned on its head with the large-scale Waldorf Rectangular Chandelier. Brutalism and harsh glamour immediately come to mind with Waldorf's angular steel shards adorning its brass frame, finished in heritage brass. The sword-like spokes yield stunning shadow play with the chandelier's four lights. Shown with radio bulbs. Additional pipe available (PIPE-172). Also available in vintage silver (89459). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Three tiers of irregular symmetry and space-like wonder. The Karrington Large Chandelier is the next step in the evolution of the popular Karrington design, updated for large-scale spaces with three tiers and 18 lights, encased in smoke glass globes to compliment the chandelier's brown nickel finish. Shown with small clear tubular bulbs. Additional pipe available (PIPE-103). Also available in antique brass (89457). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

A striking agate top in blue hues takes center stage in this cocktail table design. The iron frame lends a bit of masculinity and contrast to the design. Besides using as a cocktail table consider next to an armless chair or chaise. Available in rose quartz #2734. Agate colorations vary.

An Arteriors icon gets an update. Mid-century inspiration meets small-scale design with this 12-light, brown nickel take on the Dallas Chandelier and its Sputnik form. Features 12 adjustable arms, each topped with a smoke glass globe, to allow for customized constellation creation. Shown with 2 tubular bulbs. Additional pipe available (PIPE-103). Also available in polished nickel (89455) and vintage brass (89456). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

An Arteriors icon gets an update. Mid-century inspiration meets large-scale design with this 30-light, two-tier take on the Dallas Chandelier and its Sputnik form, finished in brown nickel. Features 30 adjustable arms, each topped with a smoke glass globe, to allow for customized constellation creation. Shown with 2 tubular bulbs. Additional pipe available (PIPE-103). Also available in vintage brass (89463) and polished nickel (89464). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

This chandelier is modern in every way. In structure, it features two tiers of three lights, each encased in a hexagonal glass shade of smoke glass. Its linear design is edgy and updated, but the brown nickel finished steel softens the look and adds a dark allure. The hexagon canopy mimics the light shades. Additional pipe available (PIPE-207). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

A scaled-down, updated take on the popular Royalton design, now featuring eight lights instead of four. Smoke glass rods lend a transitional feel to this modern, brown nickel-finished steel design. Shown with frosted globe bulbs. Additional pipe available (PIPE-103). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Also available in soft silver with clear glass (89329).

The smallest member of the Geoffrey family, the Mini Geoffrey Chandelier may be smaller in size, but its gray-washed mango wood ring still makes a statement above a smaller dining room table or kitchen island. Features nine lights and cosmetically rusted iron chains. Shown with radio bulbs. Additional chain available (CHN-140). Also available in small (84171), medium (84174), large (84175) and three-tiered (83173). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Finish may vary.

Three rings of natural wood with 27 lights, suspended with purposely rusted chain makes a great statement when hanging over a large dining table or suspended in the center of a high ceilinged room. We photographed with antique Edison bulbs to reinforce the rustic industrial feel. Additional chain CHN-987.

The latest addition to the Parrish series is a three-light chandelier. A three-pronged steel frame finished in antique bronze suspends clear glass cylinder shades. Matching floor lamp and wall sconce available. Additional pipe available (PIPE-107). Shown with Edison bulbs. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

An eight-light chandelier with natural wood branches growing out from an iron center. This organic version of the starburst motif will cast beautiful shadows in whatever room you put it. Wood finish may vary. Additional chain available (CHN-128).

This five-light chandelier is the epitome of elevated simplicity. The delicate brown nickel frame leads way to smoked glass orbs that seemingly float in the air, creating a cerebral effect. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Shown with a Radio bulb. Also available antique brass/frosted glass (89053). Finish may vary. Additonal pipe available (PIPE-147).

A new take on the globe chandelier, the Henderson features 17 lights orbiting three visual planes. The brown nickel frame is complimented with smoke glass globes. Shown with a clear tubular bulb. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Finish may vary. Also available in pale brass/seedy glass (89040). Additonal pipe available (PIPE-103).

Hanging by a purposely rusted chain, this gray wood ring and its 12 lights make a great statement when hanging over a large round dining table or kitchen island. The Edison bulbs in the photo reinforce the rustic, industrial feel. Additional chain available CHN-987. Damp rated, can be used in covered outdoor areas.
Long and narrow 4-light pendant in steel with dark bronze finish features light beige linen fabric oval shade.

A modern spin on a traditional design makes this a transitional 12-light chandelier featuring gently curved wooden arms that ascent to form a column that attaches to an iron chain. Perfect in a dining room or a large kitchen island. Natural iron “candles” house the type B sockets. Shown with antique Victorian style Edison bulbs. Additional chain available CHN- 101.
Distinctive 6-light steel chandelier in antique bronze finish has sweeping arched arms topped with a light beige colored linen scalloped edge fabric shade with taupe sheer lining.

The smaller space with lower ceilings finally has its focal point with the Nessa Round Chandelier, the more compact cousin of the larger, oval Nessa Chandelier (89009). The antique brass circular frame is adorned with clear fluted glass rods, all individually attached, adding the design's glam quotient. Shown with small clear tubular bulbs. Additional pipe available (PIPE-101). Also available in polished nickel (89425). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

A large-scale, updated take on the popular Royalton design, now featuring 12 lights instead of four. Clear glass rods lend a transitional feel to this modern, soft silver-finished steel design. Shown with frosted globe bulbs. Additional pipe available (PIPE-176). Also available in brown nickel with smoke glass (89422). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

A scaled-down, updated take on the popular Royalton design, now featuring eight lights instead of four Clear glass rods lend a transitional feel to this modern, soft silver-finished steel design. Shown with frosted globe bulbs. Additional pipe available (PIPE-176). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Also available in brown nickel with smoke glass (89328).

The smaller space with lower ceilings finally has its focal point with the Nessa Round Chandelier, the more compact cousin of the larger, oval Nessa Chandelier (89009). The polished nickel circular frame is adorned with clear fluted glass rods, all individually attached, adding to the design's glam quotient. Shown with small clear tubular bulbs. Create curiosity with this circular cluster of natural materials. Rattan pole and peel is first steamed and shaped, and then washed in a smoke gray finish to create this unique round table. Crafted entirely from rattan, the rich curvature delivers a feminine touch to its rustic frame. A perfect place for a cocktail arrangement, indoors or out. Rattan may vary.

The irregular symmetry of the design in combination with the brown nickel and smoked glass spheres almost makes this feel like something from outer space. With 12 lights, it provides plenty of wattage over a large table. Consider shortening the pipe so it appears to be hugging the ceiling for a totally original look. Shown with small clear globe bulbs. Additional pipe available (PIPE-103). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Who knew that leather and metal could make such a refined pairing? Bi-tonal finished brass forms the structure; the top has a brushed finish while the adjustable stem and accents have an antiqued golden hue. Taking a cue from fashion houses, Celerie designed the cognac leather wraps to feature exposed stitching, that celebrates craftsmanship. Also comes in indigo leather (DC2011), as well as a shorter version in cognac leather (DC2008) and indigo leather (DC2009). Leather finish may vary.
Mid-century inspiration results in this 18 light, brown nickel take on Sputnik. 12 adjustable arms. Photographed with 2" tubular bulbs. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.
This adjustable (51" - 87") eight light cluster of the smoked glass Caviar spheres is finished in brown nickel. Makes for a dramatic light sculpture over a table.
Additional chain CHN-987.

We played with finish and scale to give these geometric wooden tables an element of intrigue. Featuring one ebony stained table and one gold painted table. Use them as a set for a fabulous oversized coffee table or split the set on either side of a sofa for a more eclectic look.
The Anvil collection was inspired by early memories of the anvil in the designer's family barn in Tennessee. The forged iron tops were inspired by 19th century cake stands.

Arboreal in form and richly organic in so many ways, this pendant is quite fascinating. An exaggerated patina is created by hand using a verdigris finish, so it almost looks like a 19th-century French antique. Even the immaculate details in the iron are done by hand. Encased in glass, six sockets fit chandelier bulbs to polish the look. Verdigris finish may vary.

The geometric design of the hexagonal-shaped top of this accent table make it an instant eye-catcher. An antique brass finish has been applied to a stainless steel base that accents the earthy tones of the natural walnut wood grain top. This small and well-formed piece is a great place to rest drinks or to accent a room all on its own. Wood finish may vary.

If you’ve been scouting for a perflectly charming piece for your space, you’re in luck. This cleverly crafted stool is petite, but full of character. At bird’s eye view, you can see the stem and four-leaf design as well as the warm Sahara finish. From the side, dissected blocks of wood reveal rich wood grain and natural knots that really make it unique. Doubles as a seat or small side table. Finish may vary.

The elegant rounded tops paired with the reclaimed wood block bases create a bold statement. This round side table has a burnt wax finish on a dark waxed wooden base. Coordinates with DD2027 and DD2029.

Contemporary and modern design elements take shape in our Turnin Side Table. A round top framed by a thick rim rests atop an exaggerated bell-shaped base, drawing attention to the sculptural aspect of the unique construction of the navy lacquer table. Artistic in form and functional by design, this piece would look just as brilliant next to a sofa as it would on its own. The versatile color of this side table allows it perform alongside various décor styles.

Classic, mid-century elegance is revitalized with this polished pendant. Five bulbs brilliantly light up the upend off-white linen shade, while two are neatly concealed within the canopy—each emitting a lustrous shine to its surroundings. An exposed detailing on the steel frame peeks from under the shade, adding a textured element to its otherwise smooth surface. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Additional pipe available (PIPE-422).

Light a space with sui generis style. Reminiscent of Yayoi Kusama's pop art of the 1960s, this stainless steel globe is finished in antique brass and is adorned with clear crystal orbs—lending a retro vibe to its modish form. An innovative light solution for contemporary spaces. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Additional pipe available (PIPE-178).

Showcase classic elegance with this sophisticated accent table. Shades of black, gray and white are put on display through the unique veining of the table's solid marble top—a blend we've deemed 'Galaxy Marble'. A tapered natural iron base provides a sleek silhouette, while the beveled edges of the marble add depth. Whether you feature this stellar piece solo or grouped with the larger versions, the Webber Accent Table will elegantly elevate a space.

Descending from an iron pipe that goes completely through the globe, the three-light Keira Pendant beautifully marries a natural iron finish with elegant linen-etched glass. Perfect in a pair above a kitchen island or in multiples down a hall. Shown with small clear tubular bulbs. Additional pipe available (PIPE-161). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Finish may vary.
Kaitlyn Pendant

A concrete, multifaceted shade makes the Katrina Pendant an eye-catching, but elegant oddity. The fossil-gray finish furthers this sturdy pendant's modern, industrial look. Suspends from an antique brass pipe. Additional pipe available (PIPE-101).

A vision of decadence, the Kacee Pendant is over the top in all the best ways. From the bulbous body made from frosted smoke glass to the antique brass pipe and canopy, rich details prevail. Additional pipe available (PIPE-101).

The Jenna Pendant is the epitome of effortless cool. Subtle design features like the smoke luster finish and layered glass shades warrant a second glance. Hung from an antique brass pipe. A striking blend of materials and finishes. Additional pipe available (PIPE-160). Also available in frosted glass (42244).

An updated take on a classic pendant design. The etched glass cone canopy adds to Selene's mystery, helping the fixture time travel between futurism and ancient craft. Show with a silver bowl globe bulb. Additional pipe available (pipe-100).

Inherently vibrant, our Mini Zanadoo is an even smaller version of one of our most popular designs. Its miniature shape makes it ideal for staging in multiples. Finished in polished nickel, we love it with the small clear tubular bulbs. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Additional pipe available PIPE-100.

Entirely handmade of natural iron with brass welds, the three twisted spiraled rings are another example of the concentric circle trend we are seeing this spring This artful sculptural pendant can fold flat or be adjusted for additional dimensionality around a single exposed bulb. This one-light smokey brown glass pendant features a subtle gradient near the top and bottom of the piece which typically happens when glass in hand blown. The muted tone is accentuated with a hand-etched surface design that mimics hammered metal. Color may vary. Taupe cloth cord.

Geometrics are a big trend in fashion, just as they are for interiors. This open-caged pendant, shown here with an Edison bulb, is the perfect example of just how stylish pentagons can be. Made of polished nickel-plated stainless steel, this design makes great shadows on the wall and ceiling. Additional pipe available PIPE-127.
Mixed metal hammered iron pendent with dark silver exterior and interior accented with a brass weld. Taupe cloth cord.
Mixed metal hammered iron pendent with dark silver exterior and interior accented with a brass welds. Taupe cloth cord.

Geometrics are a big trend in fashion, just as they are for interiors. This open-caged pendant, shown here with an Edison bulb, is the perfect example of just how stylish pentagons can be. Made of polished nickel-plated stainless steel, this design makes great shadows on the wall and ceiling. Additional pipe available PIPE-127.

We especially like the juxtaposition of this really sleek dark iron shape with the artisan qualities of the hammered surface and brass welds. Makes for an interesting single-light pendant that can stand alone or hang with others. Taupe cloth cord.

Teardrop shaped pendant of translucent antique mercury glass provides ambient light. Use as a single fixture or arrange with others in a linear arrangement or clustered together at varying heights. Finish and size may vary. Socket length may vary.

Smoke ombre mouth blown glass pendant has a great rolled edge detail, and we love how the design showcases whichever style of light bulb you choose to use. The scale of this piece makes it great for a powder room. Shown with an Edison bulb.

A clear teardrop glass shade is suspended from a square polished nickel canopy with matching square pipe. Mount multiples down a hallway to create drama. Shown with a radio bulb. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Additional pipe available PIPE-133.

Material mastery at its finest, Frank Ponterio has blended dueling design elements to create a classic yet intriguing pendant design. Perfect for pairing, we envision multiples over a bar, adding architectural sophistication to any space. Additional pipe available (PIPE-211).

Revel in the refinement this simple yet sophisticated chandelier possesses. Glass artisans haphazardly scatter pieces of glass into a dome-shaped mold to construct the spaghetti glass form that creates a lightscape masterpiece each time its in use. A removable crystal orb break accents the end of the antique brass steel stem for an extra luxe touch. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Additional pipe available (PIPE-180).

The pendant version of our Vance Vase Collection is just as elegant in style as it is stately in form. A burnt smoke luster glass shade is suspended by a sleek brass pipe and is capped with a vintage brass band that accentuates the warm tones this piece emits. The clean lines that shape the straightforward silhouette offer a streamlined approach to lighting design. Hang several over a dining table to create a luxe lightscape. Finish may vary. Additional pipe available (PIPE-199).

The pendant version of our Tomlin Sconce (49298), this unrivaled luminescent elevates any space. Thick, seedy slump glass seems to float effortlessly in the room it occupies, suspended by a sleek chain. An antique brass frame houses a total of 10 bulbs, delivering a glow that is gently diffused by the hand-etched milky white glass that surrounds it. Due to the handmade nature, variances in the glass will occur. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Additional chain available (CHN-206).

This pendant breaks the boundaries of geometric design. A large opal glass globe seems to float effortlessly in a steel circular cage that has been embellished with champagne crystal disks. The interplay of circles in different materials and sizes yields an unexpected spatial silhouette. When in use, the manipulation and play of light on the steel and glass creates a warm and inspiring atmosphere. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Additional pipe available (PIPE-180).

Bask in the beauty of brass with our Wyatt Pendant. The simple and sleek form exudes elegance and brings forth a refined element to a space with its vintage brass finish and slightly exposed polished interior. A flame-cut edge takes shape around the bottom, delivering a touch of texture to the otherwise smooth surface. Finish may vary. Additional pipe available (PIPE-429).

Unveiling a slender silhouette, this brass pendant is the perfect light to hang over a breakfast nook table or a small dining setup. The thin frame spotlights a large 5" frosted globe bulb that brightens the vintage brass finish when in use. Accented with a bauble detail that adds a textured element to its smooth surface. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Additional pipe available (PIPE-428).

Lend a distinct dynamic to a dining space with this geometric pendant. The multifaceted, semi-open form is composed of perforated and smooth iron triangles that work in unison to create a stark yet complementary contrast to the overall aesthetic. The negative space and perforated holes allow light to stream through unique angles, creating a subdued lightscape. The antique brass finish offers a brilliant shine. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Additional pipe available (PIPE-435).

The unconventionality of this pendant's design delves into the depths of sculptural artwork. The dome frame that hangs from a slender pipe is constructed from hammered iron and features brass spheres that playfully accent the edge. The entire form is finished in antique brass that delivers a luminescent shine which is heightened when in use. A daring light fixture fit for contemporary spaces. Finish may vary.

Thick crystal, sculpted into an optical teardrop globe, creates the extraordinary shade of this pendant lamp. The center is carved out to fit a single light, which focuses a radiant beam of light downward, filtering the light immensely which casts outward. It’s accented with a conical armiture, which matches the pipe in an antique brass finish. Additional pipe available (PIPE-178).

Style moderne the way we like it—unique and distinct. The geometric foundation of this bird swing-like apparatus is a nod to Art Deco design with its open-form brass frame that moves about. Suspended from a solid brass pipe, the entire fixture features an antiqued finish. An inverted canopy tops the piece and lends a visual aesthetic that appeals to the geometrical design. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Additional pipe available (PIPE-430).

This pendant is full of character, with marvelous details throughout that add style and panache. The steel frame is finished in an antique brass that shows in accents all over the fixture, even in the intriguing top mount, matching canopy and uniquely modern chain in square links. Additional chain available (CHN-197).

Ultra-modern in its design, this exciting pendant is practically futuristic. Its extraordinary style comes from its dimension-an angular sleeve of opal glass is contained within several disks of heritage brass finished steel, which are precision cut to fit the glass perfectly. The layered shape construction makes this piece not only a light fixture, but an out-of-this-world, sculptural work of art. Additional pipe (PIPE-201) available. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Timeless design can elicit intrigue when done right. At first, it looks like a traditional lantern-that is, until you notice the shade is made entire of pieces of glass. Additional pipe available (PIPE-172). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas

A stylish and elegant pairing of geometric inspiration and transitional design come together in this pendant. Two linear squares of steel encase a demi-globe of opal glass, which casts a warm glow throughout a space. The frame has a classic antique brass finish. Additional pipe available (PIPE-101). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Inspired by modern jewelry design, this pendant is sculptural and functional. Five bands of twisted steel form the drop, which is finished in an antique brass to give it an elegant feel. The light is concealed in the top mount; when it is switched on , the pendant casts light and linear shadows downward in a dramatic way. It's an ideal accent light, especially in a space where it can be admired as a work of art. Additional chain available (CHN-196).

The double suspension point of this glowing beauty portrays balance and symmetry, challenged by the pull of an arrow inspired by the astrology of the night sky. Features two simple, opal glass orbs wrapped with a dark bronze steel band, embellished with decorative antique brass elements. Additional pipe available (PIPE-190).

We bow down to this beautifully romantic pendant. Features a simple, opal glass orb wrapped with a dark bronze steel band, embellished with decorative antique brass elements. See where the arrow of the Celeste Pendant will take you! Additional pipe available (PIPE-180).

Calm, space-age sheen immediately comes to mind when experiencing the soft light and matching design of the Jannah Pendant. An antiqued mirror disc adorns the Isola Pendant's classic antique brass rod and accents. A lesson in classic artisan craftsmanship. Shown with a clear bent tip candelabra bulb. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Finish may vary. Additional pipe available (PIPE-149).

This globe pendant is unique not only in style, but by design. It's crafted from thistle finished art glass, with loosely flowing bubbles and glistening metallic tonal contrasts. The traditional hourglass shape gets a modern revamp in this contemporary drop pendant. Modern elegance is simplified with this sleek and stylish pendant. A glass shade is suspended by a steel pipe with an antique brass finish that accents and brightens the moody hue of the smoke glass. Rebelling from standard, lackluster outdoor lighting, this fixture brings artistic flair into natural environments. The mid-century craftsman style of this pendant light makes it intriguing and modern, while its grand scale gives it presence. This handsomely structured lantern is upscale in form and style. This pendant is a great example of how you can take a classic form and natural aesthetic and update them to evoke a modern feel. The exaggerated, bird's nest pattern is made using thinly sliced rattan stalks that are bent and formed onto a metal frame, then painted with in a light stonewash stain for a slightly unexpected, sophisticated finish. Due to the open-weave design, the light it gives off is abundant in all directions. Additional pipe available (PIPE-101).

This pendant showcases traditional style with a modern edge. Though made in a classic lantern form, wonderful details like a natural iron finished frame and hammered-like textured glass shade give it an updated look. Light a space with timeless design. This classic globe pendant features a clear glass shade and aged iron finished steel, giving it an updated, industrial style. Like a magnetic field surrounding the central lantern, almost 100 strips of upholstered banding are made to create each of these pendants. The filtered light comes from a single bulb, casting a wonderful glow and soft, linear shadows. Additional pipe available (PIPE-101).

Classical elements like curled accents, beaded trim and a dome shape make this beauty a muse to behold. Suspended by lengths of gilt iron, this handsome shade pendant is a golden beau. Light a space with timeless design. This classic globe pendant features a clear glass shade and aged iron finished steel, giving it an updated, industrial style. Unique elements like a staggered design, detailed bulb fitting and dome glass make this a truly unique sconce.
