Distinctive 6-light steel chandelier in antique bronze finish has sweeping arched arms topped with a light beige colored linen scalloped edge fabric shade with taupe sheer lining.

This chandelier masters design simplicity. Displaying a simple natural iron silhouette, the slender five-arm frame showcases decorative baubles that have been finished in a polished brass for a subtle lamé quality—each a different shape. When illuminated, the arms appear to be fluted, delivering an extra element of texture to a space. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Additional pipe available (PIPE-197).

Modern desires take the lead on this contemporary candelabra design. Dark and sensuous, Griffith masters simplistic sophistication. Suspended from decorative piping, the steel frame is finished in a warm heritage brass and paired with black crystal rods. Also available in antique brass (DP89000). Additional chain available (CHN-203).
Modern yet classic, this celestial globe of opaline glass pares ornament down to an unadorned bronze metal ring and gold chain links. Also available in antique brass (DS89006).

We love the antique brass and natural iron combination of this 10-light chandelier. Each of the arms are joined by hammered diamond wings that are almost jewelry-like in nature, which can be playfully adjusted along the frame so you can style to your liking. Full of character and style, this piece showcases well in contemporary spaces. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Additional pipe available (PIPE-198).

When it comes to getting the perfect lighting, this chandelier is top notch. Six rotating lamps sit on branches of two tiers of stainless steel. Each can be maneuvered to face up, down, out or to the sides to light up your space. The frame is finished in a slightly weathered bronze and each light has a heritage brass polish with white interior. Additional pipe is available (PIPE-105). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Also available in pale brass with robin’s egg blue (89099).

Like a balancing act, this chandelier explores an interaction between linear composition and circular softness. The natural iron frame crosses in the center to hold four glass disks and is designed to mounts closely to the ceiling. Each disk has a handmade antique finished interior to reflect the light upward and back down from the ceiling, while also adding a textured look from below. Additional pipe available (PIPE-197). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Glamorously goth or naturally powerful, this natural iron chandelier is the darker, edgier cousin of our gilded version. Perfect for a rustic mountain retreat or an industrial loft in the city. Additional pipe available (PIPE-166). Finish may vary. Also available in gold leaf (DD42617). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

We love the bronze and antique brass combination on this modern eight light chandelier that was inspired by the spokes on a wheel. Each of the four horizontal square rods split into two and support the antique brass shades. Each shade has a frosted glass bottom diffuser. Perfect over a dining table or kitchen island. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

This eight-light chandelier is slightly whimsical. Frosted, seedy glass discs bring a modern feel to this stunning wind chime design. A blackened iron frame anchors the piece while adding a hint of industrialism. Finish may vary. Shown with a clear tubular bulb. Additional pipe available (PIPE-157).
Ring shaped 14-light iron pendant light creates a glowing luminaire effect with each light in open bronze finished box. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

This graphic six arm 48 light chandelier is suspended by a wire filament, making it appear to float. The finish is bronze. This is a sculpture waiting to be hung. Shown with clear globe bulbs. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Opal glass spheres have been placed asymmetrically across a bronze bar, giving the chandelier an organic effect reminiscent of designs in nature. Antique brass accents add the perfect amount of polish and contrast. With six lights, it provides plenty of wattage over a large table. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Additional pipe available PIPE-105.

Clean, sophisticated and practical, this six-light chandelier has a sleek, narrow silhouette perfect for hanging over an island in the kitchen or over a table that wants to be the center of attention. Constructed in steel with matte black microfiber and antique brass-finished accents. Acrylic diffusers at the top and bottom filter the light. Black cloth cord.

Who knew that leather and metal could make such a refined pairing? Bi-tonal finished brass forms the structure; the top has a brushed finish while the adjustable stem and accents have an antiqued golden hue. Taking a cue from fashion houses, Celerie designed the cognac leather wraps to feature exposed stitching, that celebrates craftsmanship. Also comes in indigo leather (DC2009), as well as an accent table version in cognac leather (DC2010) and indigo leather (DC2011). Leather finish may vary.

Hardly a bystander, the Lyle Side Table will command any space. The brass clad sabots wear decorative pitting like a coat of armor fit with an iron spear. The cerused sable stain enhances the oak grain, highlighting the attention paid to this fine piece of furniture. Finish may vary.

This completely original antique brass clad piece was sparked by an embroidered emperor's robe I saw at The Met's China Through the Looking Glass exhibition. If we draped a table with an emperor's robe, this is what we'd get. Exotic and glamourous! Perfect as the sofa or bedside...or as a small, gleaming center table! Finish may vary.

Who knew that leather and metal could make such a refined pairing? Bi-tonal finished brass forms the structure; the top has a brushed finish while the adjustable stem and accents have an antiqued golden hue. Taking a cue from fashion houses, Celerie designed the cognac leather wraps to feature exposed stitching, that celebrates craftsmanship. Also comes in cognac leather (DC2008), as well as an accent table version in cognac leather (DC2010) and indigo leather (DC2011). Leather finish may vary.

Undoubtedly modern, this handsome fixture also reveals influences in industrial design and geometric art. The entire piece is cast from iron, featuring two contrasting finishes in natural iron and antique brass. Each light is mounted inside a disk ring, allowing the finish inside to cast a more brilliant, surrounding glow. It's beautiful down to the details: brass welding joints and a slightly-aged finish. Additional pipe available (PIPE-197). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Inspired by the uniqueness our Mia Pendant (41005) imparts upon a space, we've created this colorful take in a different shape. Strips of pliable blue cadet microfiber banding surround the light, which is suspended from a steel pipe finished in a warm antique brass. The styrene shape is not only aesthetically engaging, but it filters the light and casts soft, linear shadows. Additional pipe available (PIPE-101).

Overtly dramatic in old-world style and modern sensibility, this intricately designed iron pendant has an abundance of character. Several tubes of formed antique brass metal are outfitted with cut metal detailing that creates a look reminiscent of origami art. The tubes surround the base structure, which conceals the light fixture and shines the light downward, as well as into the tubes. The effect is a moody light that sets a romantic scene. Additional chain available (CHN-195).

Geometrics are a big trend in fashion, just as they are for interiors. This open caged pendant is the perfect example of just how stylish pentagons can be. Made of polished brass plated stainless steel, this design makes great shadows on the wall and ceiling. Additional pipe available PIPE-123. Shown with an Edison bulb.

Two shades of hand-blown glass forms the drop of this pendant. Seemingly simple in its design, an inner teardrop-shaped shade conceals a standard bulb in opal glass, then a larger shade rests outside it, exposing the inner piece in clear glass. Both hang from a stainless steel stem and mount, both finished in brushed nickel. Additional pipe available (PIPE-181). Also available in antique brass (49098). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Two shades of hand-blown glass forms the drop of this pendant. Seemingly simple in its design, an inner teardrop-shaped shade conceals a standard bulb in opal glass, then a larger shade rests outside it, exposing the inner piece in clear glass. Both hang from a stainless steel stem and mount, both finished in antique brass. Additional pipe available (PIPE-180). Also available in brushed nickel (49174). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

The double suspension point of this glowing beauty portrays balance and symmetry, challenged by the pull of an arrow inspired by the astrology of the night sky. Features two simple, milky white glass orbs wrapped with a dark bronze steel band, embellished with decorative vintage silver elements. Additional pipe available (PIPE-190).

Equal parts classic and dramatic, this versatile light fixture delivers form & function in one supple curve. The streamlined dome design features an outer matte taupe surface while the interior features a brilliant silver metallic semi-matte finish. Though a stand-out fixture on its own, it makes an even bigger impact when grouped with the complementary shapes and tones in the Pascal, Patton and Ponce Pendant Collections. Additional pipe available (PIPE-101).

Brace yourself—the Joey Tray packs a punch. A Frank Ponterio favorite, the brass knuckle handles add an unexpected twist on the classic espresso brown tray, finished in a warm antique brass that pops against the sleek leather.
The perfect chair for anywhere. Zephyr’s slender, curved polished brass steel frame and gray hide-covered seat are minimal in form while offering maximum glamour. Hide will vary.

Suspended by lengths of gilt iron, this handsome shade pendant is a golden beau. The iron hook links are gilt in hand-applied gold leaf, slightly concealing the clear cord, and the tapered shade is wrapped in navy top-grain leather. Underneath, the shade is line in gold, so the light that’s downcast is warm and brilliant. Gold leaf and leather finish may vary. Also comes in dove gray leather (DC42007).

Our versatile, articulating wall light dons a woven wicker shade for a fun, textural mix. Finished in antique brass, it's useful as a reading lamp, picture light or, as Windsor uses in her own home, as accent lighting over bookcases. Shown with a 3 3" frosted globe bulb.

As a nod to the urban spirit of Chicago, Frank Ponterio designed a tattoo-inspired emblem that was hand-carved on a set of bronze ceramic containers. The perfect balance of graphic refinement, this versatile set can house vibrant succulents or be stacked on a beautiful étagère. Each piece will be hand-done, lending a one-of-a-kind quality to the designs.

Modern desires take the lead on this contemporary sconce design. Dark and sensuous, Griffith masters simplistic sophistication. The steel backplate features a warm heritage brass frame, paired with black crystal for subtle contrast. Also available in ivory and antique brass (DP49003).

Wrought with fine details, Frank Ponterio's Salotto Cabinet is the crown jewel of his debut collection. The vellum panels were inspired by a pair of bronze doors at Villa Necchi in Milan. Originally designed to guide air through a solarium, the reinterpreted cut-outs are purely decorative, offering a glimpse of the beautifully-layered contents within. Blonde oak and bronze hardware add another layer of craftsmanship. Vellum will vary.

Basking in regality and elegance is this regency glam sconce. The rounded design is simply luxurious, framed in an antique brass finished steel with several rods of clear glass. These rods filter the light just slightly, so beams from the two interior bulbs shine upward to add a bit of drama. Because it has a slightly traditional style, it’s a timeless light fixture that blends well in virtually any space. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

At first, you might think this is merely a modernist wall sculpture—but look again. Switch on the light to reveal its hidden LED light fixture, which is concealed in the linear design. It shines against the wall to reflect ambient light back into the space. The steel sconce is completely finished in antique brass, to grace any space with a hint of modern luxury. This sconce would look great mounted along a hallway or flanking a fantastic piece of art.

The organic luxury of botanical form marries the glamorous Hollywood Regency design in this flourishing sconce, slightly reminiscent of Art Deco theater style. Palm leaf textures are crafted in matte-brass plated aluminum, giving it a sense of regality as well as shine. When on, light is cast up through the peaked rim and downward through the bottom opening, emitting warm, dramatic light.

Taking a cue from modern style, this wall sconce gives a traditional design an updated look. Made entirely of brass, it is then finished in antique brass, which lends the updated twist and adds so much shine The interior of the shade is a simple, brushed brass and conceals a small light, like a torpedo bulb. The result is an elegant sconce that elevates a space with a timeless look.

Vertically symmetrical in design, two conical lamps form the brilliance that is this sconce. Crafted entirely of stainless steel, a single post stands from a square plaque mount, with matching shades casting light both upward and downward. The effect is quite moody and dramatic. Both lamps are lined with a matching antique brass metal shade, so the sconce is touch-safe when switched on. Also available in brushed nickel (44380). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

A lesson in effortless elegance, the Donovan Tray marries a timeless silhouette with modern finesse. The leather base is embossed for a shagreen effect and accented with hand-hammered brass, infusing handcrafted charm into the design.

Sleek, slender, svelte; this handsome stainless steel sconce brings light and looks to a space. A curving stem has a ball accent and is crafted into a matching flush mount with a disk of celestial blue crystal, both featuring an antique brass finish. The design is fantastically modern and the mixing of crystal and stainless steel is utterly unique. Topped with a tapered, ivory silk shade.

So simple and so modern, this is a sconce that fits in anywhere. Clean lines, crafted from stainless steel, frame cubes of frosted glass, so the light is filtered beautifully. The mid-strip is hand-punched and casts scattered light in every direction. The warm brass tones are thanks to a brushed, antique brass finish that covers the piece, all the way to the concealed mount. Fits two standard bulbs. Also available as a rectangular pendant (DC49002) and square pendant (DC89001).

The latest addition to the Parrish series is a single-light sconce. A three-pronged steel frame finished in antique brass suspends a clear glass cylinder shade on a solitary slip hook. Shown with an Edison bulb. Also available in vintage silver (49087) and antique bronze (49953), as well as an antique bronze floor lamp (79953) and chandelier (89033). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Handcrafted details, like etched trim and hammered textures, make this striking sconce a botanical wonder. Made from brass, the broad, tropical leaf design conceals five tubular or candelabra bulbs, so it casts a vibrant glow upward. It’s polished by hand in a vintage finish and has a back mount that is almost completely hidden by the design.

Crafted entirely of stainless steel, the mount and arm have a rich bronze finish that is slightly weathered to add to its vintage look. The shade is finished in an antique brass, while the interior is painted in white for added reflective light. It is mounted on an 180º swivel arm and the shade has slight vertical maneuverability. Shown with a 5-inch frosted globe bulb. Also available in pale brass (49172). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Organic, almost like handcrafted calla lilies, this grand sconce is overflowing with natural beauty. Made entirely from brass from stem to petal, it is finished in a warm polish for added gloss and shine. The surprise is at the flick of a switch; hand-punched details in the six lampshades cast dots of light that scatter around the room. At over two feet tall, this light is impactful and so brilliant. Seamlessly designed center mount keeps it secure.

So unexpected, this design is so uniquely modern it’ll be a constant marvel. A single bulb nests inside a stainless steel cube form, finished in heritage brass for a very warm and organic look. The twist lies beneath: 16 hand-formed, matching diamond links hang dramatically at almost three feet in length. Also available in soft silver (49173). Metal finish may vary.

So simple and so modern, this is a sconce that fits in anywhere. Clean lines, crafted from stainless steel, frame cubes of frosted glass, so the light is filtered beautifully. The warm metal tones are thanks to an antique brass finish that covers the piece. It mounts flush to the wall, so the look is clean and sleek. Fits two candelabra bulbs. Also available in brown nickel (49102) and dark vintage silver (49103). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Elegance, shine and an extra-curvy form give this small sconce grand style. Like a golden chalice, it is crafted from sleek iron with a luxurious brass polish, the foundation to whatever style bulb you choose. The arm stands at a slight distance from the generously sized plaque mount, reflecting just a little extra shine around the room. Shown with a 3-inch frosted globe bulb.

This hammered and polished brass sconce exemplifies simple elegance and has brilliant texture that almost shimmers in the light. The gently shaped circular back plate glows with the reflection of the light bulb. Perfect for a hallway or powder room. Shown with an antique radio bulb. Also available in smooth brass (42046).

Pressed into the shape of a wild, exotic leaf, this sconce is truly unique in all of its handcrafted features. Organic textures are made by pressing the plate of brass into shape, then the use of special tools and immense skill are needed to get the ridges and lines just right. The lovely, rounded edges are cut by hand, creating a magnificent, backlit horizon when the sconce is switched on. The stem and leaf are polished in an antique finish. Fits one standard blub.

Jadestone inspired by an 8th century emperor's sceptre, this whimsical sconce, finished in antiqued gold leaf, is at once organic and glamorous. A statement piece for any room. Topped with a white microfiber tapered shade. Also available in right sconce (DD49009). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Finish may vary.

The Arteriors bath collection is complete with the Jalen Vanity Light. An updated take on the popular Jalen chandelier and sconce designs, this five-light design features five vintage silver circles extending from a matching backplate. Each circle is finished with a frosted glass diffuser, creating ideal soft light. Also available in antique brass (49147). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.
Jennifer Sconce

This vintage-inspired sconce has endless sophistication that will never go out of style. Each piece is crafted from brass, constructed in a tall, slender form. The wall mount is made in three tiers, a plaque of brilliantly clear acrylic separating two plates of brass. All the metal is finished in a bronzy vintage polish—down to the screws—and a petite linen barrel shade in ivory perches atop. Also available in vintage silver (44379).

Frosted glass and polished nickel combine to yield a clasically cool and updated take on a hanging lantern. Evokes feelings of retrofutirism. Also available in antique brass (49044). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

This midcentury style features vintage silver and bronze steel. The opal globe is off-center, adding a welcomed layer of asymmetry. Pair with the Haynes Right Sconce (49081). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Also available in antique brass (49061).

The clear teardrop glass shade houses the bulb of your choice as it is suspended from a square polished nickel back plate. Mount multiples down a hallway to create drama. Coordinates with similar table lamp (49935) and floor lamp (79935). 79935). Shown with small clear tubular bulb. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

An adaptation of our popular floor lamp, this matte black wall sconce has two lights inside the off-white linen shade which is adjustable up and down and a stationary arm. Note the solid brass details. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Nine antiqued mirror panels come together to create the Iris Sconce. The Iris stands alone as a work of art, but doubles as function with its two sockets. Featured natural iron accents. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Finish may vary.

This midcentury style features vintage silver and bronze steel. The opal globe is off-center, adding a welcomed layer of asymmetry. Pair with the Haynes Left Sconce (49080). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Also available in antique brass (49062).

Rebelling from standard, lackluster outdoor lighting, this fixture brings artistic flair into natural environments. The shape is an inspiration of mid-century design, taking a classic indoor design and reinterpreting it for stylish outdoor spaces. The dome light is crafted from opal glass and the structure from steel finished in aged iron. The finial contrasts the shade in a nickel finish. Approved for use in outdoor areas.

This handsomely structured lantern sconce is upscale in form and style. It is made from aged iron finished steel, tapered in form, and designed with slight, exposed details and contrasting nickel finish accents to exude an industrial feel. A sleeve of opaque opal glass rests inside, filtering the light from a standard bulb. Approved for use in outdoor areas.

The latest addition to the Parrish series is a single-light outdoor sconce. A steel frame finished in aged iron suspends a clear glass cylinder shade on a solitary slip hook. Though classic and simple, its sleek lines lend a bit of an industrial edge. Shown with an Edison bulb. Also available in aged brass (49197). Approved for use in outdoor areas.

Inspired by our indoor version, the clear teardrop glass shade of this outdoor sconce houses the bulb of your choice as it is suspended from a square aged iron finished steel back plate. Mount multiples along a patio space to add tons of light and create drama. Bring the look inside with the coordinating indoor version (49984). Shown with small clear tubular bulb. Also comes in aged brass (49191). Approved for use in outdoor areas.

Architectural design and mixed materials are at the foundation of the retro yet modern appeal of this wall space luminescent. The fine execution of the sharp angles of the textured gray wood atop a sleek marble backplate, creates a stunning profile and presents a gallery-like aesthetic. The wood construction twists sideways, so changing the bulb is quite efficient. Finish may vary. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.
Kady Sconce

The seedy glass tear drop shade and natural iron backplate of the original Madeline sconce grows to a trio, perfect for above a bathroom vanity. Also available as a single sconce (42024). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Finish may vary.

Derived from the popular Stefan Indoor Sconce (49006), this outdoor-safe version combines aged iron with frosted glass and nickel finished steel to create a sophisticated and modern look. Consider pairs flanking a front door. Also available in aged brass (49188). Approved for use in outdoor areas.

Although steel is typically an industrial attribute, it is decidedly modern when finished in champagne leaf. Note how each soft opal globe is caged with metal, creating a bit of yin and yang. Pair with 49032 to create a symmetrical display on either side of a mirror. Finish may vary.

Attention to detail defines this seemingly simplistic sconce that can be hung vertically or horizontally. From hammered natural iron to the hand-applied brass welds carefully placed at the top and bottom, this classic shape takes on an industrial flair. A double socket allows light to emanate from the top and the bottom. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Although steel is typically an industrial attribute, it is decidedly modern when finished in champagne leaf. Note how each soft opal globe is caged with metal, creating a bit of yin and yang. Pair with 49031 to create a symmetrical display on either side of a mirror. Finish may vary.

The traditional hourglass shape gets a modern revamp in this contemporary steel sconce. The glow comes from the opal glass shade, which conceals two bulbs—one up and one down—to cast ample, warm light throughout a space. Its linear style is what makes it so modern, though the aged iron accents also lend an updated look, too. Approved for use in outdoor areas. Also available in Aged Brass (49185).

Chinoiserie panels of the 17th century meet French Rococo. We added an etched mirrored, three light sconce with antique brass arms holding candle drip sockets to complete the Canton Series Barry Dixon introduced last year. These will romantically glitter down a long hall or flank a gilded mirror over a vanity or buffet. Shown with clear bent tip candelabra bulbs.

A design derivative based on our popular Yale Chandelier (86762). This one light sconce has hundreds of rows of delicate antique nickel chains draped over the frame cascading down the wall giving it an elegant yet bedraggled effect. Shown with a small clear tubular bulb. Perfect in an elegant powder room, dining room or hallway. Height of sconce and chain lengths may vary.

A further exploration of this popular design, this polished nickel starburst embraces the five light bulbs creating dramatic shadows and patterns on the walls. Can be hung vertically or horizontally. Shown with silver bowl globe bulbs. This piece can also be mounted to the ceiling. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

We've taken the modern and geometric features of our Keifer Chandelier to create this wall space version. The four bronze arms are defined with sharp angles and antique brass accents; each topped with torch-like opal shade that brings together the muted softer industrial tone and echoes mid-century Italian design. Right version avaiable (49272). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

A simple, delicate, and geometric two-light sconce is perfect for small spaces that need a little extra light. The hammered natural iron finish and brass welds add a contemporary touch to its iron base. Also available in white (42235), vintage brass (42236), and bronze (42237). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

We've taken the modern and geometric features of our Keifer Chandelier to create this wall space version. The four bronze arms are defined with sharp angles and antique brass accents; each topped with torch-like opal shade that brings together the muted softer industrial tone and echoes mid-century Italian design. Left version avaiable (49273). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

The popular Prescott Collection now features this unique, two-light sconce. Iron finished in champagne leaf, with an antiqued, speckled mirror back plate, this sconce is a go-anywhere design. Damp rated and approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

A design derivative based on our popular Yale chandelier (86762). This dramatic one-light sconce has hundreds of rows of delicate antique nickel chains artistically draped and looped over the frame, leaving extra-long staggered chains cascading down the wall for an elegant yet bedraggled tassel effect. Shown with a small clear tubular bulb. Height of sconce and chain lengths may vary.

Our Yasmin Sconce gets an edgy update with a perforated bronze metal shade and antique brass details. The uniformed puncture design creates a unique shadow play against any interior or exterior façade when in use. Features a stationary arm with an adjustable shade, so you can choose an angle that suits you. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Keep your bedtime reads well-lit with this simply stunning wall sconce. The adjustable position of the sleek steel frame makes it the perfect task light for bedrooms or directional lighting option for an entryway. Spotlight a space by pairing with another for an even more dramatic lightscape. Also available in vintage silver and bronze finishes. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

The traditional French silhouette and classic elements of this sconce are updated with an antique brass decorative chain. The subtle yet distinct play on different shapes of this luminescent delivers a striking visual aesthetic to a wall space. When illuminated, the ivory microfiber shade funnels the light so that it creates a unique shadowplay alongside the rectangular links of the chain. Great for traditional or contemporary spaces. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

A lesson in geometry in the absence of symmetry, this sconce displays an asymmetrical design that is both simple and sleek. Faceted champagne crystal glass tapers through a thick antique brass belt, creating a luxe structure that is as much of a visual aesthetic as it is a functioning form. Pair with another to double the amount of lustrous illumination. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

The Trevi Sconce is a perfect example of the resurgence of contemporary geometric design. A bronze finish trims two opal glass triangles, anchored on an antique brass steel mount, delivering a stark contrast to the opaque hue. The sleek yet sharp angles become more defined when in use and work to add depth and dimension to a wall space. A modish light solution for most spaces. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Sleek and stylish, the modern form of this antique brass sconce offers a clean and streamlined visual to a wall space. The rectangular profile lends a contemporary touch to traditional lighting designs, and its steel form delivers a slight industrial appeal. When in use, the sconce appears lucent thanks to the ultramodern LED light. Its slender silhouette makes this a great light option for small spaces. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

In a classic fashion, this multi-light sconce revels in sophisticated simplicity. The steel wall mount is finished in a stunning antique brass, and features two arms that showcase capsule-shaped frosted glass shades which help to subtly diffuse the light. Each shade encases two bulbs, delivering an extra element of shine to a wall space. A great light solution for a vanity or powder room. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Blending simplicity and functionality, this unassuming light fixture subtly accents a space while delivering a warm glow to a wallscape. The circlet form is shaped by textured and smooth iron that contrasts brilliantly when lit. A sleek stem centers the structure and anchors the spherical shape for a more dynamic design. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Modern origami takes shape in this two-light wall sconce. The sharp angles of the iron form work to filter light through the top and bottom, allowing the light to play on the symmetry of its geometric design. Its antique brass finish helps to warm up a wall space. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.
Sink in to the rolling landscape of the Dune Lounger. Designed for comfort in every way, the sleek channeled form with the farrow linen and tapered antique brass legs are elegantly effortless.

This extremely practical wall sconce pivots to allow the customization of the light source: top, bottom, or side depending on what you want to highlight. Finished in antique brass, this light is at its essence classically simple and completely modern.

Our bronzed two-light sconce is a truly minimalist expression of traditional ironwork, consisting of a single hand-forged stem and dual Edison-style candelabra bulbs. Use it in pairs for classical symmetry, or in numbers to line a foyer or hallway. Shown with a nostalgic loop bulb.

This aperture beauty exemplifies light play and obscure illumination. The bronze finished steel spotlight shines light upwards onto the gold leafed disc, generating a warm glow that emanates against the wall. Adjustable arms allow you to adjust the glow as desired. The white marble backplate adds another layer of visual dimension, creating a beautiful material mix. Marble may vary.

Our beautifully sculpted urn begged for a companion stand to infuse it with modern life. This simple pedestal with its slim proportions and combination of white marble and antique brass feels inherently modern and will work as well with a modern sculpture as it does with the urn. Marble may vary.

Blending art and poetry together with useful functionality - the Aja Wall Sonce was originally designed to hold a cookbook but lends itself as the perfect perch for a poem or artwork. The steel frame is finished in antique brass.

The artisan beauty of these gray suede bands handwoven into a simple basket weave pattern that is stretched around a sleek and modern polished brass frame, makes this bench both a statement piece and a practical seating option. Influenced by equestrian culture and the juxtaposition of the materials, this bench brings texture and modern style to any room. Suede will vary in color.

This steel sconce is equal parts neo-classical, traditional, and contemporary. The squared chain drop and elegantly shaped cage in antique brass provide the perfect vessel to house the clear crystal sphere, which is illuminated from a halogen bulb set above. This light is a perfect example of how jewelry has influenced my designs and would look beautiful above a mirror or in a pair over a long console table.

The amorphic shape of this stylish blotter tray brings back the lost art of writing. The sumptuous mottled brown leather and bronzed finished aluminum edging elicit delight, inspiring old traditions to take new form.
Dark Matter comes to life with this frosted smoke glass pendant. Shade is highlighted by contrasting ridged and divoted patterns. Shown with a Radio bulb. Finish may vary.

Create a unique lighting environment without compromising class. The tiered silhouette of the pendant features opal glass fashioned with an aged-iron finish steel belt, forging a classic and clean style. The diamond-esque shape allows light to flow over any outdoor setup. Approved for use in outdoor areas. Additional pipe available (PIPE-420)

The contemporary form of this outdoor pendant is striking and catches the eye. Aged-iron rods drape over beautiful opal glass to create this industrial-esque fixture, delivering a sculptural quality to its functionality. The opal glass creates a brilliant glow when lit, making it an exceptional lighting option for an outdoor space. Approved for use in outdoor areas. Additional pipe available (PIPE-420)

A stylish and elegant pairing of geometric inspiration and transitional design come together in this pendant. Two linear squares of steel encase a demi-globe of opal glass, which casts a warm glow throughout a space. The frame has a classic bronze finish. Additional pipe available (PIPE-105). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Svelte. Sleek. Sophisticated. This large-scale pendant brings romantic and moody light to a space while showcasing its own curvy and sultry style. It's built with two layers; the interior form is made of naturally finished woven rattan slats on a metal frame and the outer shade is woven with rattan core strips that are finished in black. The top flair has an organic, wavy edge, recalling the look of a pomegranate or vintage dress form. Additional pipe available (PIPE-101).

Nature takes the luminary lead with this bamboo pendant. Stalks of bamboo are sliced and then bound together by hand with thin pieces of rattan to create the open-frame conical shade. An antique black wash finishes the bamboo, delivering a modern aesthetic to its natural form. Perfect for rustic spaces in need of a little extra texture and a lot of extra light. Additional pipe available (PIPE-416).

This unique pendant reimagines the traditional Chinese lantern in a more modern, abstract perspective. It is crafted from bent strips of resilient bamboo, mounted to the rattan frame in two layers to create depth and filter the glow even further. Adding to the modern look is a black painted finish throughout that makes it stand out in the daylight. The light that comes through the bamboo strips casts wonderful shadows around the room. Additional pipe available (PIPE-101).

Drawing inspiration from the beauty in natural materials, this pendant is a muse for organic design. Blending the rich textures of strung coconut shells with the modern silhouette, this light fixture exudes an exotic, yet botanical look. Each shell is dyed in rich black, individually cut and hand-strung onto a wire frame. It's finished with wide hoop links that are wrapped in smaller coconut beads, dyed to complement the shade. Additional chain available CHN-989.

This playfully named hi & low adjustable pendant is artfully weighted with a solid egg that allows you to hang the metal hooded light at any height. Finished in dull bronzes and antiqued brass tones, the Egg Drop Pendant also works high or low in terms of formality. So incredibly versatile, Barry suggests using it over a counter or in pairs over a long table, left and right of a bed or sofa, and as a task light over a desk or work table to conserve surface space. Just a great light!

Equal parts classic and dramatic, this versatile light fixture delivers form & function in one supple curve. The streamlined dome design features an outer matte black surface while the interior features a brilliant gold metallic semi-matte finish. Though a stand-out fixture on its own, it makes an even bigger impact when grouped with the complementary shapes and tones in the Pascal, Patton and Ponce Pendant Collections. Additional pipe available PIPE-101.

Equal parts classic and dramatic, this over-scaled light fixture delivers form & function in grand scale. The streamlined dome design features an outer matte black surface while the interior of features a brilliant gold metallic semi-matte finish. Though a stand-out fixture on its own, it makes an even bigger presentation when grouped with the complementary shapes and tones in the Pascal, Patton and Ponce Pendant Collections. Additional pipe available (PIPE-101).

A bold style statement, this hand-hammered iron drum shade pendant is in a richly weathered bronze finish both on exterior and interior. It features a double diffuser suspended from within and a perforated metal bottom allowing light to illuminate playfully beneath. Suspends from matching pipe stem and illuminates three standard bulbs. Also available in small (42466). Additional pipe available PIPE-188.

Equal parts classic and dramatic, this versatile light fixture delivers form & function in one supple curve. The streamlined dome design features an outer matte black surface while the interior features a brilliant gold metallic semi-matte finish. Though a stand-out fixture on its own, it makes an even bigger impact when grouped with the complementary shapes and tones in the Pascal, Patton and Ponce Pendant Collections. Additional pipe available (PIPE-101).

3-light hand hammered iron drum shade pendant in a bronze finish both on exterior and interior, features a double diffuser suspended from within. Perforated metal bottom allows light to illuminate and suspends from matching linked chain. Additional chain available CHN-946.

A tube of perforated antique brass-finished steel with bronze framing, Keenan industrializes a modular silhouette, all hung from a matching bronze pipe. Creates instant shadow play. Additional pipe available (PIPE-105). Also available in brushed nickel (49121). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

It's easy to imagine a cluster of these hanging in an isolated bedouin tent in the desert. While its design origins might be based in far off locales, the Terrene pendant lights the way in any modern setting. The blown, sculpted glass orb features a subtle quilting pattern that is enhanced by the smoke luster finish. The polished brass chain adds more detail to this pendant. Additional chain available (CHN-153).

Inspired by the success of Zanadoo, this three-light pendant features a perforated metal diffuser at both the top and bottom. The spikes clustered at the top and bottom are finished in antique brass to contrast with the bronze finish on the drum. The result is unexpected and subtle. Additional chain available CHN-971.

Handwoven, rattan wicker is just as Caribbean in its style as it is sophisticated. The outer trim is made of natural rattan, surrounding a rounded plate of frosted acrylic, so the light that is cast is warm and filtered. The stem is crafted from stainless steel, finished in a warm antique brass that pairs well with the elevated look. Four fittings hold standard size bulbs. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Perfectly playful, Celerie Kemble's Parasol series is the epitome of coastal cool. Staggered in size, the shades and mount are made of natural handwoven rattan; the shades feature a scallop edge while the base conceals a steel plate. The stem is crafted from stainless steel, finished in an antique brass that elevates the look. Each tier has fittings to hold three candelabra bulbs. Also comes in a large pendant (DC49011) and small pendant (DC49012). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas

Like a magnetic field surrounding the central lantern, almost 100 strips of upholstered banding are made to create each of these pendants. The bands are made of a super pliable material and simple beige cotton, the lantern from white cotton and the fixture suspends from a stainless steel stem finished in a warm antique brass. The filtered light comes from a single bulb, casting a wonderful glow and soft, linear shadows. Additional pipe available (PIPE-101).
Kay Pendant

Perfectly playful, Celerie Kemble's Parasol series is the epitome of coastal cool. The shade and mount are made of natural handwoven rattan; the shade featuring an exaggerated scallop edge while the base conceals a steel plate. The stem is crafted from stainless steel, finished in a warm antique brass that pairs well with the elevated look. Three fittings hold standard size bulbs. Also comes in a small size (DC49012) and tiered pendant (DC49013). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Brown nickel and smoked glass create a the masculine yet refined Kayla Pendant. Its smoke glass shade, enveloping the opal glass globe, makes Kayla perfect for above-bar placement. Additional pipe available (PIPE-103). Also available in antique brass with clear glass (49158). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

A smoke glass shade fits perfectly into the brown nickel base in one continuous, oval, bulb-inspired Germaine Pendant. Glass and familiar curves create a warm, familiar design with a touch of curiousity. Shown with a 4" frosted globe bulb. Also available in antique brass and opal glass (49052). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Additonal pipe available (PIPE-103).
Louisa Pendant

Perfectly playful, Celerie Kemble's Parasol series is the epitome of coastal cool. The shade and mount are both made of natural handwoven rattan; the shade featuring an exaggerated scallop edge while the base conceals a steel plate. The stem is crafted from stainless steel, finished in a warm antique brass that pairs well with the elevated look. Three fittings hold candelabra bulbs.

A mix of contemporary shape and organic materials. This hanging 6-light pendant is made of grey-washed wood carved in imperfect, undulating circles. Each of the concentric circles appears to float, but they are secure with filament wire. This is a natural element in a beach house over a driftwood dining table. Shown with small nostalgic loop bulbs. Additional chain available CHN-101.

This one-light glass pendant has a taupe cloth cord and a simple round antique brass canopy. The irregularly shaped glass is a beautiful smoky color with a luster finish that creates a warm glow when lit, making it a great powder room fixture. Finish may vary. Shown with an antique large tubular bulb.

Opaque opulence is brought to life with the Geraldine Pendant. The glass sphere features a beautiful etched pattern, made even more curious with the frosted tobacco finish. Table lamp (17124-144) also available. Finish may vary.

Laura Kirar hit a grand slam when she designed the Caviar lighting collection. This is the medium sized 1 light brown nickel pendant with smoked glass globe. It is also available in 2 other finishes…DK49911 polished nickel and DK49927 Rose gold.

Rectangular 4-light pendant is constructed of iron in an bronze finish and clear glass body with two metal pipe extensions. Consider an antique style bulb to create a subtle glow while featuring various filament designs. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

This pendant is a great example of how concentric circles can influence product design. These hand-carved undulating wood circles are arranged to create a contemporary open sphere finished in a gray-wash. While appearing to float around the single light, these hoops are secured with filament wire. This is a natural element in a beach house. Shown with a nostalgic thread bulb. Additional chain available CHN-101.

Laura Kirar hit a grand slam when she designed the Caviar lighting collection. This is the large size 1 light brown nickel pendant with smoked glass globe. It is also available in 2 other finishes…DK49913 polished nickel and DK49928 Rose gold.
Hammered pot bellied iron pendent with dark bronze finish and silver mesh fabric cord.

This one-light glass pendant has a taupe cloth cord and a simple round vintage brass canopy. The glass is a beautiful smoky color with a luster finish that creates a warm glow when lit, making it a great powder room fixture. Taupe cloth cord. Shown with a Nostalgic thread bulb.

A spin off of Noreen, this one-light glass pendant has a vintage brass pipe and canopy. The glass is a beautiful smoky color with a luster finish that creates a warm glow when lit, making it a great powder room fixture. Glass finish will vary. Shown with an edison bulb. Additional pipe available PIPE-137.

Classic, mid-century elegance is revitalized with this polished pendant. Five bulbs brilliantly light up the upend off-white linen shade, while two are neatly concealed within the top of the pendant body. An exposed detailing on the heritage brass steel frame peeks from under the shade, adding a textured element to its otherwise smooth surface. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Additional pipe available (PIPE-172).

Frank Ponterio drew inspiration from classic Roman architecture and design to inform his debut collection. Natural rope and an organic silhouette would make this pendant right at home in the storied gardens of Rome. Suspended from an intriguing combination of natural iron piping and hook closures, a nod to old world craftsmanship. Additional pipe available (PIPE-417).

For centuries, craftsman have used rattan to create works of art—this pendant following suit. The cage pattern is made using thinly sliced rattan stalks that are shaped by hand, then painted with a dark brown stain for a decadent but natural touch. Suspended from an antique brass steel pipe, the open-form of the design allows light to flow freely and abundantly. Finish may vary. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Additional pipe available (PIPE-101).

Create a unique lighting environment without compromising class. The tiered silhouette of the pendant features opal glass fashioned with an aged-brass finish steel belt, forging a classic and clean style. The diamond-esque shape allows light to flow over any outdoor setup. Approved for use in outdoor areas. Additional pipe available (PIPE-418)

Light a space with sui generis style. Reminiscent of Yayoi Kusama's pop art of the 1960s, this stainless steel globe is finished in bronze and is adorned with clear crystal orbs—lending a retro vibe to its modish form. An innovative light solution for contemporary spaces. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Additional pipe available (PIPE-178).

The contemporary form of this outdoor pendant is striking and catches the eye. Aged-brass rods drape over beautiful opal glass to create this industrial-esque fixture, delivering a sculptural quality to its functionality. The opal glass creates a brilliant glow when lit, making it an exceptional lighting option for an outdoor space. Approved for use in outdoor areas. Additional pipe available (PIPE-418)

When it comes to contemporary lighting design, this pendant is top notch. A quarter-inch steel plate is seated on a sleek steel pipe above a pendulum-style point. Finished in heritage brass and bronze, a beaded texture has been applied to the circumference of the circular form, mimicking a flame-cut edge that is softly illuminated by the lucency of the LED light. A functional focal point for modern spaces. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Additional pipe available (PIPE-172).

Inherently vibrant, this version of the Zanadoo pendant is an outdoor friendly version of one of our most iconic designs. In this design, the modern starburst design is concealed in an aged brass steel frame and clear glass panels. Approved for use in outdoor areas. Additional pipe available (PIPE-192). Also available in Aged Iron (49225).

The depths of spatial design are defined with the Volta Pendant. A smoke glass globe is suspended by a steel pipe finished in heritage brass that encompasses it in free-form fashion. The simple geometric silhouette of the circumambient façade creates a visual of a floating orb, delivering a dimensional dynamic to a space. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Additional pipe available (PIPE-172).

The mid-century craftsman style of this pendant light makes it intriguing and modern, while its grand scale gives it presence. The steel frame is almost sculptural, featuring a linear pattern that is hammered and finished in aged brass, adding to the mid-century modern feel. It conceals a sleeve of opal glass that filters the light from three bulbs, so the light it emits spreads warmly outward and openly downward. Additional chain (CHN-194) available. Approved for outdoor use.

The traditional hourglass shape gets a modern revamp in this contemporary drop pendant. The glow comes from the opal glass shade, which conceals two bulbs—one up and one down—to cast ample, warm light throughout a space. Its linear style is what makes it so modern, though the aged brass finished steel accents also lend an updated look, too. Approved for use in outdoor areas. Additional pipe available PIPE-194. Also available in Aged Iron (49228).

Rebelling from standard, lackluster outdoor lighting, this fixture brings artistic flair into natural environments. The shape is an inspiration of mid-century design, taking a classic indoor design and reinterpreting it for stylish outdoor spaces. The dome light is crafted from opal glass and the structure from aged brass finish steel. The exposed finial contrasts the shade in an antique brass finish. Additional pipe available (PIPE-192). Approved for use in outdoor areas.

This handsomely structured lantern is upscale in form and style. It is made from aged brass finished steel, tapered in form, and designed with slight, exposed details and contrasting antique brass finish accents to exude an industrial feel. A sleeve of opaque opal glass rests inside, filtering the light from a standard bulb. Additional chain available (CHN-192). Approved for use in outdoor areas.

Light a space with timeless design. This classic globe pendant features a clear glass shade and aged brass finished steel, giving it an updated, industrial style. Consider an antique style bulb to create a subtle glow with stylized filament designs. Shown with an Edison bulb. Also comes in Large Aged Brass (49208), Large Aged Iron (49207) and Small Aged Iron (49210). Additional pipe available (PIPE-192). Approved for use in outdoor areas.

Light a space with timeless design. This classic globe pendant features a clear glass shade and aged brass finished steel, giving it an updated, industrial style. Consider an antique style bulb to create a subtle glow with stylized filament designs. Shown with an Edison bulb. Also comes in Large Aged Iron (49207), Small Aged Iron (49210) and Small Aged Brass (49211). Additional pipe available (PIPE-192). Approved for use in outdoor areas.

Organic yet modern, this piece shows off naturally good looks in a mid-century saucer shape. To get the layered design, craftsmen first hand-forge the metal frame to its unique shape. Then, they take double strands of natural wicker and weave the designs by hand, including the criss-cross detail which helps offer more light in a space. The finished piece features iron accents in an antique brass finish. Imagine several in line above an island or a bar. Additional chain (CHN-198) available.

Both organic and modern in feel, this piece shows off naturally good looks in a slender form from a taupe cloth cord. To get the layered design, craftsmen first hand-forge the metal frame to its unique drop shape. Then, they take double strands of natural wicker and weave the neck and dome designs; the first is a free-form open-weave and the latter has a wavy pattern. Imagine several in line above an island or clustered as a brilliant entryway light.

You can find this undulated barrel shape throughout the natural world, from sea urchins in the Pacific to barrel cactuses in the desert. This ubiquitous silhouette was the inspiration behind the Pismo Pendant, which is crafted entirely from thin, hand-woven natural raffia on a metal frame. We've added our unique interpretation with antique-brass finished accents, adding a twist of modern style to its organic aesthetic. Additional pipe available (PIPE-101).

Inspired by natural materials, this pendant blends the rich textures of strung coconut beads with the modern silhouette of an oversized lantern, exuding an exotic, yet cosmopolitan persona. Each bead is naturally finished, individually cut and hand -strung into knots, recalling an open crochet pattern that allows light to peek slightly from the shade. It’s finished with wide hoop links that are wrapped in smaller coconut shell beads to complement the shade. Additional chain available CHN-989.

Equal parts classic and dramatic, this versatile light fixture delivers form & function in one supple curve. The streamlined dome design features an outer matte taupe surface while the interior of the dome features a brilliant silver metallic semi-matte finish. Though a stand-out fixture on its own, it makes an even bigger impact when grouped with the complementary shapes and tones in the Pascal, Patton and Ponce Pendant Collections. Additional pipe available (PIPE-101).

Thick crystal, sculpted into an optical globe, creates the extraordinary shade of this pendant lamp. The center is carved out to fit a single light, which is concealed in its frosted texture, giving the light a filtered glow. It’s accented with a band of stainless steel, which matches the stem in an antique brass finish. Additional pipe available (PIPE-180). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.
Clear glass ribbed dome pendant with natural jute rope. Display alone or in multiples.

A clear seedy dome layers with one of frosted glass for a refracted effect in Jenna. Hung from an antique brass pipe. A striking and elegant blend of materials and finishes. Additional pipe available (PIPE-160). Also available in smoke luster glass (42247). Finish may vary.

Updated cone shaped pendent with clear glass shade and polished nickel accents. Industrial styled silver mesh fabric wrapped cord. Consider an antique style bulb to create a subtle glow while featuring various filament designs. Shown with an Edison bulb.

This etched pendant brings a touch of elegance to a simple form. Lends itself to any area of the home and the etching varies from inspiration that is both Indian and Asian and provides a touch of flora and fauna, with etched glass and antique brass accents. Shown with an Edison bulb. Additional chain CHN-991.

Inspired by vintage lanterns of the early 20th century, the Natasha Pendant has given the form updated style. Clear, hand-blown glass is crafted with wonderfully modern curves, hanging from an antique-brass finished stainless steel stem. Shown with a radio bulb. Also available in smoky teal glass (47441). Additional pipe available (PIPE-101). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

The glass for this one-light pendant has been mouth blown with sand and metals to create the lightly colored texture. Hang over the nightstands in your guest room instead of using lamps or in multiples over your bar. Taupe cloth cord. Shown with a Nostalgic thread bulb.

Laura Kirar hit a grand slam when she designed the Caviar lighting collection. This is the largest 1 light polished nickel pendant with clear glass globe. It is also available in 2 other finishes…DK49914 brown nickel and DK49928 Rose gold.
This clear glass hand faceted cylinder pendant with one light was designed by Laura Kirar. The solid brass fitting was inspired by a vintage pendant. Available in a smaller size DK42050.

Laura Kirar hit a grand slam when she designed the Caviar lighting collection. This is the small 1 light polished nickel pendant with clear glass globe. It is also available in 2 other finishes…DK49910 brown nickel and DK49926 Rose gold.
Modern 4-light oval pendant with multiple clear glass rods that drape over a pair of polished nickel frames.

This seven light horizontal Caviar fixture, designed by Laura Kirar, is finished in polished nickel. The irregular staggered placement of the 10" clear glass spheres is exactly what the designer wanted…something a bit lyrical.
Molded clear glass sphere pendant cinched with an antique brass belt. Shown with Medium Clear Tubular Bulb.

Hexagonal shaped glass pendant with antique brass finished iron “came” strips between each triangular glass shape. Consider an antique style bulb to create a subtle glow while featuring various filament designs.

Laura Kirar hit a grand slam when she designed the Caviar lighting collection. This is the medium sized 1 light polished nickel pendant with clear glass globe. It is also available in 2 other finishes…DK49912 brown nickel and DK49927 Rose gold.

This iron, mid-century-inspired, four-light vintage brass-finished pendant is the perfect light to hang over a dining table. The dark, bronze, floating band adds contrast and dimensionality to the simple elegant design. A tri-chain mount blends seamlessly with the metallic finish. Additional chain available CHN-885.
Seeded glass cylinder shaped pendent with irregular edges and features dots of bubbles in the glass. Display alone or in multiples. Taupe fabric cord. Glass will vary in shape & size.
Molded clear glass cylinder cinched with antique brass. Shown with antique tubular bulb.

Perhaps Barry's favorite piece in this new collection, the Cloud Pendant rains three seedy glass orbs of light from a carved, antiqued gold leaf-finished cloud-like canopy that mounts onto the ceiling as a sculpture. Glamorously magical, this dynami c fixture lends Asian elan and clean geometric from to any interior, modern or traditional. Use it in any room of a home. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Finish may vary.

Estelle is a gleaming example of the latest renaissance in industrial design. The steel hanging stem holds a cone matching in finish in an antique brass. The crystal facet beneath acts as a diffuser, creating stunning prisms of light that soften the overall design. Additional pipe available (PIPE-178). Also available as a matching sconce (49167) and blackened bronze chandelier (89700). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

So simple and so modern, this is a pendant that fits in anywhere. Clean lines, crafted from stainless steel, frame plates of frosted glass, so the light beneath is filtered beautifully. The bottom plate is hand-punched and casts scattered light downward—it’s also removable for easy bulb replacement. The warm brass tones are thanks to a brushed, antique brass finish that runs all the way up to the flush mount. Fits a standard bulb size.

Lovely for indoors or out, this handsome lantern pendant is upscale in form and style. It is made from stainless steel and rods of iron are seamlessly welded to create the rounded petal design. It’s completely finished in antique brass, even the matching hanging chain and ceiling mount. A sheath of opaque opal glass rests inside, filtering the light from a standard bulb. Additional chain available (CHN-149). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Clean, subdued and timeless, the London Pendant's opal glass cylindrical shade is caged by antique brass-finished steel framing and finished off with a delicate matching finial detail. Additional pipe available (PIPE-101). Also available in vintage silver (42161). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Modern and calm are two things that immediately come to mind when experiencing the soft light and matching design of the Jannah Pendant. Jannah's antique brass dome is completed with a part frosted, part clear crystal diffuser. Additional pipe available (PIPE-174). Also available in vintage silver (49159). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.
Katya Sconce

This five-light chandelier features a stunning arrangement of gently-curved plates, embossed with a leaf motif and finished in vintage brass. This gilded piece has a traditional and feminine feel that won't overpower a streamlined space. A frosted acrylic diffuser softens the light. Additional pipe available (PIPE-159). Also available in small (42252) and two-tiered (84310).

Antique brass and glass create a the masculine yet refined Kayla Pendant. Its clear glass shade, enveloping the opal glass globe, makes Kayla perfect for above-bar placement. Additional pipe available (PIPE-101). Also available in brown nickel with smoke glass (49129). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Simple but dramatic, the mirrored polished brass dome of this sleek fixture could be interpreted as a temple dome or a spaceship. The perforated openings on the body that encircle the base create a fantastic chain of light on the surface of walls and ceiling, while the open base sheds light directly on any surface below. Additional pipe available (PIPE-101). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

A singular take on the popular Ramirez Chandelier. The Ramirez Pendant is highlighted by its organically-curved, opal glass shade, exuding classic elegance with its antique brass-finished steel cap. Additional pipe available (PIPE-110). Also available in vintage silver (49155). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Abstracted from Chinese carvings and porcelains, our elegant Iris lantern-like pendant celebrates this symbol for happiness on all 4 sides. In antique brass and off-white linen. Barry suggests using this alone or in multiples of matching or varying heights. Additional pipe available (PIPE-132). Also available as sconce (DS49008). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.
Leo Pendant

Delicate in stature, the brass Edith Pendant is reminiscent of a rose bud in bloom. The ethereal design is finished in a light vintage brass and would be perfect for a dressing room or hallway. Shown with a nostalgic loop bulb. Additional pipe available (PIPE-144).

This six-light steel chandelier features a three-tier design and antique brass finish, elements that draw inspiration from Art Deco motifs. A frosted acrylic diffuser tops each bowl, softening the light and making it thoroughly modern. Additional pipe available (PIPE 101).

This glossy white, mid-century-inspired, one-light brass pendant is the perfect light to hang over your dining table. The polished brass floating band adds contrast and dimensionality to the simple elegant design.?Interior highlighted by brushed and polished brass finishes. Also available in vintage brass/bronze (44077). Additional chain available (CHN-142). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.
Zanadoo Mini Chandelier
Kimberly Pendant

Individual iron rods are welded together and hand-finished with gold leaf to create this striking three-light pendant. Rustic but elegant. Part of the Prescott collection of mirrors and sconces. Additional chain available CHN-886.
Handcrafted pendant with rustic diamond shaped antique gold finish leaves are pieced together to form a dome. Additional chain available CHN-973.
This three light design by Laura Kirar is made of distressed mercury glass which has been dressed in antique brass chainmail and hung from five antique brass chains. Finish may vary.

This iron, mid-century-inspired, one-light vintage brass-finished pendant is the perfect light to hang over your dining table. The dark bronze floating band adds contrast and dimensionality to the simple elegant design. Additional chain available CHN-885.

Cascading swags of fine brass chain in antique brass and nickel finishes make this chandelier a dramatic addition to any space. The uneven ends of the delicate chains add to the decadent elegance. Each piece is handmade and will feature slightly different chain placement as well as varying finishes. Shown with Nostalgic spiral radio bulbs. Additional chain available (CHN-942).
Clear glass mini pendant covered with chain mail mesh in antique brass finish.

Bell shaped polished brass pendant with wire extension. Copper plated interior enhances the illumination offering a warm and intimate glow. Perfect for kitchen island lighting or restaurant bar lighting.

Geometrics are a big trend in fashion, just as they are for interiors. This open caged pendant is the perfect example of just how stylish pentagons can be. Made of polished brass plated stainless steel, this design makes great shadows on the wall and ceiling. Additional pipe available PIPE-123. Shown with an Edison bulb.

Find the elegance in simplicity with this luxurious drop pendant. The rounded shade is crafted from thick glass with finely cut details. The wide channels cut into the glass brilliantly cast the light, while also adding a more elevated look to its classic style. It hangs from an iron frame in an antique brass finish, with a cross mount that holds the glass shade-a detail we think also acts as a nice accent. Additional pipe available (PIPE-199).

Find the elegance in simplicity with this luxurious drop pendant. The teardrop shade is crafted from thick glass with finely cut details. The wide channels cut into the glass brilliantly cast the light, while also adding a more elevated look to its classic style. It hangs from an iron frame in an antique brass finish, with a cross mount that holds the glass shade-a detail we think also acts as a nice accent. Additional pipe available (PIPE-199).

Traditional materials take on classic geometric shapes to create this modern marvel. A single light extends from a brass pipe with an antiqued finish into a clear, seedy glass shade, that when lit accentuates the bubbled texture and softly illuminates a room. This large-scale piece is a great focal point for modern dining settings or casual contemporary spaces. Variances in glass may occur. Additional pipe available (PIPE-431).

The saucer shape that forms each of the three tiers in this pendant is an early mid-century modern inspiration. The saucers are made of hand-blown glass, which are each richly filled with seeded texture, and suspended on a gold-leafed iron pipe. The top saucer holds all the light with three bulbs. Due to its tapered silhouette and size variance, it's an ideal light for virtually any space. Additional pipe available (PIPE-195).

Traditional materials take on classic geometric shapes to create this modern marvel. A single light extends from a brass pipe with an antiqued finish into a clear, seedy glass globe, that when lit accentuates the bubbled texture and softly illuminates a room. This large-scale piece is a great focal point for modern dining settings or casual contemporary spaces. Variances in glass may occur. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Additional pipe available (PIPE-431).

So stately, this pendant is the ultimate sophisticate. A polished brass structure holds a large sleeve of clear glass, framed in real walnut wood. The blend of warm brass and dark finished wood is what gives this fixture its signature level of elegance. An exposed bulb becomes the center of attention, perfect for an Edison bulb or other decorative bulb. Also available as a ceiling mount light (DC42009).

Jadestone inspired by an 8th century emperor's sceptre, this whimsical sconce, finished in antiqued gold leaf, is at once organic and glamorous. A statement piece for any room. Topped with a white microfiber tapered shade. Also available in left sconce (DD49010). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Finish may vary.

From table lamp to floor lamp, pendant to chandelier, the Sabine family continues to evolve with the Sabine Vanity Light. Three opal glass tear drops hang from an antique brass backplate, featuring matching brass details. Also available in vintage silver (49154). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

The Hampton Sconce is already a popular bath lighting choice, now the Hampton Vanity Light takes it to the next level. Delicate antique brass rings fall playfully around its frosted glass shades, tripled and mounted on a matching antique brass backplate. Also available in vintage silver (49152). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

The Arteriors bath collection is complete with the Jalen Vanity Light. An updated take on the popular Jalen chandelier and sconce designs, this five-light design features five antique brass circles extending from a matching backplate. Each circle is finished with a frosted glass diffuser, creating ideal soft light. Also available in vintage silver (49148). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

A steel back plate and center spear finished in antique brass serve as the anchor on this unique sconce design. Two pairs of symmetrical discs are finished in oil-rubbed bronze. Frosted glass diffusers add a lightness to the piece. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

The Gibbons Sconce is a curvaceous, modular marriage of form and finish. Gibbons features a modular brass body, finished in hammered vintage brass.
