It is made with absolute precision, with seamless welding, intricately applied gold leaf and naturally formed texture throughout. It really is a grand piece, reaching over two feet high and resting on a solid block of white marble. Marble may vary.
This playful iron sculpture finished in antique nickel captures the essence of the game. The large size also works well as a door stop.

Deliver an artistic narrative to a tablescape with this interpretive sculpture. Resin is sculpted into intertwining vine-like pieces to create an abstract work of art. The writhed objects are free in form and are finished in antique gold for an elevated look. Finish may vary.

One continuous band of aluminum crosses over and under itself in this interpretive art piece. It’s stunning. It’s abstract. It’s brilliant; finished in antique brass to reflect elegance and shine, free in form with no base. When incorporated into a spread of collected objets d’arts, the look is transformative, lending a modern edge and artistic narrative.

One continuous band of aluminum crosses over and under itself in this interpretive art piece. It’s stunning. It’s abstract. It’s brilliant; finished with hand-applied gold leaf to reflect elegance and shine. When incorporated into a spread of collected objets d’arts, the look is transformative, lending a modern edge and artistic narrative. It’s mounted on a bronze-finished metal base. Finish may vary.

This sculpture gives the phrase “band of gold” a whole new meaning. Traditionally, rings symbolize eternity, and in this art piece we foresee a lifetime of brilliance and beauty. Forged iron is first crafted into shape, then delicate gold leaf is applied to the entire band. Dually mounted on stacked slabs of natural iron to keep it well grounded and elevated. Gold leaf finish may vary.

This contemporary sculpture is playful in its simplicity, yet deceivingly complex with variations in shape, color, depth and height. Perhaps an exploration of diversity or simply as a piece to admire, it exudes sophistication in its blend of polished nickel, pale brass and antique brass tones. Each is mounted firmly in a platform of black marble cut 1.5 inches thick. Metal finishes, marble tone and grain may vary.

Simple, yet so sophisticated, this modern art piece adds that little bit of sparkle that every space needs. A thick, seeded crystal disk rests majestically atop a golden-hued throne. The antique brass finish of the metal base complements the crystal, adding to its splendor. Also available in a small size (9535).
Fit for a flawless selfie, Kingston is perfectly unassuming. The antique brass finish and petite scale are versatile elements that offer a swift transition from coffee table, to console, to desk.

Sculptural art is demonstrated with this truly unique work of art. The abstract form of this modernist sculpture takes shape in faux marble, which is exhibited on a clear crystal base that has been beveled for a more textured look. An elegant yet expressive showpiece that will enhance your contemporary décor.

Revive your coastal décor with one of the sea's lost treasures. This ammonite-shaped sculpture is composed of faux marble, which creates a desired textured façade, and is showcased on a clear crystal base with beveled edges. A maritime objet d'art for any space. Finish may vary.

Like geometric pillars, these sculptures add a bit of modern sophistication to a table, desk or shelf. The ivory finish makes them almost identical to marble, with even, prism surfaces and clean lines with modern class. They provide form or function, whether as bookends and paperweights or simply as decorative accents to elevate a look.

This accent piece is simple and modern with both form and function on its side. It is a nod to the grand pieces once found in turn-of-the-century gardens, scaled down to fit perfectly on a desk or table for functional or purely decorative purposes. It pairs ideally with the Marietta Urn (9567) and Miranda Urn (9566).

This sleek and slender vase would work wonderfully layered on an entryway table or flanking a console. The aluminum form has subtle curves and a vintage silver finish that gives it a moody, romantic brilliance. It’s quite tall too, making it ideal to set in a space that reaches extreme heights–set it with the complementary Ryan Vase and Regan Vase to stage a dramatic scene.

Simple, yet so sophisticated, this modern art piece adds that little bit of sparkle that every space needs. A thick, seeded crystal disk rests majestically atop a golden-hued throne. The antique brass finish of the metal base complements the crystal, adding to its splendor. Also available in a large size (9534).

With all its shine and gloss, this centerpiece will catch the eye of many an admirer. Eighth-inch glass is given extra shine with a silver leaf antiqued finish and trails of etched leaf designs in a warm bronze tone. Rests on a natural iron disk base. For decorative use only. Finish may vary.
Boat shaped hammered brass bowl in polished nickel becomes a centerpiece or sculptural piece.
Naturally inspired driftwood abstract bowl serves as sculpture or centerpiece. Size may vary up to 10".

The etched gold doors of this bar cabinet add a little bit of chic to any room. Open the doors to reveal an ebony stained interior, mirrored walls, recessed light, and a spot for your best liquor. Suddenly you're everyone's best friend!

The likeness in this mammoth coastal centerpiece is uncanny. Think of it as a sculptural trompe l’oeil, a work of magic that tricks the senses into its manmade wonder. To the touch, rich textures recall what would’ve been hundreds of years of sculpting in the making; to the eye, a hand-painted marbled finish replicates aging so convincing, you may think it was plucked directly from the waters. But don’t be fooled, this piece is a replica—leave the real thing in its underwater habitat.
Reminiscent of the graceful stiletto of a mosquito's leg, this piece works well as extra seating in a large room or at the foot of a bed. Natural iron legs with natural linen seats.

Linkka showcases our new heritage brass finish, a warm tone with vintage appeal. The sharp angles of the arms create graphic movement that is softened by the opal glass globes. Also available in vintage silver (49160). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

So simple and so modern, this is a sconce that fits in anywhere. Clean lines, crafted from stainless steel, frame cubes of smoked glass, so the light is filtered beautifully. The warm metal tones are thanks to a brushed, brown nickel finish that covers the piece. It mounts flush to the wall, so the look is clean and sleek. Fits two candelabra bulbs. Also available in dark vintage silver (49103) and antique brass (49104). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

The versatility in this four piece table is unmatched. Keep them close together for a tight fit or pull them apart for more space when entertaining. Style books and accessories on the bottom to finish off the piece. Featuring ebony stained oak with a cerused gray interior.

This sultry trio makes a dramatic statement for a tabletop or bar cart. Together they create a trifecta, if you will, of color, shape and height. Each is blown with optic glass, which is what gives them an alluring, twisted banding, and the neutral color palette of amber, smoke and amethyst is a moody take on a range of pastels. Elevate barware or simply display them to establish a bit of sophistication. Finish may vary.

ItemName: Duran Chair Pebble Tweed Black Cerused
ItemDescription: The Duran Chair is simple, elegant and strong. The deep seat is complemented by a curved shelter frame featuring a beautifully cerused black wood. Covered in Pebble Tweed.

This ebony stained cabinet is a stunner. From exaggerated diamond-shaped legs to contrasting finishes, every detail has been considered. The cerused gray interior adds a subtle softness that complements the solid oak frame. Gold hardware adds a touch of glamour.

A simple, delicate, and geometric two-light sconce is perfect for small spaces that need a little extra light. The hammered?bronze finish adds a contemporary touch to its iron base. Also available in white (42235), vintage brass (42237), and natural iron with brass welds (42238). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Part starburst, part shield, the carved wood Clifton Sconce is a lesson in dramatic craftsmanship. Evokes a sense of protection and strength with its shield-like form, but also sets a tranquil, calm tone with its warm and light shadows. A unique blend of pickled walnut wood and iron.

A perfect balance of proportions, this double sconce sets smoke glass globes against brown nickel-finished arms and the back plate. It’s an eclectic element for modern settings and can be horizontally or vertically mounted. The two-light sconce is shown with small tubular bulbs. Damp rated: Approved for use in covered outdoor areas or bathrooms.

A traditional style gets an exotic twist with woven rattan. The sconce is crafted from iron, finished in matte black for a look that’s elevated and elegant. The two stems, which hold four lamps, are wrapped in woven rattan, lending warmth and an organic sophistication. Each lamp is topped with a black cotton tapered shade and is fitted for a standard candelabra bulb.

Vintage meets modern with the Waits Outdoor Sconce. This two-light fixture combines steel with an aged-iron finish and opal glass to create a contemporary yet timeless design. For a more dynamic look and a little more luster, consider pairing this piece with another. Approved for use in outdoor areas.

So contemporary, so modern—so stunning. Celestial in nature, this sconce is crafted from brass and finished in a matte bronze finish, contrasted with a polished brass orb on the stem. Inspired by the night sky, the cone shade features meticulous perforations that cast a subtle glow outwards. Also available as a floor lamp (DC72000).

A modest lighting solution for exterior spaces that illuminates its surroundings while delivering a contemporary look to a space. Aged-iron and frosted glass unite to create the unobtrusive profile of this outdoor sconce. The slightly tapered shape of the shade works to softly scintillate the light across a patio or porch. Approved for use in outdoor areas.

Handcrafted details, like etched trim and hammered textures, make this striking sconce a botanical wonder. Made from iron and finished in a deep bronze polish, the broad, tropical leaf design conceals five tubular or candelabra bulbs, so it casts a vibrant glow upward. Inside the five bulb shades, a polished, copper finish adds shine and even more light. A back mount is almost completely hidden by the design.

Made entirely from iron from stem to petal, it is finished in a deep bronze polish for added mystery. Inside the six bulb shades, a polished, copper finish adds shine and reflective light. The surprise is at the flick of a switch; hand-punched details in the six lampshades cast dots of light that scatter around the room. At over two feet tall, this light is impactful and so brilliant. Seamlessly designed center mount keeps it secure.

The mid-century craftsman style of this sconce makes it intriguing, modern and artistic. The steel frame is almost sculptural, featuring a linear pattern that is hammered and finished in aged iron, adding to the mid-century modern feel. It conceals a sheet of opal glass that filters the light from two bulbs, so the light it emits spreads warmly outward. Also available in aged brass (49182). Approved for outdoor use.

The minimalist frosted glass and bronze design of the Stefan sconce triples for?this above-mirror vanity light. Mounted on a vintage silver backplate with frosted glass shades to create soft, welcoming light. The Stefan Vanity Light completes the already-popular Stefan Sconce's entry in the bath. Also available in antique brass (49149). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Single arm sconce with square tubing and a square steel back plate. Antique bronze finish with a clear glass cylinder shade houses a single light. These are perfect for flanking a mirror. Shown with an Edison bulb. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

The minimalist frosted glass and bronze design of the Stefan sconce triples for this above-mirror vanity light. Mounted on an antique brass backplate with frosted glass shades to create soft, welcoming light. The Stefan Vanity Light completes the already-popular Stefan Sconce's entry in the bath. Also available in vintage silver (49150). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Depending on the bulbs, the three-light Logan can either be a harsh, industrial masterpiece or callback to old Hollywood glam. Features a two-tiered natural iron base. With the gold globe bulbs shown here, the iron layers create an instantly arresting glow, with the light projecting outward, while also providing a mute reflection to the lower tier. Also available as a round sconce (42222). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Elevate a wall space to museum status with this unrivaled luminescent. A thick, clear seedy slump glass seems to float effortlessly between a slender antique brass steel frame. The hand-etched edges deliver a textural quality to a blank wall space, while the translucency projects an intimate illuminating glow. Due to the handmade nature, variances in the glass will occur. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Inspired by the 1950s brutalist movement, this one-light, iron sconce is crafted out of hand cut geometric shapes, welded together into a tribal-like pattern. The wax finish helps keep the sconce natural – perfect for horizontal or vertical mounting. Damp rated and approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Estelle is a gleaming example of the latest renaissance in industrial design. The steel frame is finished in an antique brass and mounts directly to the wall. The crystal facet acts as a diffuser, creating stunning prisms of light that soften the overall design. Also available as a matching pendant (49127) and blackened bronze chandelier (89700).

A modern sensibility defines this midcentury sconce finished in antique brass with a bronze backplate. The scale makes this the perfect sconce for spotlighting your favorite art piece or next to a bed when space is tight and a nightstand won't fit.

This tuxedo-style sconce bestows a classic element to any façade it graces. The two-light fixture features clear fluted glass shades, fixed on a heritage brass steel plate, that maximize the light and add texture to its directional pattern. Pair with another to create a double vanity story in a powder room, or for a more dramatic effect on a wallscape. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Three clear seedy glass plates form the arresting single-light Mugler Sconce. The steel frame's antique brass finish sets a stylish and graceful tone. The unique glass plates, each etched with an oblong octagon, add a touch of curiosity, with varying finishes so no two being exactly alike. Each plate of glass is almost like melting ice, suspended in time. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

The teardrop seedy glass shade houses a single bulb of your choice, and is suspended from a square, natural iron back plate. Mount multiples down a hallway to create drama or use two to flank a mirror in a bathroom. Shown with a Nostalgic spiral radio bulb.

The simple and sophisticated style of this sconce goes a long way. This clear, fluted glass fixture features an heritage brass belt that cinches the shape, adding a polished element to its textured form. Versatile, this piece works well in almost any style setting. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

This tuxedo-style sconce bestows a classic element to any façade it graces. The two-light fixture features clear fluted glass shades, fixed on a pale brass steel plate, that maximize the light and add texture to its directional pattern. Pair with another to create a double vanity story in a powder room, or for a more dramatic effect on a wallscape. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Inspired by the lustrousness of our Waldorf Chandelier, we've created a smaller version fit for a wallspace. Depth and scale are just as transformative, as angular steel shards in varying sizes extend from the center. Steel rods are interspersed throughout the vibrant form finished in heritage brass, creating a stunning contrast from the metal form. Available in a vintage silver finish (49276). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Keep your bedtime reads well-lit with this simply stunning wall sconce. The adjsutable position of the sleek steel frame makes it the perfect task light for bedrooms or directional lighting option for an entryway. Spotlight a space by pairing with another for an even more dramatic lightscape. Also available in vintage silver and antique brass finishes. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Sleek and stylish, the modern form of this heritage brass sconce offers a clean and streamlined visual to a wall space. The rectangular profile lends a contemporary touch to traditional lighting designs, and its steel form delivers a slight industrial appeal. When in use, the sconce appears lucent thanks to the ultramodern LED light. Its slender silhouette makes this a great light option for small spaces. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

A modest lighting solution for exterior spaces that illuminates its surroundings while delivering a contemporary look to a space. Aged-brass and frosted glass unite to create the unobtrusive profile of this outdoor sconce. The slightly tapered shape of the shade works to softly scintillate the light across a patio or porch. Approved for use in outdoor areas.

Rebelling from standard, lackluster outdoor lighting, this fixture brings artistic flair into natural environments. The shape is an inspiration of mid-century design, taking a classic indoor design and reinterpreting it for stylish outdoor spaces. The dome light is crafted from opal glass and the structure from steel finished in aged brass. The finial contrasts the shade in an antique brass finish. Approved for use in outdoor areas.

Vintage meets modern with the Waits Outdoor Sconce. This two-light fixture combines steel with an aged-brass finish and opal glass to create a contemporary yet timeless design. For a more dynamic look and a little more luster, consider pairing this piece with another. Approved for use in outdoor areas.

The latest addition to the Parrish series is a single-light outdoor sconce. A steel frame finished in aged brass suspends a clear glass cylinder shade on a solitary slip hook. Though classic and simple, its sleek lines lend a bit of an industrial edge. Shown with an Edison bulb. Also available in aged iron (49196). Approved for use in outdoor areas.

The mid-century craftsman style of this sconce makes it intriguing, modern and artistic. The steel frame is almost sculptural, featuring a linear pattern that is hammered and finished in aged brass, adding to the mid-century modern feel. It conceals a sheet of opal glass that filters the light from two bulbs, so the light it emits spreads warmly outward. Also available in aged iron (49181). Approved for outdoor use.

In a classic fashion, this multi-light sconce revels in sophisticated simplicity. The steel wall mount is finished in a stunning heritage brass, and features two arms that showcase capsule-shaped frosted glass shades which help to subtly diffuse the light. Each shade encases two bulbs, delivering an extra element of shine to a wall space. A great light solution for a vanity or powder room. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

The traditional hourglass shape gets a modern revamp in this contemporary steel sconce. The glow comes from the opal glass shade, which conceals two bulbs—one up and one down—to cast ample, warm light throughout a space. Its linear style is what makes it so modern, though the aged brass accents also lend an updated look, too. Approved for use in outdoor areas. Also available in Aged Iron (49184).

Derived from the popular Stefan Indoor Sconce (49999), this outdoor-safe version combines aged brass with frosted glass and an antique brass finished steel to create a sophisticated and modern look. Consider pairs flanking a front door. Also available in aged iron (49187). Approved for use in outdoor areas.

Inspired by our indoor version, the clear teardrop glass shade of this outdoor sconce houses the bulb of your choice as it is suspended from a square aged brass finished steel back plate. Mount multiples along a patio space to add tons of light and create drama. Bring the look inside with the coordinating indoor version (49986). Shown with small clear tubular bulb. Also comes in aged iron (49190). Approved for use in outdoor areas.

A natural iron flat bar anchors three vintage brass hammered plates in this six-light sconce. Each disc conceals two sockets, so light will emanate evenly from each side. Mount across the top of a mirror in the powder room or on either side of a mirror in the hallway.

This handsomely structured lantern sconce is upscale in form and style. It is made from aged brass finished steel, tapered in form, and designed with slight, exposed details and contrasting antique brass finish accents to exude an industrial feel. A sleeve of opaque opal glass rests inside, filtering the light from a standard bulb. Approved for use in outdoor areas.

Bringing the outdoors in brings continuity to modern living. True to its namesake, the Hive Sconce is inspired by one of nature's most fascinating habitats. Viewing the piece from below will reveal a modular honeycomb shape in antique brass.
This starburst design in antique brass has eight lights and works as well on the wall as it does as a ceiling mount. Shown with small clear tubular bulbs. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Brass has been cast to mimic molten metal in this romantic wall sconce. The fluid nature of the matte brass is evocative of Salvador Dali's surreal designs. Topped with an off-white linen Uno mounted shade.

This organic brass sconce finished in gold leaf speaks to movement as it arches from the wall. Looks best when placed so you can take advantage of its profile and the dramatic shadow it casts on the wall. Perfect for hallways. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

Barry's personal favorite from the new collection, the Aramis Sconce is avant garde, commanding and totally unique. Barry was inspired by McQueen's ponytailed models with face masks, and this evolving into the "couture for the home". Cast in brass with a convex glass shield and a brass wire "ponytail", this is fashion fused nature.

The frosted glass globe houses a bulb of your choice as it rests on the round steel arm, which is plated in antique brass. Mount multiples down a hallway to create drama or place them on either side of a mirror. Damp rated: Approved for use in covered outdoor areas or bathrooms.

This polished brass sconce exemplifies simple elegance. The gently shaped circular back plate glows with the reflection of the light bulb. Perfect for a hallway or powder room. Shown with an antique radio bulb.
Inspired by one of our best selling mirror collections, this gold leafed iron wall sconce has two lights and an antiqued mirrored back plate.

The clear teardrop glass shade houses the bulb of your choice as it is suspended from a square antique brass back plate. Mount multiples down a hallway to create drama. Coordinates with similar table lamp (49889) and floor lamp (79889). Shown with small clear tubular bulb. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

An adaptation of one of our most popular chandeliers, this antique brass sconce has five lights and can be hung horizontally or vertically. This piece can also be mounted to the ceiling. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

A perfect balance of proportions, this double sconce sets frosted glass globes against antique brass arms and back plate. It’s a sophisticated element for modern settings and can be horizontally or vertically mounted. Damp rated: Approved for use in covered outdoor areas or bathrooms.

Delicate clear seedy glass is the star on this floating sconce design. A smoke glass panel has been added to the bottom half of the glass plate, creating another layer of dimensionality. The double socket attached to the antique brass backplate generates a warm glow that is diffused against the murky glass. Shown with small clear tubular bulbs. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Finish may vary.

A design derivative based on our popular Yale chandelier (86762). This 1 light sconce has rows of delicate antique brass chains draped over the frame with staggered lengths giving it a tassel effect. Shown with antique tubular bulbs. Height of sconce and chain lengths may vary.
Lawrence Sconce

A design derivative based on our popular Yale chandelier (86762). This 1 light sconce has rows of delicate antique brass chains draped over the frame with staggered lengths giving it a tassel effect. Shown with antique tubular bulbs. Height of sconce and chain lengths may vary.

The Khloe Sconce features a steel backplate, finished in antique brass, that gives way to a matching, adjustable arm with pivot. At the end of the arm lies an elegant, opal glass shade, housing two bulbs. The white and brass finishes combine to yield a classically elegant design. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.
Keiran Sconce

The Karina Sconce's seedy glass shade combines with its antique brass-finished steel backplate to a wholly unique and warming glow. The form and finish of the shade almost resemble a carved piece of granite. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Finish may vary.

Art purveyors will love the Kenley Sconce's playful splatter design. The opal glass globe pops off of the antique brass backplate, or canvas in this instance. Opal glass combines with an antique brass finish to create a graphic statement that can't be ignored. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

The versatile wall sconce version of our Iris Pendant evokes an eastern accent while remaining crisp and modern. Finished in antique brass and off-white linen. Perfect in a hall, bath or dining room. Also available as pendant (DD49007). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

The iconic two-light sconce in contrasting bronze and antique brass, has adjustable pivoting shades, yields a playfully modern piece. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

The evolution of the Ramirez design family. An organically-shaped, opal glass shade rests atop an antique brass-finished steel arm, creating a soft statement piece. Also available in vintage silver (49157). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.
Jerome Sconce

A simple, delicate, and geometric two-light sconce is perfect for small spaces that need a little extra light. The hammered vintage brass finish adds a contemporary touch to its iron base. Also available in white (42235), bronze (42236), and natural iron with brass welds (42238). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

A sheet of vintage brass has been split in two, pressed and folded into the multifaceted cone-like Liam Sconces. The set of two is ideal for a short hallway or flanking a mirror. Creates warm, indirect light through each opening. Also available in bronze (42233).

Cousin of the popular Yasmin design, the Inwood Sconce is highlighted by two off-white linen shades, emitting light atop and below the sconce. Finished in antique brass throughout. Also available in vintage silver (49041). outdoor areas.

Minimal in visual weight, but heavy in design detail. The Havana Sconce is an arresting blend of varying steel finishes. Bronze steel pipes give way to duelling antique brass shades, with antique brass details to match. Each shade features a matte white lining, creating additional light. Also available in polished nickel (49055).

A torch for the new age, the Griffin Sconce is a unique option for true design enthusiasts seeking something with flair. Frosted glass shades diffuse the light, creating a soft glow that contrasts the sharp angles and bronze finish with antique brass details. Shown with a clear globe bulb. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

This traditional sconce has been updated for a more contemporary feel. The brass rod has a clear crystal shell accented with antique brass accents. Topped with a white linen shade. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

The corresponding serving tray to our Wakefield Ice Bucket (6825), this piece lets you serve your spread in style. The hexagonal shape of the white marble tray creates sharp, clean lines that draw the eye and add depth when resting on a tabletop. The antique brass handles are both sculptural and functional. A sophisticated way to serve hor d'oeuvres at your next soirée. Food safe. Marble may vary.

Perfectly sized vintage brass handles make this white marble tray very easy to carry. Use the linear surface for a row of sushi or to display perfume bottles. This versatile tray can be useful anywhere. Food safe, but use care as marble stains easily.

This neutral set of leather ottomans is a host’s dream. Immaculately stitched cream leather wraps the entire cushioned seat, with a platform base that’s plated with an antique brass finish. Together, they form one beautiful ottoman, but they also have a secret purpose. The quadrants individually fit our Nomad Cocktail Table (DC2001) perfectly, so you can tuck some underneath as extra seating for entertaining. Genius! Leather grain and tone may vary.

Though crafted to function as a tray, this piece could display as art on its own. Perfectly square, but anything from ordinary, its made and finished to look identical to marble, but without the weight so it’s easy to carry around. Sleek curves slope down into the center to keep everything in the vessel while maintaining its natural allure.
Bordeaux Large Tray

This vase is as elegant in style as it is stately in form. A burnt smoke glass is trimmed with an antique brass band that accentuates the warm tones of this rounded vase. Watertight, it would work wonderfully displaying a bouquet on an entryway table or console. As an alternative to a floral vase, this piece easily doubles as a candleholder. Pair with the larger versions to stage a dramatic scene. Finish may vary.

This set of four textured aluminum trays was inspired by the exploration of modern shapes and artistic finishes. The set is cleverly designed so that the three smaller trays rest neatly inside the larger one, and each size is given a unique finish in varying degrees of distressed copper. The fluid finishes pair beautifully to bring out the textures of the metal and add color. They’re great for entertaining, laid out in a spread or simply as a decorative accent. Finish may vary.

This set of four textured aluminum trays was inspired by the exploration of modern shapes and artistic finishes. The set is cleverly designed so that the three smaller trays rest neatly inside the larger one, and each size is given a unique finish in varying degrees of distressed brass. The fluid finishes pair beautifully to bring out the textures of the metal and add color. They’re great for entertaining, laid out in a spread or simply as a decorative accent. Finish may vary.

The mixture of simple geometric forms create a dynamic visual element with this set of beaker-style vases. Modern in form, smoke luster glass with antique brass necks unite to create each individually shaped piece. These watertight vases are a sophisticated way to showcase beautiful blooms. Out of fresh flowers? This set looks just as stunning as an accent for a console or desk. Finish may vary.

Unique in form and functional in design, this valve-shaped vase tugs on our design heart strings. Cast aluminum in an antique bronze finish is sculpted into a vase with three stalks in a tapered design that are perfect for adding a few stems of your favorite flower. No flowers? This sculptural piece creates interest and intrigue all on its own. Watertight.
Layered geometric wall sculpture features hammered open iron squares joined together with touches of dark golden brass.
Circular disk carved wall plaque with brass foil overlay in metallic gold finish. Hang alone or group.

This iron wall art is made up of over 100 discs, each hand-burnt to create unique colorations, then welded together in a layered, freeform composition. Whether it’s displayed horizontally or vertically, the result will be a one-of-a-kind play of light and shadow. The inspiration may be mid-century, yet this wall decor adds dimension and texture to any room.

The Horner Bookshelf features a clean frame that will let your treasured books and collectibles shine. Finished in a beautiful smoke gray that highlights the natural wood grain. Also available in sable (5500).

Brilliant as a room screen or as decor against an expansive wall, this modern piece solves a variety of design issues. The rectangular iron panel is entirely finished with gold leaf and frames a geometric overlay of intersecting circles. There’s no way you can have a bad day with this shiny and bubbly piece around. Designed to pair seamlessly with the right version (4609) for a continuous design. Gold leaf finish may vary.

A study in geometrics, our Weaver Short Etagere possesses classic style in modern form. The multi-tiered unit features white marble and clear glass shelves that contemporizes the antique brass finish of its iron frame. The open construction creates an airy effect and works to showcase your prized possessions in full form. Its smaller stature allows this piece to double as a stationary bar cart or console table. Available in a larger version (6861).

A study in geometrics, our Weaver Etagere possesses classic style in modern form. The multi-tiered unit features white marble and clear glass shelves that contemporizes the antique brass finish of its stately iron frame. The open construction creates an airy effect and works to showcase your prized possessions in full form. Available in a smaller version (6860).

Brilliant as a room screen or as decor against an expansive wall, this modern piece solves a variety of design issues. The rectangular iron panel is entirely finished with gold leaf and frames a geometric overlay of intersecting circles. There’s no way you can have a bad day with this shiny and bubbly piece around. Designed to pair seamlessly with the left version (4608) for a continuous design. Gold leaf finish may vary

Style and elegance come together in this entertaining cabinet. Built from solid oak, it’s finished entirely in a dark sable veneer with shining accents of champagne brass handles and foiled-glass inlay details. Open the doors and discover two adjustable glass shelves and a mirrored backsplash lit from led lights concealed in the design. Inside you’ll also find two pull-out drawers and table extension with matching hardware. The legs are connected by a brace and levelers to keep it steady.

Ease into the slight incline and you’ll never want to get out—with the comfort of plush cushioning at all angles, you’ll be settled in for the night. It even has looks to boot; unique modern lines, pipe detail and tapered wood legs give this chair class and style. Also comes in cognac leather (8091) and muslin (8092).

ItemName: Turner Sofa Stillwater Tweed Grey Ash
ItemDescription: The voluptuous Turner Sofa is all glamour, appealing to style makers who appreciate bold design. The entire silhouette is one long, sexy curve. This plush design is sleek but inviting, making Turner the perfect anchor for any room that is built for entertaining. Float two facing each other with a round cocktail table in the middle or use our elegant drinks tables to create an intimate lounge-like vibe.

This Scandinavian style frame is a lesson in elevated minimalism. A slight wing on the back and an unexpected angle where the back and seat meet gives the piece a unique profile. The simple design will neutralize any over-styled space, commanding just the right amount of attention. Covered in Muslin, allowing you to slipcover or upholster in the fabric of your choice.

It’s in the details that make the Catalina Chaise a lounging beauty. It is designed in a modern way, but softened with rolling curves, rounded angles and an extra plush seat. Up close, observe all the immaculate details, like corner pleating, self welting and grey ash finished tapered legs. Upholstered with a sumptuous crushed velvet in a bold shade of mulberry, this hue complements a palette of almost any range. Also available in Stone Boucle (8109) and Muslin (8114).

Influenced by mid-century design, the Christophe's linear channeling and metal capped legs elevate what could be ordinary into something special. Upholstered with a light metallic silver leather that adds a sense of glamour. Also available in Driftwood Tweed (8068), Sharkskin Velvet Grey Ash (8002), Graphite Leather Grey Ash (8003), Indigo Leather Dark Walnut (8069), Oatmeal Linen Dark Walnut (8001) and Muslin Dark Walnut (8005). Matching Christophe Sofa available.

Form meets function as modern meets traditional with this bar stool. The black leather seat lends a contemporary touch to the traditional style of the solid walnut-finish wood legs, while an antique brass stretcher adds support and acts as an accent to the dark façade. Featuring a low back and no arms, the minimalist profile of this piece makes it ideal for tucking under a counter. Finish and leather may vary.

Form meets function as modern meets traditional with this counter stool. The black leather seat lends a contemporary touch to the traditional style of the solid walnut-finish wood legs, while an antique brass stretcher adds support and acts as an accent to the dark façade. Featuring a low back and no arms, the minimalist profile of this piece makes it ideal for tucking under a counter. Finish and leather may vary.

Crafted entirely from natural materials, this stool is anything but simple. The open pattern is hand-woven with flat rattan, styled in the traditional cane pattern, though exaggerated in a modern way for a hint of added drama. The frame is also made of rattan, built with round poles—for added support, a pole has been added in the low-profile back. This version is finished in espresso, but it is also available in a natural tone (5537). Also available as a bar stool (5534).

A breathtaking blend of finishes catch the eye with the classic style of our Walton Chair. Solid oak in a sable finish frames a plush indigo leather seat that accentuates its timeless profile. The mix of natural materials and rich hues makes it perfect for a formal setting or a well-styled study. Leather may vary.

Inspired by a teak and leather chair spotted at a Parisian flea market, we added jute for a more natural feel. The contrast between the contemporary profile and hand-woven rope is sublime. Grooves on each arm adjust the chair to four different heights for easy lounging.

Craftsman style handiwork and modern elegance make a beautiful collaboration in this dynamic chair. It’s made entirely from solid oak and is finished in a dark umber veneer that has wonderful wood textures you can see and feel. Turned details, a coal-toned leather seat and brass inlay in the top rail all bring a sense of sophistication and edge to the design. Also comes in muslin (8094).

An arresting blend of finishes draws the eye in on this European style. The satin walnut frame curves upward to meet the modified barrel design featuring a glossy black lacquer. The plush black leather seat makes it perfect for a formal dining room or well-styled reading nook.

Crafted entirely from natural materials, this dining chair is anything but simple. The open pattern is handwoven with flat rattan, styled in the traditional cane pattern, though exaggerated in a modern way for a hint of added drama. The frame is also made of rattan, built with round poles—for added support, a pole has been added in the low-profile back. This version is finished in an espresso tone, but is also available in a natural finish.
Tapered mahogany legs with brass feet pair with splayed legs to support the chair's plush seat and c-shaped back. Finished in glazed mottled brown top grain leather, mahogany finish on wood.

This exquisite frame is perfectly poised, perched on delicate legs that are as faint as insects'. The natural iron body has been hand-forged, yielding soft impressions along the sharp-angled frame. The tight seat and bolster back cushion are covered in a delicate juniper silk. Finish may vary.
Transitional styled box style top grain leather seat with low curved back is supported by antique brass finish frame. For counters and bars.

Rattan has been used for centuries to create impeccably designed, durable furniture. Continuing this tradition we've created the Tarbela Chair, which was inspired by the exceptional beauty of the native Indonesian Cendrawasih bird, otherwise known as the bird of paradise. Rattan is first steamed, shaped and structured manually to create the sturdy and stylish tub-like design. Complete with a matte black finish for a refined touch that would look stunning in any setting

A new version of our ever-popular Calvin Barstools. We dropped the back and arm height so it could easily slide under the bar top to provide more room when not in use. The top grain brindle-colored leather combines beautifully with the antique brass frame.

Transitional box style low barstool with low curved back is supported by polished nickel finish on stainless steel frame. Seat upholstery features top grain seat and detailed with black and white hide back. Hide patterns will differ and color will vary.

A new version of our ever-popular Calvin Barstools. We dropped the back and arm height so it could easily slide under the counter to provide more room when not in use. The top grain brindle-colored leather in combination with antique brass frame work beautifully together.
Transitional styled box style top grain leather seat with low curved back is supported by antique brass finish frame and bars.

The perfect transitional club chair with a tub chair silhouette. The curved back and arms make it comfortable, the brindle leather makes it luxurious and the antique brass frame makes it sophisticated. Great in a den or office.

Occasional chairs are known for their sense of casual luxury. The Kitts Chair is no exception, built plush and sturdy for whatever your lifestyle brings. The curved back gives you ample support, while the sloping arms keep you curled up inside. Upholstered in a plush, marigold velvet with welting details to accentuate the curves. The base rests on tapered, light bronze finished metal legs that have a hint of glisten. Also available in Flax Linen (8119) and Marigold Velvet (8118).

ItemName: Springsteen Chair Flint Velvet Champagne Swivel
ItemDescription: Springsteen Chair Flint Velvet Champagne Swivel

This handsome devil is just like our popular Turner Sofa, built a little smaller for a studio, loft or inviting formal space. The blend of upholstery and soft hue are all glamour, appealing to style makers who appreciate bold design. The entire silhouette is one long, sexy curve. Float two facing each other with a round cocktail table in the middle or use our elegant drinks tables to create an intimate lounge-like vibe. Also comes in mist velvet (8095) and muslin (8097).

ItemName: Beck Chair Stone Leather Grey Ash
ItemDescription: This Scandinavian style frame is a lesson in elevated minimalism. A slight wing on the back and an unexpected angle where the back and seat meet gives the piece a unique profile. The simple design will neutralize any over-styled space, commanding just the right amount of attention.

A traditional Chesterfield gets an update in our Klein Sofa. Its classic features are in the deep button-tufting and rolled arms, but virtually everything else has been given a modern lift. The curved back and a custom juniper blue chenille update the design. The fabric has a silver accent peeking through, and a deeper seat for serious lounging nights—you’ll love the extra comfy down fill. It’s finished with self welting and grey ash finished maple wood legs.

ItemName: Beck Settee Indigo Boucle Dark Walnut
ItemDescription: This Scandinavian style frame is a lesson in elevated minimalism. A slight wing on the back and unexpected angle at the base give the Beck a unique profile. The slender frame makes this settee ideal for a smaller sitting area or bedroom. Covered in Indigo Boucle, with inherent loops and curls that add warmth to the midcentury-inspired design. Varying shades of blue make the Beck the personification of the popular hue. Splayed kiln dried, dark walnut legs match its simple, stripped-down frame.

ItemName: Capri Chair Juniper Leather Champagne Swivel
ItemDescription: Deep, elegant tufting comes together with soft curves and a champagne-finished swivel base to create the classically stylish Capri Chair. This updated take on the Springsteen Chair is covered in Juniper Leather, highlighted by its greyed, teal coloring. This top grain, aniline leather allows for natural, unique distinctions and markings to shine through. With each pull, stretch or impression, the Capri becomes even more distinct.

ItemName: Springsteen Chair Indigo Tweed Champagne Swivel
ItemDescription: Style reigns supreme in this sensuous swivel chair plucked straight from the seventies. The inviting barrel back, plush channeling and sleek satin brass plinth base create the perfect club chair. Place a pair in your favorite entertaining space with petite drinks tables or use four around a cocktail table instead of the traditional sofa and chair combo. These are meant to be touted, not tucked away!

ItemName: Turner Sofa Indigo Velvet Dark Walnut
ItemDescription: The voluptuous Turner Sofa is all glamour, appealing to style makers who appreciate bold design. The entire silhouette is one long, sexy curve. This plush design is sleek but inviting, making Turner the perfect anchor for any room that is built for entertaining. Float two facing each other with a round cocktail table in the middle or use our elegant drinks tables to create an intimate lounge-like vibe.

ItemDescription: This Scandinavian style frame is a lesson in elevated minimalism. A slight wing on the back and an unexpected angle where the back and seat meet gives the piece a unique profile. The simple design will neutralize any over-styled space, commanding just the right amount of attention.

ItemName: Seger Chair Driftwood Tweed Grey Ash
ItemDescription: Much like its namesake, Seger is a timeless classic. The refined silhouette is accented with creatively spaced decorative nail heads running along the chair's outer curves. A horizontal channel in the center of the back adds visual interest. Perfect as a pair or on its own in a stylish reading nook.

Made with hundreds of buri sticks, derived from a palm in the Asian tropics, the fixture is formed using traditional hand-weave practices used to make baskets and plates. The ancient construction technique gets a modern update with a dark gray finish. The open-weave allows light to graciously disperse through the frame, and the antique brass steel pipe adds shine to a space. Finish may vary. Approved for use in covered outdoor areas. Additional pipe available (PIPE-101).

The inspiration for this settee comes from a vintage Parisian find, adored for its unique shape and traditional styling. Though slightly updated, it stays true to the fanciful air of its predecessor, with welting details that accentuate the curves. It's built a bit longer than a traditional settee and the back cushions are made just a little smaller than the seat cushions-which have a split seam-in order to create a playful imbalance. Sits on dark walnut finished maple wood legs.
